169namespace WTF {
170template <>
171struct LogArgument<URL> {
172 static String toString(const URL& url)
173 {
174#if !LOG_DISABLED
175 static const unsigned maximumURLLengthForLogging = 512;
176
177 if (url.string().length() < maximumURLLengthForLogging)
178 return url.string();
179 return url.string().substring(0, maximumURLLengthForLogging) + "...";
180#else
181 UNUSED_PARAM(url);
182 return "[url]";
183#endif
184 }
185};
186}

218String convertEnumerationToString(HTMLMediaElement::ReadyState enumerationValue)
219{
220 static const NeverDestroyed<String> values[] = {
221 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("HAVE_NOTHING"),
222 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("HAVE_METADATA"),
223 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("HAVE_CURRENT_DATA"),
224 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("HAVE_FUTURE_DATA"),
225 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA"),
226 };
227 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_NOTHING) == 0, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_NOTHING is not 0 as expected");
228 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_METADATA) == 1, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_METADATA is not 1 as expected");
229 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_CURRENT_DATA) == 2, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_CURRENT_DATA is not 2 as expected");
230 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_FUTURE_DATA) == 3, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_FUTURE_DATA is not 3 as expected");
231 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA) == 4, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA is not 4 as expected");
232 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue) < WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(values));
233 return values[static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue)];
234}
235
236String convertEnumerationToString(HTMLMediaElement::NetworkState enumerationValue)
237{
238 static const NeverDestroyed<String> values[] = {
239 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("NETWORK_EMPTY"),

245 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::NETWORK_IDLE) == 1, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::NETWORK_IDLE is not 1 as expected");
246 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::NETWORK_LOADING) == 2, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::NETWORK_LOADING is not 2 as expected");
247 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElementEnums::NETWORK_NO_SOURCE) == 3, "HTMLMediaElementEnums::NETWORK_NO_SOURCE is not 3 as expected");
248 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue) < WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(values));
249 return values[static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue)];
250}

252String convertEnumerationToString(HTMLMediaElement::AutoplayEventPlaybackState enumerationValue)
253{
254 static const NeverDestroyed<String> values[] = {
255 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("None"),
256 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("PreventedAutoplay"),
257 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("StartedWithUserGesture"),
258 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("StartedWithoutUserGesture"),
259 };
260 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElement::AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None) == 0, "AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None is not 0 as expected");
261 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElement::AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay) == 1, "AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay is not 1 as expected");
262 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElement::AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithUserGesture) == 2, "AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithUserGesture is not 2 as expected");
263 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(HTMLMediaElement::AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithoutUserGesture) == 3, "AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithoutUserGesture is not 3 as expected");
264 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue) < WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(values));
265 return values[static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue)];
266}

316
317struct MediaElementSessionInfo {
318 const MediaElementSession* session;
319 MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose purpose;
320
321 MonotonicTime timeOfLastUserInteraction;
322 bool canShowControlsManager : 1;
323 bool isVisibleInViewportOrFullscreen : 1;
324 bool isLargeEnoughForMainContent : 1;
325 bool isPlayingAudio : 1;
326 bool hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying : 1;
327};
328
329static MediaElementSessionInfo mediaElementSessionInfoForSession(const MediaElementSession& session, MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose purpose)
330{
331 const HTMLMediaElement& element = session.element();
332 return {
333 &session,
334 purpose,
335 session.mostRecentUserInteractionTime(),
336 session.canShowControlsManager(purpose),
337 element.isFullscreen() || element.isVisibleInViewport(),
338 session.isLargeEnoughForMainContent(MediaSessionMainContentPurpose::MediaControls),
339 element.isPlaying() && element.hasAudio() && !element.muted(),
340 element.hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying()
341 };
342}
343
344static bool preferMediaControlsForCandidateSessionOverOtherCandidateSession(const MediaElementSessionInfo& session, const MediaElementSessionInfo& otherSession)
345{
346 MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose purpose = session.purpose;
347 ASSERT(purpose == otherSession.purpose);
348
349 // For the controls manager and MediaSession, prioritize visible media over offscreen media.
350 if ((purpose == MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose::ControlsManager || purpose == MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose::MediaSession)
351 && session.isVisibleInViewportOrFullscreen != otherSession.isVisibleInViewportOrFullscreen)
352 return session.isVisibleInViewportOrFullscreen;
353
354 // For Now Playing and MediaSession, prioritize elements that would normally satisfy main content.
355 if ((purpose == MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose::NowPlaying || purpose == MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose::MediaSession)
356 && session.isLargeEnoughForMainContent != otherSession.isLargeEnoughForMainContent)
357 return session.isLargeEnoughForMainContent;
358
359 // For MediaSession, prioritize elements that have been played before.
360 if (purpose == MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose::MediaSession
361 && session.hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying != otherSession.hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying)
362 return session.hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying;
363
364 // As a tiebreaker, prioritize elements that the user recently interacted with.
365 return session.timeOfLastUserInteraction > otherSession.timeOfLastUserInteraction;
366}
367
368static bool mediaSessionMayBeConfusedWithMainContent(const MediaElementSessionInfo& session, MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose purpose)
369{
370 if (purpose == MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose::MediaSession)
371 return false;
372
373 if (purpose == MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose::NowPlaying)
374 return session.isPlayingAudio;
375
376 if (!session.isVisibleInViewportOrFullscreen)
377 return false;
378
379 if (!session.isLargeEnoughForMainContent)
380 return false;
381
382 // Even if this video is not a candidate, if it is visible to the user and large enough
383 // to be main content, it poses a risk for being confused with main content.
384 return true;
385}

387HTMLMediaElement::HTMLMediaElement(const QualifiedName& tagName, Document& document, bool createdByParser)
388 : HTMLElement(tagName, document)
389 , ActiveDOMObject(document)
390 , m_progressEventTimer(*this, &HTMLMediaElement::progressEventTimerFired)
391 , m_playbackProgressTimer(*this, &HTMLMediaElement::playbackProgressTimerFired)
392 , m_scanTimer(*this, &HTMLMediaElement::scanTimerFired)
393 , m_playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTimer(*this, &HTMLMediaElement::playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTimerFired)
394 , m_seekToPlaybackPositionEndedTimer(*this, &HTMLMediaElement::seekToPlaybackPositionEndedTimerFired)
395 , m_lastTimeUpdateEventMovieTime(MediaTime::positiveInfiniteTime())
396 , m_firstTimePlaying(true)
397 , m_playing(false)
398 , m_isWaitingUntilMediaCanStart(false)
399 , m_shouldDelayLoadEvent(false)
400 , m_haveFiredLoadedData(false)
401 , m_inActiveDocument(true)
402 , m_autoplaying(true)
403 , m_muted(false)
404 , m_explicitlyMuted(false)
405 , m_initiallyMuted(false)
406 , m_paused(true)
407 , m_seeking(false)
408 , m_seekRequested(false)
409 , m_sentStalledEvent(false)
410 , m_sentEndEvent(false)
411 , m_pausedInternal(false)
412 , m_closedCaptionsVisible(false)
413 , m_webkitLegacyClosedCaptionOverride(false)
414 , m_completelyLoaded(false)
415 , m_havePreparedToPlay(false)
416 , m_parsingInProgress(createdByParser)
417 , m_elementIsHidden(document.hidden())
418 , m_creatingControls(false)
419 , m_receivedLayoutSizeChanged(false)
420 , m_hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying(false)
421 , m_hasEverHadAudio(false)
422 , m_hasEverHadVideo(false)
423 , m_mediaControlsDependOnPageScaleFactor(false)
424 , m_haveSetUpCaptionContainer(false)
425 , m_isScrubbingRemotely(false)
426 , m_waitingToEnterFullscreen(false)
427 , m_showPoster(true)
428 , m_tracksAreReady(true)
429 , m_haveVisibleTextTrack(false)
430 , m_processingPreferenceChange(false)
431 , m_shouldAudioPlaybackRequireUserGesture(document.topDocument().audioPlaybackRequiresUserGesture() && !processingUserGestureForMedia())
432 , m_shouldVideoPlaybackRequireUserGesture(document.topDocument().videoPlaybackRequiresUserGesture() && !processingUserGestureForMedia())
433#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
434 , m_remote(RemotePlayback::create(*this))
435#endif
436#if !RELEASE_LOG_DISABLED
437 , m_logger(&document.logger())
438 , m_logIdentifier(uniqueLogIdentifier())
439#endif
440{
441 allMediaElements().add(this);
442
443 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
444
445 setHasCustomStyleResolveCallbacks();
446
447 InspectorInstrumentation::addEventListenersToNode(*this);
448}
449
450void HTMLMediaElement::initializeMediaSession()
451{
452 ASSERT(!m_mediaSession);
453 m_mediaSession = makeUnique<MediaElementSession>(*this);
454
455 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForFullscreen);
456 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequirePageConsentToLoadMedia);
457#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
458 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToAutoplayToExternalDevice);
459#endif
460 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
461 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequirePlaybackToControlControlsManager);
462
463 auto& document = this->document();
464 auto* page = document.page();
465
466 if (document.settings().invisibleAutoplayNotPermitted())
467 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::InvisibleAutoplayNotPermitted);
468
469 if (document.ownerElement() || !document.isMediaDocument()) {
470 if (m_shouldVideoPlaybackRequireUserGesture) {
471 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoRateChange);
472 if (document.settings().requiresUserGestureToLoadVideo())
473 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForLoad);
474 }
475
476 if (page && page->isLowPowerModeEnabled())
477 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoDueToLowPowerMode);
478
479 if (m_shouldAudioPlaybackRequireUserGesture)
480 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForAudioRateChange);
481
482#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
483 if (m_shouldVideoPlaybackRequireUserGesture || m_shouldAudioPlaybackRequireUserGesture)
484 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToShowPlaybackTargetPicker);
485#endif
486
487 if (!document.mediaDataLoadsAutomatically() && !document.quirks().needsPreloadAutoQuirk())
488 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::AutoPreloadingNotPermitted);
489
490 if (document.settings().mainContentUserGestureOverrideEnabled())
491 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::OverrideUserGestureRequirementForMainContent);
492 }
493
494#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
495 if (!document.settings().videoPlaybackRequiresUserGesture() && !document.settings().audioPlaybackRequiresUserGesture()) {
496 // Relax RequireUserGestureForFullscreen when videoPlaybackRequiresUserGesture and audioPlaybackRequiresUserGesture is not set:
497 m_mediaSession->removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForFullscreen);
498 }
499#endif
500
501 registerWithDocument(document);
502
503#if USE(AUDIO_SESSION) && PLATFORM(MAC)
504 AudioSession::sharedSession().addMutedStateObserver(this);
505#endif
506
507 m_mediaSession->clientWillBeginAutoplaying();
508}
509
510HTMLMediaElement::~HTMLMediaElement()
511{
512 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
513
514 beginIgnoringTrackDisplayUpdateRequests();
515 allMediaElements().remove(this);
516
517 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
518 unregisterWithDocument(document());
519
520#if USE(AUDIO_SESSION) && PLATFORM(MAC)
521 AudioSession::sharedSession().removeMutedStateObserver(this);
522#endif
523
524 if (m_audioTracks)
525 m_audioTracks->clearElement();
526 if (m_textTracks)
527 m_textTracks->clearElement();
528 if (m_videoTracks)
529 m_videoTracks->clearElement();
530
531#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
532 if (hasEventListeners(eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent) || m_remote->hasAvailabilityCallbacks()) {
533 m_hasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners = false;
534 if (m_mediaSession)
535 m_mediaSession->setHasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners(false);
536 updateMediaState();
537 }
538#endif
539
540 if (m_mediaController) {
541 m_mediaController->removeMediaElement(*this);
542 m_mediaController = nullptr;
543 }
544
545#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
546 detachMediaSource();
547#endif
548
549#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
550 webkitSetMediaKeys(nullptr);
551#endif
552
553#if ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
554 if (m_mediaKeys) {
555 m_mediaKeys->detachCDMClient(*this);
556 if (m_player)
557 m_player->cdmInstanceDetached(m_mediaKeys->cdmInstance());
558 }
559#endif
560
561 if (m_isolatedWorld)
562 m_isolatedWorld->clearWrappers();
563
564 m_completelyLoaded = true;
565
566 if (m_player) {
567 m_player->invalidate();
568 m_player = nullptr;
569 }
570
571 m_mediaSession = nullptr;
572 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
573
574 if (!m_blobURLForReading.isEmpty())
575 ThreadableBlobRegistry::unregisterBlobURL(m_blobURLForReading);
576}
577
578RefPtr<HTMLMediaElement> HTMLMediaElement::bestMediaElementForRemoteControls(MediaElementSession::PlaybackControlsPurpose purpose, const Document* document)
579{
580 Vector<MediaElementSessionInfo> candidateSessions;
581 bool atLeastOneNonCandidateMayBeConfusedForMainContent = false;
582 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().forEachMatchingSession([document](auto& session) {
583 return is<MediaElementSession>(session)
584 && (!document || &downcast<MediaElementSession>(session).element().document() == document);
585 }, [&](auto& session) {
586 auto mediaElementSessionInfo = mediaElementSessionInfoForSession(downcast<MediaElementSession>(session), purpose);
587 if (mediaElementSessionInfo.canShowControlsManager)
588 candidateSessions.append(mediaElementSessionInfo);
589 else if (mediaSessionMayBeConfusedWithMainContent(mediaElementSessionInfo, purpose))
590 atLeastOneNonCandidateMayBeConfusedForMainContent = true;
591 });
592
593 if (!candidateSessions.size())
594 return nullptr;
595
596 std::sort(candidateSessions.begin(), candidateSessions.end(), preferMediaControlsForCandidateSessionOverOtherCandidateSession);
597 auto strongestSessionCandidate = candidateSessions.first();
598 if (!strongestSessionCandidate.isVisibleInViewportOrFullscreen && !strongestSessionCandidate.isPlayingAudio && atLeastOneNonCandidateMayBeConfusedForMainContent)
599 return nullptr;
600
601 return &strongestSessionCandidate.session->element();
602}
603
604void HTMLMediaElement::registerWithDocument(Document& document)
605{
606 document.registerMediaElement(*this);
607
608 mediaSession().registerWithDocument(document);
609
610 if (m_isWaitingUntilMediaCanStart)
611 document.addMediaCanStartListener(*this);
612
613 document.registerForVisibilityStateChangedCallbacks(*this);
614
615 if (m_requireCaptionPreferencesChangedCallbacks)
616 document.registerForCaptionPreferencesChangedCallbacks(*this);
617
618#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
619 document.registerForDocumentSuspensionCallbacks(*this);
620#endif
621
622 document.addAudioProducer(*this);
623}
624
625void HTMLMediaElement::unregisterWithDocument(Document& document)
626{
627 document.unregisterMediaElement(*this);
628
629 if (m_mediaSession)
630 m_mediaSession->unregisterWithDocument(document);
631
632 if (m_isWaitingUntilMediaCanStart)
633 document.removeMediaCanStartListener(*this);
634
635 document.unregisterForVisibilityStateChangedCallbacks(*this);
636
637 if (m_requireCaptionPreferencesChangedCallbacks)
638 document.unregisterForCaptionPreferencesChangedCallbacks(*this);
639
640#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
641 document.unregisterForDocumentSuspensionCallbacks(*this);
642#endif
643
644 document.removeAudioProducer(*this);
645}
646
647void HTMLMediaElement::didMoveToNewDocument(Document& oldDocument, Document& newDocument)
648{
649 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(&document() == &newDocument);
650 if (m_shouldDelayLoadEvent) {
651 oldDocument.decrementLoadEventDelayCount();
652 newDocument.incrementLoadEventDelayCount();
653 }
654
655 unregisterWithDocument(oldDocument);
656 registerWithDocument(newDocument);
657
658 HTMLElement::didMoveToNewDocument(oldDocument, newDocument);
659 updateShouldAutoplay();
660 visibilityStateChanged();
661}
662
663#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
664
665void HTMLMediaElement::prepareForDocumentSuspension()
666{
667 mediaSession().unregisterWithDocument(document());
668}
669
670void HTMLMediaElement::resumeFromDocumentSuspension()
671{
672 mediaSession().registerWithDocument(document());
673 updateShouldAutoplay();
674}
675
676#endif
677
678bool HTMLMediaElement::supportsFocus() const
679{
680 if (document().isMediaDocument())
681 return false;
682
683 // If no controls specified, we should still be able to focus the element if it has tabIndex.
684 return controls() || HTMLElement::supportsFocus();
685}
686
687bool HTMLMediaElement::isMouseFocusable() const
688{
689 return false;
690}
691
692bool HTMLMediaElement::isInteractiveContent() const
693{
694 return controls();
695}
696
697void HTMLMediaElement::parseAttribute(const QualifiedName& name, const AtomString& value)
698{
699 if (name == idAttr)
700 m_id = value;
701
702 if (name == srcAttr) {
703 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/embedded-content.html#location-of-the-media-resource
704 // Location of the Media Resource
705 // 12 February 2017
706
707 // If a src attribute of a media element is set or changed, the user
708 // agent must invoke the media element's media element load algorithm.
709 if (!value.isNull())
710 prepareForLoad();
711 } else if (name == controlsAttr)
712 configureMediaControls();
713 else if (name == loopAttr)
714 updateSleepDisabling();
715 else if (name == preloadAttr) {
716 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(value, "none"))
717 m_preload = MediaPlayer::Preload::None;
718 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(value, "metadata"))
719 m_preload = MediaPlayer::Preload::MetaData;
720 else {
721 // The spec does not define an "invalid value default" but "auto" is suggested as the
722 // "missing value default", so use it for everything except "none" and "metadata"
723 m_preload = MediaPlayer::Preload::Auto;
724 }
725
726 // The attribute must be ignored if the autoplay attribute is present
727 if (!autoplay() && !m_havePreparedToPlay && m_player)
728 m_player->setPreload(mediaSession().effectivePreloadForElement());
729
730 } else if (name == mediagroupAttr)
731 setMediaGroup(value);
732 else if (name == autoplayAttr) {
733 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
734 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture();
735 } else if (name == titleAttr) {
736 if (m_mediaSession)
737 m_mediaSession->clientCharacteristicsChanged();
738 }
739 else
740 HTMLElement::parseAttribute(name, value);
741}
742
743void HTMLMediaElement::finishParsingChildren()
744{
745 HTMLElement::finishParsingChildren();
746 m_parsingInProgress = false;
747
748 if (childrenOfType<HTMLTrackElement>(*this).first())
749 scheduleConfigureTextTracks();
750}
751
752bool HTMLMediaElement::rendererIsNeeded(const RenderStyle& style)
753{
754 return controls() && HTMLElement::rendererIsNeeded(style);
755}
756
757RenderPtr<RenderElement> HTMLMediaElement::createElementRenderer(RenderStyle&& style, const RenderTreePosition&)
758{
759 return createRenderer<RenderMedia>(*this, WTFMove(style));
760}
761
762bool HTMLMediaElement::childShouldCreateRenderer(const Node& child) const
763{
764 return hasShadowRootParent(child) && HTMLElement::childShouldCreateRenderer(child);
765}
766
767Node::InsertedIntoAncestorResult HTMLMediaElement::insertedIntoAncestor(InsertionType insertionType, ContainerNode& parentOfInsertedTree)
768{
769 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
770
771 HTMLElement::insertedIntoAncestor(insertionType, parentOfInsertedTree);
772 if (insertionType.connectedToDocument)
773 setInActiveDocument(true);
774
775 return InsertedIntoAncestorResult::NeedsPostInsertionCallback;
776}
777
778void HTMLMediaElement::didFinishInsertingNode()
779{
780 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // prepareForLoad may result in a 'beforeload' event, which can make arbitrary DOM mutations.
781
782 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
783
784 if (m_inActiveDocument && m_networkState == NETWORK_EMPTY && !attributeWithoutSynchronization(srcAttr).isEmpty())
785 prepareForLoad();
786
787 if (!m_explicitlyMuted) {
788 m_explicitlyMuted = true;
789 m_muted = hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(mutedAttr);
790 mediaSession().canProduceAudioChanged();
791 }
792
793 configureMediaControls();
794}
795
796void HTMLMediaElement::pauseAfterDetachedTask()
797{
798 // If we were re-inserted into an active document, no need to pause.
799 if (m_inActiveDocument)
800 return;
801
802 if (m_videoFullscreenMode != VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture && m_networkState > NETWORK_EMPTY)
803 pause();
804 if (m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard)
805 exitFullscreen();
806
807 if (!m_player)
808 return;
809
810 size_t extraMemoryCost = m_player->extraMemoryCost();
811 if (extraMemoryCost > m_reportedExtraMemoryCost) {
812 JSC::VM& vm = commonVM();
813 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
814
815 size_t extraMemoryCostDelta = extraMemoryCost - m_reportedExtraMemoryCost;
816 m_reportedExtraMemoryCost = extraMemoryCost;
817 // FIXME: Adopt reportExtraMemoryVisited, and switch to reportExtraMemoryAllocated.
818 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=142595
819 vm.heap.deprecatedReportExtraMemory(extraMemoryCostDelta);
820 }
821}
822
823void HTMLMediaElement::removedFromAncestor(RemovalType removalType, ContainerNode& oldParentOfRemovedTree)
824{
825 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
826
827 setInActiveDocument(false);
828 if (removalType.disconnectedFromDocument) {
829 // Pause asynchronously to let the operation that removed us finish, in case we get inserted back into a document.
830 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this] {
831 if (!isContextStopped())
832 pauseAfterDetachedTask();
833 });
834 }
835
836 if (m_mediaSession)
837 m_mediaSession->clientCharacteristicsChanged();
838
839 HTMLElement::removedFromAncestor(removalType, oldParentOfRemovedTree);
840}

902
903void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleResolvePendingPlayPromises()
904{
905 if (m_pendingPlayPromises.isEmpty())
906 return;
907
908 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this, pendingPlayPromises = WTFMove(m_pendingPlayPromises)] () mutable {
909 if (!isContextStopped())
910 resolvePendingPlayPromises(WTFMove(pendingPlayPromises));
911 });
912}
913
914void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleRejectPendingPlayPromises(Ref<DOMException>&& error)
915{
916 if (m_pendingPlayPromises.isEmpty())
917 return;
918
919 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this, error = WTFMove(error), pendingPlayPromises = WTFMove(m_pendingPlayPromises)] () mutable {
920 if (!isContextStopped())
921 rejectPendingPlayPromises(WTFMove(pendingPlayPromises), WTFMove(error));
922 });
923}
924
925void HTMLMediaElement::rejectPendingPlayPromises(PlayPromiseVector&& pendingPlayPromises, Ref<DOMException>&& error)
926{
927 for (auto& promise : pendingPlayPromises)
928 promise.rejectType<IDLInterface<DOMException>>(error);
929}
930
931void HTMLMediaElement::resolvePendingPlayPromises(PlayPromiseVector&& pendingPlayPromises)
932{
933 for (auto& promise : pendingPlayPromises)
934 promise.resolve();
935}
936
937void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleNotifyAboutPlaying()
938{
939 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this, pendingPlayPromises = WTFMove(m_pendingPlayPromises)] () mutable {
940 if (!isContextStopped())
941 notifyAboutPlaying(WTFMove(pendingPlayPromises));
942 });
943}
944
945void HTMLMediaElement::notifyAboutPlaying(PlayPromiseVector&& pendingPlayPromises)
946{
947 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // The 'playing' event can make arbitrary DOM mutations.
948 m_playbackStartedTime = currentMediaTime().toDouble();
949 m_hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying = true;
950 dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().playingEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::Yes));
951 resolvePendingPlayPromises(WTFMove(pendingPlayPromises));
952
953 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
954}
955
956bool HTMLMediaElement::hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying() const
957{
958 return m_hasEverNotifiedAboutPlaying;
959}
960
961void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleCheckPlaybackTargetCompatability()
962{
963 if (m_checkPlaybackTargetCompatibilityTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
964 return;
965
966 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
967 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_checkPlaybackTargetCompatibilityTaskCancellationGroup, [this] {
968 checkPlaybackTargetCompatibility();
969 });
970}
971
972void HTMLMediaElement::checkPlaybackTargetCompatibility()
973{
974#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
975 if (m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget && !m_player->canPlayToWirelessPlaybackTarget()) {
976 static const Seconds maxIntervalForWirelessPlaybackPlayerUpdate { 500_ms };
977 Seconds delta = MonotonicTime::now() - m_currentPlaybackTargetIsWirelessEventFiredTime;
978 if (delta < maxIntervalForWirelessPlaybackPlayerUpdate) {
979 scheduleCheckPlaybackTargetCompatability();
980 return;
981 }
982
983 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "player incompatible after ", delta.value(), ", calling setShouldPlayToPlaybackTarget(false)");
984 m_failedToPlayToWirelessTarget = true;
985 m_player->setShouldPlayToPlaybackTarget(false);
986 }
987#endif
988}

990MediaError* HTMLMediaElement::error() const
