994
995void HTMLMediaElement::setSrcObject(MediaProvider&& mediaProvider)
996{
997 // FIXME: Setting the srcObject attribute may cause other changes to the media element's internal state:
998 // Specifically, if srcObject is specified, the UA must use it as the source of media, even if the src
999 // attribute is also set or children are present. If the value of srcObject is replaced or set to null
1000 // the UA must re-run the media element load algorithm.
1001 //
1002 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=124896
1003
1004
1005 // https://www.w3.org/TR/html51/semantics-embedded-content.html#dom-htmlmediaelement-srcobject
1006 // 4.7.14.2. Location of the media resource
1007 // srcObject: On setting, it must set the elements assigned media provider object to the new
1008 // value, and then invoke the elements media element load algorithm.
1009 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
1010 m_mediaProvider = WTFMove(mediaProvider);
1011#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
1012 m_mediaStreamSrcObject = nullptr;
1013#endif
1014#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
1015 m_mediaSource = nullptr;
1016#endif
1017 m_blob = nullptr;
1018
1019 prepareForLoad();
1020}
1021
1022void HTMLMediaElement::setCrossOrigin(const AtomString& value)
1023{
1024 setAttributeWithoutSynchronization(crossoriginAttr, value);
1025}
1026
1027String HTMLMediaElement::crossOrigin() const
1028{
1029 return parseCORSSettingsAttribute(attributeWithoutSynchronization(crossoriginAttr));
1030}
1031
1032HTMLMediaElement::NetworkState HTMLMediaElement::networkState() const
1033{
1034 return m_networkState;
1035}
1036
1037String HTMLMediaElement::canPlayType(const String& mimeType) const
1038{
1039 MediaEngineSupportParameters parameters;
1040 ContentType contentType(mimeType);
1041 parameters.type = contentType;
1042 parameters.contentTypesRequiringHardwareSupport = mediaContentTypesRequiringHardwareSupport();
1043 MediaPlayer::SupportsType support = MediaPlayer::supportsType(parameters);
1044 String canPlay;
1045
1046#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1047 // Temporarily work around bug 226922. For now claim that the opus and vorbis codecs aren't supported
1048 // so that sites relying on this test to determine if webaudio use of opus or vorbis won't error.
1049 auto codecs = contentType.codecs();
1050 if (support == MediaPlayer::SupportsType::IsSupported && (codecs.contains("opus") || codecs.contains("vorbis")))
1051 support = MediaPlayer::SupportsType::IsNotSupported;
1052#endif
1053
1054 // 4.8.10.3
1055 switch (support)
1056 {
1057 case MediaPlayer::SupportsType::IsNotSupported:
1058 canPlay = emptyString();
1059 break;
1060 case MediaPlayer::SupportsType::MayBeSupported:
1061 canPlay = "maybe"_s;
1062 break;
1063 case MediaPlayer::SupportsType::IsSupported:
1064 canPlay = "probably"_s;
1065 break;
1066 }
1067
1068 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, mimeType, ": ", canPlay);
1069
1070 return canPlay;
1071}
1072
1073double HTMLMediaElement::getStartDate() const
1074{
1075 if (!m_player)
1076 return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1077 return m_player->getStartDate().toDouble();
1078}
1079
1080void HTMLMediaElement::load()
1081{
1082 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // prepareForLoad may result in a 'beforeload' event, which can make arbitrary DOM mutations.
1083
1084 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
1085
1086 if (m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture && document().quirks().requiresUserGestureToLoadInPictureInPicture() && !document().processingUserGestureForMedia())
1087 return;
1088
1089 prepareForLoad();
1090 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup, std::bind(&HTMLMediaElement::prepareToPlay, this));
1091}
1092
1093void HTMLMediaElement::prepareForLoad()
1094{
1095 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/embedded-content.html#media-element-load-algorithm
1096 // The Media Element Load Algorithm
1097 // 12 February 2017
1098
1099 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "gesture = ", processingUserGestureForMedia());
1100
1101 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
1102 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture();
1103
1104 // 1 - Abort any already-running instance of the resource selection algorithm for this element.
1105 // Perform the cleanup required for the resource load algorithm to run.
1106 stopPeriodicTimers();
1107 m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
1108 // FIXME: Figure out appropriate place to reset LoadTextTrackResource if necessary and set m_pendingActionFlags to 0 here.
1109 m_sentEndEvent = false;
1110 m_sentStalledEvent = false;
1111 m_haveFiredLoadedData = false;
1112 m_completelyLoaded = false;
1113 m_havePreparedToPlay = false;
1114 setCurrentSrc(URL());
1115
1116#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
1117 m_failedToPlayToWirelessTarget = false;
1118#endif
1119
1120 m_loadState = WaitingForSource;
1121 m_currentSourceNode = nullptr;
1122
1123 if (!document().hasBrowsingContext())
1124 return;
1125
1126 createMediaPlayer();
1127
1128 // 2 - Let pending tasks be a list of all tasks from the media element's media element event task source in one of the task queues.
1129 // 3 - For each task in pending tasks that would resolve pending play promises or reject pending play promises, immediately resolve or reject those promises in the order the corresponding tasks were queued.
1130 // 4 - Remove each task in pending tasks from its task queue
1131 cancelPendingEventsAndCallbacks();
1132
1133 // 5 - If the media element's networkState is set to NETWORK_LOADING or NETWORK_IDLE, queue
1134 // a task to fire a simple event named abort at the media element.
1135 if (m_networkState == NETWORK_LOADING || m_networkState == NETWORK_IDLE)
1136 scheduleEvent(eventNames().abortEvent);
1137
1138 // 6 - If the media element's networkState is not set to NETWORK_EMPTY, then run these substeps
1139 if (m_networkState != NETWORK_EMPTY) {
1140 // 6.1 - Queue a task to fire a simple event named emptied at the media element.
1141 scheduleEvent(eventNames().emptiedEvent);
1142
1143 // 6.2 - If a fetching process is in progress for the media element, the user agent should stop it.
1144 m_networkState = NETWORK_EMPTY;
1145
1146 // 6.3 - If the media elements assigned media provider object is a MediaSource object, then detach it.
1147#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
1148 detachMediaSource();
1149#endif
1150
1151 // 6.4 - Forget the media element's media-resource-specific tracks.
1152 forgetResourceSpecificTracks();
1153
1154 // 6.5 - If readyState is not set to HAVE_NOTHING, then set it to that state.
1155 m_readyState = HAVE_NOTHING;
1156 m_readyStateMaximum = HAVE_NOTHING;
1157
1158 // 6.6 - If the paused attribute is false, then set it to true.
1159 m_paused = true;
1160
1161 // 6.7 - If seeking is true, set it to false.
1162 clearSeeking();
1163
1164 // 6.8 - Set the current playback position to 0.
1165 // Set the official playback position to 0.
1166 // If this changed the official playback position, then queue a task to fire a simple event named timeupdate at the media element.
1167 m_lastSeekTime = MediaTime::zeroTime();
1168 m_playedTimeRanges = TimeRanges::create();
1169 // FIXME: Add support for firing this event. e.g., scheduleEvent(eventNames().timeUpdateEvent);
1170
1171 // 4.9 - Set the initial playback position to 0.
1172 // FIXME: Make this less subtle. The position only becomes 0 because of the createMediaPlayer() call
1173 // above.
1174 refreshCachedTime();
1175
1176 invalidateCachedTime();
1177
1178 // 4.10 - Set the timeline offset to Not-a-Number (NaN).
1179 // 4.11 - Update the duration attribute to Not-a-Number (NaN).
1180
1181 updateMediaController();
1182 updateActiveTextTrackCues(MediaTime::zeroTime());
1183 }
1184
1185 // 7 - Set the playbackRate attribute to the value of the defaultPlaybackRate attribute.
1186 setPlaybackRate(defaultPlaybackRate());
1187
1188 // 8 - Set the error attribute to null and the autoplaying flag to true.
1189 m_error = nullptr;
1190 m_autoplaying = true;
1191 mediaSession().clientWillBeginAutoplaying();
1192
1193 if (!MediaPlayer::isAvailable())
1194 noneSupported();
1195 else {
1196 // 9 - Invoke the media element's resource selection algorithm.
1197 // Note, unless the restriction on requiring user action has been removed,
1198 // do not begin downloading data.
1199 if (mediaSession().dataLoadingPermitted())
1200 selectMediaResource();
1201 }
1202
1203 // 10 - Note: Playback of any previously playing media resource for this element stops.
1204
1205 configureMediaControls();
1206}
1207
1208void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerReloadAndResumePlaybackIfNeeded()
1209{
1210 auto previousMediaTime = m_cachedTime;
1211 bool wasPaused = paused();
1212
1213 load();
1214
1215 if (m_videoFullscreenMode != VideoFullscreenModeNone)
1216 enterFullscreen(m_videoFullscreenMode);
1217
1218 if (previousMediaTime) {
1219 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup, [this, previousMediaTime] {
1220 if (m_player)
1221 m_player->seekWhenPossible(previousMediaTime);
1222 });
1223 }
1224
1225 if (!wasPaused)
1226 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup, std::bind(&HTMLMediaElement::playInternal, this));
1227}
1228
1229void HTMLMediaElement::selectMediaResource()
1230{
1231 // https://www.w3.org/TR/2016/REC-html51-20161101/semantics-embedded-content.html#resource-selection-algorithm
1232 // The Resource Selection Algorithm
1233
1234 // 1. Set the elements networkState attribute to the NETWORK_NO_SOURCE value.
1235 m_networkState = NETWORK_NO_SOURCE;
1236
1237 // 2. Set the elements show poster flag to true.
1238 setShowPosterFlag(true);
1239
1240 // 3. Set the media elements delaying-the-load-event flag to true (this delays the load event).
1241 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(true);
1242
1243 // 4. in parallel await a stable state, allowing the task that invoked this algorithm to continue.
1244 if (m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
1245 return;
1246
1247 if (!mediaSession().pageAllowsDataLoading()) {
1248 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "not allowed to load in background, waiting");
1249 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
1250 if (m_isWaitingUntilMediaCanStart)
1251 return;
1252 m_isWaitingUntilMediaCanStart = true;
1253 document().addMediaCanStartListener(*this);
1254 return;
1255 }
1256
1257 // Once the page has allowed an element to load media, it is free to load at will. This allows a
1258 // playlist that starts in a foreground tab to continue automatically if the tab is subsequently
1259 // put into the background.
1260 mediaSession().removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequirePageConsentToLoadMedia);
1261
1262 auto logSiteIdentifier = LOGIDENTIFIER;
1263 UNUSED_PARAM(logSiteIdentifier);
1264
1265 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup, [this, logSiteIdentifier] {
1266
1267 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "lambda(), task fired");
1268
1269 // 5. If the media elements blocked-on-parser flag is false, then populate the list of pending text tracks.
1270 // HTMLMediaElement::textTracksAreReady will need "... the text tracks whose mode was not in the
1271 // disabled state when the element's resource selection algorithm last started".
1272 // FIXME: Update this to match "populate the list of pending text tracks" step.
1273 m_textTracksWhenResourceSelectionBegan.clear();
1274 if (m_textTracks) {
1275 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_textTracks->length(); ++i) {
1276 RefPtr<TextTrack> track = m_textTracks->item(i);
1277 if (track->mode() != TextTrack::Mode::Disabled)
1278 m_textTracksWhenResourceSelectionBegan.append(track);
1279 }
1280 }
1281
1282 enum Mode { None, Object, Attribute, Children };
1283 Mode mode = None;
1284
1285 if (m_mediaProvider) {
1286 // 6. If the media element has an assigned media provider object, then let mode be object.
1287 mode = Object;
1288 } else if (hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(srcAttr)) {
1289 // Otherwise, if the media element has no assigned media provider object but has a src attribute, then let mode be attribute.
1290 mode = Attribute;
1291 ASSERT(m_player);
1292 if (!m_player) {
1293 ERROR_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "has srcAttr but m_player is not created");
1294 return;
1295 }
1296 } else if (auto firstSource = childrenOfType<HTMLSourceElement>(*this).first()) {
1297 // Otherwise, if the media element does not have an assigned media provider object and does not have a src attribute,
1298 // but does have a source element child, then let mode be children and let candidate be the first such source element
1299 // child in tree order.
1300 mode = Children;
1301 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = firstSource;
1302 m_currentSourceNode = nullptr;
1303 } else {
1304 // Otherwise the media element has no assigned media provider object and has neither a src attribute nor a source
1305 // element child: set the networkState to NETWORK_EMPTY, and abort these steps; the synchronous section ends.
1306 m_loadState = WaitingForSource;
1307 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
1308 m_networkState = NETWORK_EMPTY;
1309
1310 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "nothing to load");
1311 return;
1312 }
1313
1314 // 7. Set the media elements networkState to NETWORK_LOADING.
1315 m_networkState = NETWORK_LOADING;
1316
1317 // 8. Queue a task to fire a simple event named loadstart at the media element.
1318 scheduleEvent(eventNames().loadstartEvent);
1319
1320 // 9. Run the appropriate steps from the following list:
1321 // If mode is object
1322 if (mode == Object) {
1323 // 1. Set the currentSrc attribute to the empty string.
1324 setCurrentSrc(URL());
1325
1326 // 2. End the synchronous section, continuing the remaining steps in parallel.
1327 // 3. Run the resource fetch algorithm with the assigned media provider object.
1328 switchOn(m_mediaProvider.value(),
1329#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
1330 [this](RefPtr<MediaStream> stream) { m_mediaStreamSrcObject = stream; },
1331#endif
1332#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
1333 [this](RefPtr<MediaSource> source) { m_mediaSource = source; },
1334#endif
1335 [this](RefPtr<Blob> blob) { m_blob = blob; }
1336 );
1337
1338 ContentType contentType;
1339 loadResource(URL(), contentType, String());
1340 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "using 'srcObject' property");
1341
1342 // If that algorithm returns without aborting this one, then the load failed.
1343 // 4. Failed with media provider: Reaching this step indicates that the media resource
1344 // failed to load. Queue a task to run the dedicated media source failure steps.
1345 // 5. Wait for the task queued by the previous step to have executed.
1346 // 6. Abort these steps. The element wont attempt to load another resource until this
1347 // algorithm is triggered again.
1348 return;
1349 }
1350
1351 // If mode is attribute
1352 if (mode == Attribute) {
1353 m_loadState = LoadingFromSrcAttr;
1354
1355 // 1. If the src attributes value is the empty string, then end the synchronous section,
1356 // and jump down to the failed with attribute step below.
1357 // 2. Let absolute URL be the absolute URL that would have resulted from parsing the URL
1358 // specified by the src attributes value relative to the media element when the src
1359 // attribute was last changed.
1360 URL absoluteURL = getNonEmptyURLAttribute(srcAttr);
1361 if (absoluteURL.isEmpty()) {
1362 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1363 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "empty 'src'");
1364 return;
1365 }
1366
1367 if (!isSafeToLoadURL(absoluteURL, Complain) || !dispatchBeforeLoadEvent(absoluteURL.string())) {
1368 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1369 return;
1370 }
1371
1372 // 3. If absolute URL was obtained successfully, set the currentSrc attribute to absolute URL.
1373 setCurrentSrc(absoluteURL);
1374
1375 // 4. End the synchronous section, continuing the remaining steps in parallel.
1376 // 5. If absolute URL was obtained successfully, run the resource fetch algorithm with absolute
1377 // URL. If that algorithm returns without aborting this one, then the load failed.
1378
1379 // No type or key system information is available when the url comes
1380 // from the 'src' attribute so MediaPlayer
1381 // will have to pick a media engine based on the file extension.
1382 ContentType contentType;
1383 loadResource(absoluteURL, contentType, String());
1384 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "using 'src' attribute url");
1385
1386 // 6. Failed with attribute: Reaching this step indicates that the media resource failed to load
1387 // or that the given URL could not be resolved. Queue a task to run the dedicated media source failure steps.
1388 // 7. Wait for the task queued by the previous step to have executed.
1389 // 8. Abort these steps. The element wont attempt to load another resource until this algorithm is triggered again.
1390 return;
1391 }
1392
1393 // Otherwise (mode is children)
1394 // (Ctd. in loadNextSourceChild())
1395 loadNextSourceChild();
1396 });
1397}
1398
1399void HTMLMediaElement::loadNextSourceChild()
1400{
1401 ContentType contentType;
1402 String keySystem;
1403 URL mediaURL = selectNextSourceChild(&contentType, &keySystem, Complain);
1404 if (!mediaURL.isValid()) {
1405 waitForSourceChange();
1406 return;
1407 }
1408
1409 // Recreate the media player for the new url
1410 createMediaPlayer();
1411
1412 m_loadState = LoadingFromSourceElement;
1413 loadResource(mediaURL, contentType, keySystem);
1414}
1415
1416void HTMLMediaElement::loadResource(const URL& initialURL, ContentType& contentType, const String& keySystem)
1417{
1418 ASSERT(initialURL.isEmpty() || isSafeToLoadURL(initialURL, Complain));
1419
1420 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, initialURL, contentType, keySystem);
1421
1422 RefPtr<Frame> frame = document().frame();
1423 if (!frame) {
1424 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1425 return;
1426 }
1427
1428 Page* page = frame->page();
1429 if (!page) {
1430 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1431 return;
1432 }
1433
1434 URL url = initialURL;
1435 if (!url.isEmpty() && !frame->loader().willLoadMediaElementURL(url, *this)) {
1436 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1437 return;
1438 }
1439
1440#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
1441 if (auto documentLoader = makeRefPtr(frame->loader().documentLoader())) {
1442 if (page->userContentProvider().processContentRuleListsForLoad(*page, url, ContentExtensions::ResourceType::Media, *documentLoader).summary.blockedLoad) {
1443 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1444 return;
1445 }
1446 }
1447#endif
1448
1449 // The resource fetch algorithm
1450 m_networkState = NETWORK_LOADING;
1451
1452 // If the URL should be loaded from the application cache, pass the URL of the cached file to the media engine.
1453 ApplicationCacheResource* resource = nullptr;
1454 if (!url.isEmpty() && frame->loader().documentLoader()->applicationCacheHost().shouldLoadResourceFromApplicationCache(ResourceRequest(url), resource)) {
1455 // Resources that are not present in the manifest will always fail to load (at least, after the
1456 // cache has been primed the first time), making the testing of offline applications simpler.
1457 if (!resource || resource->path().isEmpty()) {
1458 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::NetworkError);
1459 return;
1460 }
1461 }
1462
1463 // Log that we started loading a media element.
1464 page->diagnosticLoggingClient().logDiagnosticMessage(isVideo() ? DiagnosticLoggingKeys::videoKey() : DiagnosticLoggingKeys::audioKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::loadingKey(), ShouldSample::No);
1465
1466 m_firstTimePlaying = true;
1467
1468 // Set m_currentSrc *before* changing to the cache URL, the fact that we are loading from the app
1469 // cache is an internal detail not exposed through the media element API.
1470 setCurrentSrc(url);
1471
1472 if (resource) {
1473 url = ApplicationCacheHost::createFileURL(resource->path());
1474 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "will load from app cache ", url);
1475 }
1476
1477 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "m_currentSrc is ", m_currentSrc);
1478
1479 startProgressEventTimer();
1480
1481 bool privateMode = document().page() && document().page()->usesEphemeralSession();
1482 m_player->setPrivateBrowsingMode(privateMode);
1483
1484 if (!autoplay() && !m_havePreparedToPlay)
1485 m_player->setPreload(mediaSession().effectivePreloadForElement());
1486 m_player->setPreservesPitch(m_webkitPreservesPitch);
1487 m_player->setPitchCorrectionAlgorithm(document().settings().pitchCorrectionAlgorithm());
1488
1489 if (!m_explicitlyMuted) {
1490 m_explicitlyMuted = true;
1491 m_muted = hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(mutedAttr);
1492 mediaSession().canProduceAudioChanged();
1493 }
1494
1495 updateVolume();
1496
1497 bool loadAttempted = false;
1498#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
1499 if (!m_mediaSource && url.protocolIs(mediaSourceBlobProtocol))
1500 m_mediaSource = MediaSource::lookup(url.string());
1501
1502 if (m_mediaSource) {
1503 loadAttempted = true;
1504
1505 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "loading MSE blob");
1506 if (!m_mediaSource->attachToElement(*this)) {
1507 // Forget our reference to the MediaSource, so we leave it alone
1508 // while processing remainder of load failure.
1509 m_mediaSource = nullptr;
1510 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1511 } else if (!m_player->load(url, contentType, m_mediaSource.get())) {
1512 // We have to detach the MediaSource before we forget the reference to it.
1513 m_mediaSource->detachFromElement(*this);
1514 m_mediaSource = nullptr;
1515 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1516 }
1517 }
1518#endif
1519#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
1520 if (!loadAttempted && m_mediaStreamSrcObject) {
1521 loadAttempted = true;
1522 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "loading media stream blob ", m_mediaStreamSrcObject->logIdentifier());
1523 if (!m_player->load(m_mediaStreamSrcObject->privateStream()))
1524 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1525 }
1526#endif
1527
1528 if (!loadAttempted && m_blob) {
1529 loadAttempted = true;
1530 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "loading generic blob");
1531 if (!m_blobURLForReading.isEmpty())
1532 ThreadableBlobRegistry::unregisterBlobURL(m_blobURLForReading);
1533 m_blobURLForReading = BlobURL::createPublicURL(&document().securityOrigin());
1534 ThreadableBlobRegistry::registerBlobURL(&document().securityOrigin(), m_blobURLForReading, m_blob->url());
1535
1536 if (!m_player->load(m_blobURLForReading, contentType, keySystem))
1537 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1538 }
1539
1540 if (!loadAttempted && !m_player->load(url, contentType, keySystem))
1541 mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
1542
1543 mediaPlayerRenderingModeChanged();
1544}
1545
1546struct HTMLMediaElement::CueData {
1547 WTF_MAKE_STRUCT_FAST_ALLOCATED;
1548 PODIntervalTree<MediaTime, TextTrackCue*> cueTree;
1549 CueList currentlyActiveCues;
1550};
1551
1552static bool trackIndexCompare(TextTrack* a, TextTrack* b)
1553{
1554 return a->trackIndex() - b->trackIndex() < 0;
1555}
1556
1557static bool eventTimeCueCompare(const std::pair<MediaTime, TextTrackCue*>& a, const std::pair<MediaTime, TextTrackCue*>& b)
1558{
1559 // 12 - Sort the tasks in events in ascending time order (tasks with earlier
1560 // times first).
1561 if (a.first != b.first)
1562 return a.first - b.first < MediaTime::zeroTime();
1563
1564 // If the cues belong to different text tracks, it doesn't make sense to
1565 // compare the two tracks by the relative cue order, so return the relative
1566 // track order.
1567 if (a.second->track() != b.second->track())
1568 return trackIndexCompare(a.second->track(), b.second->track());
1569
1570 // 12 - Further sort tasks in events that have the same time by the
1571 // relative text track cue order of the text track cues associated
1572 // with these tasks.
1573 return a.second->isOrderedBefore(b.second);
1574}
1575
1576static bool compareCueInterval(const CueInterval& one, const CueInterval& two)
1577{
1578 return one.data()->isOrderedBefore(two.data());
1579}
1580
1581static bool compareCueIntervalEndTime(const CueInterval& one, const CueInterval& two)
1582{
1583 return one.data()->endMediaTime() > two.data()->endMediaTime();
1584}
1585
1586bool HTMLMediaElement::ignoreTrackDisplayUpdateRequests() const
1587{
1588 return m_ignoreTrackDisplayUpdate > 0 || !m_textTracks || !m_cueData || m_cueData->cueTree.isEmpty();
1589}
1590
1591void HTMLMediaElement::updateActiveTextTrackCues(const MediaTime& movieTime)
1592{
1593 // 4.8.10.8 Playing the media resource
1594
1595 // If the current playback position changes while the steps are running,
1596 // then the user agent must wait for the steps to complete, and then must
1597 // immediately rerun the steps.
1598 if (ignoreTrackDisplayUpdateRequests())
1599 return;
1600
1601 // 1 - Let current cues be a list of cues, initialized to contain all the
1602 // cues of all the hidden, showing, or showing by default text tracks of the
1603 // media element (not the disabled ones) whose start times are less than or
1604 // equal to the current playback position and whose end times are greater
1605 // than the current playback position.
1606 CueList currentCues;
1607
1608 // The user agent must synchronously unset [the text track cue active] flag
1609 // whenever ... the media element's readyState is changed back to HAVE_NOTHING.
1610 if (m_readyState != HAVE_NOTHING && m_player) {
1611 currentCues = m_cueData->cueTree.allOverlaps({ movieTime, movieTime });
1612 if (currentCues.size() > 1)
1613 std::sort(currentCues.begin(), currentCues.end(), &compareCueInterval);
1614 }
1615
1616 CueList previousCues;
1617 CueList missedCues;
1618
1619 // 2 - Let other cues be a list of cues, initialized to contain all the cues
1620 // of hidden, showing, and showing by default text tracks of the media
1621 // element that are not present in current cues.
1622 previousCues = m_cueData->currentlyActiveCues;
1623
1624 // 3 - Let last time be the current playback position at the time this
1625 // algorithm was last run for this media element, if this is not the first
1626 // time it has run.
1627 MediaTime lastTime = m_lastTextTrackUpdateTime;
1628
1629 // 4 - If the current playback position has, since the last time this
1630 // algorithm was run, only changed through its usual monotonic increase
1631 // during normal playback, then let missed cues be the list of cues in other
1632 // cues whose start times are greater than or equal to last time and whose
1633 // end times are less than or equal to the current playback position.
1634 // Otherwise, let missed cues be an empty list.
1635 if (lastTime >= MediaTime::zeroTime() && m_lastSeekTime < movieTime) {
1636 for (auto& cue : m_cueData->cueTree.allOverlaps({ lastTime, movieTime })) {
1637 // Consider cues that may have been missed since the last seek time.
1638 if (cue.low() > std::max(m_lastSeekTime, lastTime) && cue.high() < movieTime)
1639 missedCues.append(cue);
1640 }
1641 }
1642
1643 m_lastTextTrackUpdateTime = movieTime;
1644
1645 // 5 - If the time was reached through the usual monotonic increase of the
1646 // current playback position during normal playback, and if the user agent
1647 // has not fired a timeupdate event at the element in the past 15 to 250ms
1648 // and is not still running event handlers for such an event, then the user
1649 // agent must queue a task to fire a simple event named timeupdate at the
1650 // element. (In the other cases, such as explicit seeks, relevant events get
1651 // fired as part of the overall process of changing the current playback
1652 // position.)
1653 if (!m_paused && m_lastSeekTime <= lastTime)
1654 scheduleTimeupdateEvent(false);
1655
1656 // Explicitly cache vector sizes, as their content is constant from here.
1657 size_t currentCuesSize = currentCues.size();
1658 size_t missedCuesSize = missedCues.size();
1659 size_t previousCuesSize = previousCues.size();
1660
1661 // 6 - If all of the cues in current cues have their text track cue active
1662 // flag set, none of the cues in other cues have their text track cue active
1663 // flag set, and missed cues is empty, then abort these steps.
1664 bool activeSetChanged = missedCuesSize;
1665
1666 for (size_t i = 0; !activeSetChanged && i < previousCuesSize; ++i)
1667 if (!currentCues.contains(previousCues[i]) && previousCues[i].data()->isActive())
1668 activeSetChanged = true;
1669
1670 for (size_t i = 0; i < currentCuesSize; ++i) {
1671 RefPtr<TextTrackCue> cue = currentCues[i].data();
1672 cue->updateDisplayTree(movieTime);
1673 if (!cue->isActive())
1674 activeSetChanged = true;
1675 }
1676
1677 MediaTime nextInterestingTime = MediaTime::invalidTime();
1678 if (auto nearestEndingCue = std::min_element(currentCues.begin(), currentCues.end(), compareCueIntervalEndTime))
1679 nextInterestingTime = nearestEndingCue->data()->endMediaTime();
1680
1681 std::optional<CueInterval> nextCue = m_cueData->cueTree.nextIntervalAfter(movieTime);
1682 if (nextCue)
1683 nextInterestingTime = std::min(nextInterestingTime, nextCue->low());
1684
1685 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "nextInterestingTime:", nextInterestingTime);
1686
1687 if (nextInterestingTime.isValid() && m_player) {
1688 m_player->performTaskAtMediaTime([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(this)] {
1689 if (!weakThis)
1690 return;
1691
1692 auto currentMediaTime = this->currentMediaTime();
1693 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, " lambda, currentMediaTime: ", currentMediaTime);
1694 this->updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime);
1695 }, nextInterestingTime);
1696 }
1697
1698 if (!activeSetChanged)
1699 return;
1700
1701 // 7 - If the time was reached through the usual monotonic increase of the
1702 // current playback position during normal playback, and there are cues in
1703 // other cues that have their text track cue pause-on-exi flag set and that
1704 // either have their text track cue active flag set or are also in missed
1705 // cues, then immediately pause the media element.
1706 for (size_t i = 0; !m_paused && i < previousCuesSize; ++i) {
1707 if (previousCues[i].data()->pauseOnExit()
1708 && previousCues[i].data()->isActive()
1709 && !currentCues.contains(previousCues[i]))
1710 pause();
1711 }
1712
1713 for (size_t i = 0; !m_paused && i < missedCuesSize; ++i) {
1714 if (missedCues[i].data()->pauseOnExit())
1715 pause();
1716 }
1717
1718 // 8 - Let events be a list of tasks, initially empty. Each task in this
1719 // list will be associated with a text track, a text track cue, and a time,
1720 // which are used to sort the list before the tasks are queued.
1721 Vector<std::pair<MediaTime, TextTrackCue*>> eventTasks;
1722
1723 // 8 - Let affected tracks be a list of text tracks, initially empty.
1724 Vector<TextTrack*> affectedTracks;
1725
1726 for (size_t i = 0; i < missedCuesSize; ++i) {
1727 // 9 - For each text track cue in missed cues, prepare an event named enter
1728 // for the TextTrackCue object with the text track cue start time.
1729 eventTasks.append({ missedCues[i].data()->startMediaTime(), missedCues[i].data() });
1730
1731 // 10 - For each text track [...] in missed cues, prepare an event
1732 // named exit for the TextTrackCue object with the with the later of
1733 // the text track cue end time and the text track cue start time.
1734
1735 // Note: An explicit task is added only if the cue is NOT a zero or
1736 // negative length cue. Otherwise, the need for an exit event is
1737 // checked when these tasks are actually queued below. This doesn't
1738 // affect sorting events before dispatch either, because the exit
1739 // event has the same time as the enter event.
1740 if (missedCues[i].data()->startMediaTime() < missedCues[i].data()->endMediaTime())
1741 eventTasks.append({ missedCues[i].data()->endMediaTime(), missedCues[i].data() });
1742 }
1743
1744 for (size_t i = 0; i < previousCuesSize; ++i) {
1745 // 10 - For each text track cue in other cues that has its text
1746 // track cue active flag set prepare an event named exit for the
1747 // TextTrackCue object with the text track cue end time.
1748 if (!currentCues.contains(previousCues[i]))
1749 eventTasks.append({ previousCues[i].data()->endMediaTime(), previousCues[i].data() });
1750 }
1751
1752 for (size_t i = 0; i < currentCuesSize; ++i) {
1753 // 11 - For each text track cue in current cues that does not have its
1754 // text track cue active flag set, prepare an event named enter for the
1755 // TextTrackCue object with the text track cue start time.
1756 if (!previousCues.contains(currentCues[i]))
1757 eventTasks.append({ currentCues[i].data()->startMediaTime(), currentCues[i].data() });
1758 }
1759
1760 // 12 - Sort the tasks in events in ascending time order (tasks with earlier
1761 // times first).
1762 std::sort(eventTasks.begin(), eventTasks.end(), eventTimeCueCompare);
1763
1764 for (auto& eventTask : eventTasks) {
1765 if (!affectedTracks.contains(eventTask.second->track()))
1766 affectedTracks.append(eventTask.second->track());
1767
1768 // 13 - Queue each task in events, in list order.
1769
1770 // Each event in eventTasks may be either an enterEvent or an exitEvent,
1771 // depending on the time that is associated with the event. This
1772 // correctly identifies the type of the event, if the startTime is
1773 // less than the endTime in the cue.
1774 if (eventTask.second->startTime() >= eventTask.second->endTime()) {
1775 auto enterEvent = Event::create(eventNames().enterEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No);
1776 scheduleEventOn(*eventTask.second, WTFMove(enterEvent));
1777
1778 auto exitEvent = Event::create(eventNames().exitEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No);
1779 scheduleEventOn(*eventTask.second, WTFMove(exitEvent));
1780 } else {
1781 RefPtr<Event> event;
1782 if (eventTask.first == eventTask.second->startMediaTime())
1783 event = Event::create(eventNames().enterEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No);
1784 else
1785 event = Event::create(eventNames().exitEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No);
1786 scheduleEventOn(*eventTask.second, event.releaseNonNull());
1787 }
1788 }
1789
1790 // 14 - Sort affected tracks in the same order as the text tracks appear in
1791 // the media element's list of text tracks, and remove duplicates.
1792 std::sort(affectedTracks.begin(), affectedTracks.end(), trackIndexCompare);
1793
1794 // 15 - For each text track in affected tracks, in the list order, queue a
1795 // task to fire a simple event named cuechange at the TextTrack object, and, ...
1796 for (auto& affectedTrack : affectedTracks) {
1797 auto event = Event::create(eventNames().cuechangeEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No);
1798 scheduleEventOn(*affectedTrack, WTFMove(event));
1799
1800 // ... if the text track has a corresponding track element, to then fire a
1801 // simple event named cuechange at the track element as well.
1802 if (is<LoadableTextTrack>(*affectedTrack)) {
1803 auto event = Event::create(eventNames().cuechangeEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No);
1804 auto trackElement = makeRefPtr(downcast<LoadableTextTrack>(*affectedTrack).trackElement());
1805 ASSERT(trackElement);
1806 scheduleEventOn(*trackElement, WTFMove(event));
1807 }
1808 }
1809
1810 // 16 - Set the text track cue active flag of all the cues in the current
1811 // cues, and unset the text track cue active flag of all the cues in the
1812 // other cues.
1813 for (size_t i = 0; i < currentCuesSize; ++i)
1814 currentCues[i].data()->setIsActive(true);
1815
1816 for (size_t i = 0; i < previousCuesSize; ++i)
1817 if (!currentCues.contains(previousCues[i]))
1818 previousCues[i].data()->setIsActive(false);
1819
1820 // Update the current active cues.
1821 m_cueData->currentlyActiveCues = currentCues;
1822
1823 if (activeSetChanged)
1824 updateTextTrackDisplay();
1825}
1826
1827void HTMLMediaElement::audioTrackEnabledChanged(AudioTrack& track)
1828{
1829 if (m_audioTracks && m_audioTracks->contains(track))
1830 m_audioTracks->scheduleChangeEvent();
1831 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
1832 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture(MediaElementSession::AllRestrictions & ~MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
1833 checkForAudioAndVideo();
1834}
1835
1836void HTMLMediaElement::textTrackModeChanged(TextTrack& track)
1837{
1838 bool trackIsLoaded = true;
1839 if (track.trackType() == TextTrack::TrackElement) {
1840 trackIsLoaded = false;
1841 for (auto& trackElement : childrenOfType<HTMLTrackElement>(*this)) {
1842 if (&trackElement.track() == &track) {
1843 if (trackElement.readyState() == HTMLTrackElement::LOADING || trackElement.readyState() == HTMLTrackElement::LOADED)
1844 trackIsLoaded = true;
1845 break;
1846 }
1847 }
1848 }
1849
1850 // If this is the first added track, create the list of text tracks.
1851 if (!m_textTracks)
1852 m_textTracks = TextTrackList::create(makeWeakPtr(this), ActiveDOMObject::scriptExecutionContext());
1853
1854 // Mark this track as "configured" so configureTextTracks won't change the mode again.
1855 track.setHasBeenConfigured(true);
1856
1857 if (track.mode() != TextTrack::Mode::Disabled && trackIsLoaded)
1858 textTrackAddCues(track, *track.cues());
1859
1860 configureTextTrackDisplay(AssumeTextTrackVisibilityChanged);
1861
1862 if (m_textTracks && m_textTracks->contains(track))
1863 m_textTracks->scheduleChangeEvent();
1864
1865#if ENABLE(AVF_CAPTIONS)
1866 if (track.trackType() == TextTrack::TrackElement && m_player)
1867 m_player->notifyTrackModeChanged();
1868#endif
1869}
1870
1871void HTMLMediaElement::videoTrackSelectedChanged(VideoTrack& track)
1872{
1873 if (m_videoTracks && m_videoTracks->contains(track))
1874 m_videoTracks->scheduleChangeEvent();
1875 checkForAudioAndVideo();
1876}
1877
1878void HTMLMediaElement::textTrackKindChanged(TextTrack& track)
1879{
1880 if (track.kind() != TextTrack::Kind::Captions && track.kind() != TextTrack::Kind::Subtitles && track.mode() == TextTrack::Mode::Showing)
1881 track.setMode(TextTrack::Mode::Hidden);
1882}
1883
1884void HTMLMediaElement::beginIgnoringTrackDisplayUpdateRequests()
1885{
1886 ++m_ignoreTrackDisplayUpdate;
1887}
1888
1889void HTMLMediaElement::endIgnoringTrackDisplayUpdateRequests()
1890{
1891 ASSERT(m_ignoreTrackDisplayUpdate);
1892 --m_ignoreTrackDisplayUpdate;
1893 if (!m_ignoreTrackDisplayUpdate && m_inActiveDocument)
1894 updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime());
1895}
1896
1897void HTMLMediaElement::textTrackAddCues(TextTrack& track, const TextTrackCueList& cues)
1898{
1899 if (track.mode() == TextTrack::Mode::Disabled)
1900 return;
1901
1902 TrackDisplayUpdateScope scope { *this };
1903 for (unsigned i = 0; i < cues.length(); ++i)
1904 textTrackAddCue(track, *cues.item(i));
1905}
1906
1907void HTMLMediaElement::textTrackRemoveCues(TextTrack&, const TextTrackCueList& cues)
1908{
1909 TrackDisplayUpdateScope scope { *this };
1910 for (unsigned i = 0; i < cues.length(); ++i) {
1911 auto& cue = *cues.item(i);
1912 textTrackRemoveCue(*cue.track(), cue);
1913 }
1914}
1915
1916void HTMLMediaElement::textTrackAddCue(TextTrack& track, TextTrackCue& cue)
1917{
1918 if (track.mode() == TextTrack::Mode::Disabled)
1919 return;
1920
1921 if (!m_cueData)
1922 m_cueData = makeUnique<CueData>();
1923
1924 // Negative duration cues need be treated in the interval tree as
1925 // zero-length cues.
1926 MediaTime endTime = std::max(cue.startMediaTime(), cue.endMediaTime());
1927
1928 CueInterval interval(cue.startMediaTime(), endTime, &cue);
1929 if (!m_cueData->cueTree.contains(interval))
1930 m_cueData->cueTree.add(interval);
1931 updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime());
1932}
1933
1934void HTMLMediaElement::textTrackRemoveCue(TextTrack&, TextTrackCue& cue)
1935{
1936 if (!m_cueData)
1937 m_cueData = makeUnique<CueData>();
1938
1939 // Negative duration cues need to be treated in the interval tree as
1940 // zero-length cues.
1941 MediaTime endTime = std::max(cue.startMediaTime(), cue.endMediaTime());
1942
1943 CueInterval interval(cue.startMediaTime(), endTime, &cue);
1944 m_cueData->cueTree.remove(interval);
1945
1946 // Since the cue will be removed from the media element and likely the
1947 // TextTrack might also be destroyed, notifying the region of the cue
1948 // removal shouldn't be done.
1949 auto isVTT = is<VTTCue>(cue);
1950 if (isVTT)
1951 downcast<VTTCue>(cue).notifyRegionWhenRemovingDisplayTree(false);
1952
1953 size_t index = m_cueData->currentlyActiveCues.find(interval);
1954 if (index != notFound) {
1955 cue.setIsActive(false);
1956 m_cueData->currentlyActiveCues.remove(index);
1957 }
1958
1959 cue.removeDisplayTree();
1960 updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime());
1961
1962 if (isVTT)
1963 downcast<VTTCue>(cue).notifyRegionWhenRemovingDisplayTree(true);
1964}
1965
1966CueList HTMLMediaElement::currentlyActiveCues() const
1967{
1968 if (!m_cueData)
1969 return { };
1970 return m_cueData->currentlyActiveCues;
1971}
1972
1973static inline bool isAllowedToLoadMediaURL(HTMLMediaElement& element, const URL& url, bool isInUserAgentShadowTree)
1974{
1975 // Elements in user agent show tree should load whatever the embedding document policy is.
1976 if (isInUserAgentShadowTree)
1977 return true;
1978
1979 ASSERT(element.document().contentSecurityPolicy());
1980 return element.document().contentSecurityPolicy()->allowMediaFromSource(url);
1981}
1982
1983bool HTMLMediaElement::isSafeToLoadURL(const URL& url, InvalidURLAction actionIfInvalid)
1984{
1985 if (!url.isValid()) {
1986 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, url, " is invalid");
1987 return false;
1988 }
1989
1990 RefPtr<Frame> frame = document().frame();
1991 if (!frame || !document().securityOrigin().canDisplay(url)) {
1992 if (actionIfInvalid == Complain) {
1993 FrameLoader::reportLocalLoadFailed(frame.get(), url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength());
1994 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, url , " was rejected by SecurityOrigin");
1995 }
1996 return false;
1997 }
1998
1999 if (!portAllowed(url)) {
2000 if (actionIfInvalid == Complain) {
2001 if (frame)
2002 FrameLoader::reportBlockedLoadFailed(*frame, url);
2003 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, url , " was rejected because the port is not allowed");
2004 }
2005 return false;
2006 }
2007
2008 if (!isAllowedToLoadMediaURL(*this, url, isInUserAgentShadowTree())) {
2009 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, url, " was rejected by Content Security Policy");
2010 return false;
2011 }
2012
2013 return true;
2014}
2015
2016void HTMLMediaElement::startProgressEventTimer()
2017{
2018 if (m_progressEventTimer.isActive())
2019 return;
2020
2021 m_previousProgressTime = MonotonicTime::now();
2022 // 350ms is not magic, it is in the spec!
2023 m_progressEventTimer.startRepeating(350_ms);
2024}
2025
2026void HTMLMediaElement::waitForSourceChange()
2027{
2028 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
2029
2030 stopPeriodicTimers();
2031 m_loadState = WaitingForSource;
2032
2033 // 6.17 - Waiting: Set the element's networkState attribute to the NETWORK_NO_SOURCE value
2034 m_networkState = NETWORK_NO_SOURCE;
2035
2036 // 6.18 - Set the element's show poster flag to true.
2037 setShowPosterFlag(true);
2038
2039 // 6.19 - Queue a media element task given the media element given the element to set the
2040 // element's delaying-the-load-event flag to false. This stops delaying the load event.
2041 // FIXME: this should be done in a task queue
2042 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
2043
2044 updateRenderer();
2045}
2046
2047void HTMLMediaElement::noneSupported()
2048{
2049 if (m_error)
2050 return;
2051
2052 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
2053
2054 stopPeriodicTimers();
2055 m_loadState = WaitingForSource;
2056 m_currentSourceNode = nullptr;
2057
2058 // 4.8.10.5
2059 // 6 - Reaching this step indicates that the media resource failed to load or that the given
2060 // URL could not be resolved. In one atomic operation, run the following steps:
2061
2062 // 6.1 - Set the error attribute to a new MediaError object whose code attribute is set to
2063 // MEDIA_ERR_SRC_NOT_SUPPORTED.
2064 m_error = MediaError::create(MediaError::MEDIA_ERR_SRC_NOT_SUPPORTED);
2065
2066 // 6.2 - Forget the media element's media-resource-specific text tracks.
2067 forgetResourceSpecificTracks();
2068
2069 // 6.3 - Set the element's networkState attribute to the NETWORK_NO_SOURCE value.
2070 m_networkState = NETWORK_NO_SOURCE;
2071
2072 // 6.4 - Set the element's show poster flag to true.
2073 setShowPosterFlag(true);
2074
2075 // 7 - Queue a task to fire a simple event named error at the media element.
2076 scheduleEvent(eventNames().errorEvent);
2077
2078 rejectPendingPlayPromises(WTFMove(m_pendingPlayPromises), DOMException::create(NotSupportedError));
2079
2080#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
2081 detachMediaSource();
2082#endif
2083
2084 // 8 - Set the element's delaying-the-load-event flag to false. This stops delaying the load event.
2085 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
2086
2087 // 9 - Abort these steps. Until the load() method is invoked or the src attribute is changed,
2088 // the element won't attempt to load another resource.
2089
2090 updateRenderer();
2091}
2092
2093void HTMLMediaElement::mediaLoadingFailedFatally(MediaPlayer::NetworkState error)
2094{
2095 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#loading-the-media-resource:dom-media-have_nothing-2
2096 // 17 March 2021
2097
2098 // 1 - The user agent should cancel the fetching process.
2099 stopPeriodicTimers();
2100 m_loadState = WaitingForSource;
2101
2102 // 2 - Set the error attribute to a new MediaError object whose code attribute is
2103 // set to MEDIA_ERR_NETWORK/MEDIA_ERR_DECODE.
2104 if (error == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::NetworkError)
2105 m_error = MediaError::create(MediaError::MEDIA_ERR_NETWORK);
2106 else if (error == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::DecodeError)
2107 m_error = MediaError::create(MediaError::MEDIA_ERR_DECODE);
2108 else
2109 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2110
2111#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
2112 detachMediaSource();
2113#endif
2114
2115 // 3 - Set the element's networkState attribute to the NETWORK_IDLE value.
2116 m_networkState = NETWORK_IDLE;
2117
2118 // 4 - Set the element's delaying-the-load-event flag to false. This stops delaying the load event.
2119 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
2120
2121 // 5 - Fire an event named error at the media element.
2122 scheduleEvent(eventNames().errorEvent);
2123
2124 // 6 - Abort the overall resource selection algorithm.
2125 m_currentSourceNode = nullptr;
2126}
2127
2128void HTMLMediaElement::cancelPendingEventsAndCallbacks()
2129{
2130 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
2131 m_asyncEventsCancellationGroup.cancel();
2132
2133 for (auto& source : childrenOfType<HTMLSourceElement>(*this))
2134 source.cancelPendingErrorEvent();
2135
2136 rejectPendingPlayPromises(WTFMove(m_pendingPlayPromises), DOMException::create(AbortError));
2137}
2138
2139void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerNetworkStateChanged()
2140{
2141 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
2142 setNetworkState(m_player->networkState());
2143 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
2144}
2145
2146static void logMediaLoadRequest(Page* page, const String& mediaEngine, const String& errorMessage, bool succeeded)
2147{
2148 if (!page)
2149 return;
2150
2151 DiagnosticLoggingClient& diagnosticLoggingClient = page->diagnosticLoggingClient();
2152 if (!succeeded) {
2153 diagnosticLoggingClient.logDiagnosticMessageWithResult(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::mediaLoadingFailedKey(), errorMessage, DiagnosticLoggingResultFail, ShouldSample::No);
2154 return;
2155 }
2156
2157 diagnosticLoggingClient.logDiagnosticMessage(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::mediaLoadedKey(), mediaEngine, ShouldSample::No);
2158
2159 if (!page->hasSeenAnyMediaEngine())
2160 diagnosticLoggingClient.logDiagnosticMessage(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::pageContainsAtLeastOneMediaEngineKey(), emptyString(), ShouldSample::No);
2161
2162 if (!page->hasSeenMediaEngine(mediaEngine))
2163 diagnosticLoggingClient.logDiagnosticMessage(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::pageContainsMediaEngineKey(), mediaEngine, ShouldSample::No);
2164
2165 page->sawMediaEngine(mediaEngine);
2166}
2167
2168void HTMLMediaElement::mediaLoadingFailed(MediaPlayer::NetworkState error)
2169{
2170 stopPeriodicTimers();
2171
2172 // If we failed while trying to load a <source> element, the movie was never parsed, and there are more
2173 // <source> children, schedule the next one
2174 if (m_readyState < HAVE_METADATA && m_loadState == LoadingFromSourceElement) {
2175
2176 // resource selection algorithm
2177 // Step 9.Otherwise.9 - Failed with elements: Queue a task, using the DOM manipulation task source, to fire a simple event named error at the candidate element.
2178 if (m_currentSourceNode)
2179 m_currentSourceNode->scheduleErrorEvent();
2180 else
2181 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "error event not sent, <source> was removed");
2182
2183 // 9.Otherwise.10 - Asynchronously await a stable state. The synchronous section consists of all the remaining steps of this algorithm until the algorithm says the synchronous section has ended.
2184
2185 // 9.Otherwise.11 - Forget the media element's media-resource-specific tracks.
2186 forgetResourceSpecificTracks();
2187
2188 if (havePotentialSourceChild()) {
2189 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "scheduling next <source>");
2190 scheduleNextSourceChild();
2191 } else {
2192 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "no more <source> elements, waiting");
2193 waitForSourceChange();
2194 }
2195
2196 return;
2197 }
2198
2199 if ((error == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::NetworkError && m_readyState >= HAVE_METADATA) || error == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::DecodeError)
2200 mediaLoadingFailedFatally(error);
2201 else if ((error == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError || error == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::NetworkError) && m_loadState == LoadingFromSrcAttr)
2202 noneSupported();
2203
2204 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "error = ", static_cast<int>(error));
2205
2206 logMediaLoadRequest(document().page(), String(), convertEnumerationToString(error), false);
2207
2208 mediaSession().clientCharacteristicsChanged();
2209#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
2210 if (!m_hasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners)
2211 mediaSession().setActive(false);
2212#else
2213 mediaSession().setActive(false);
2214#endif
2215}
2216
2217void HTMLMediaElement::setNetworkState(MediaPlayer::NetworkState state)
2218{
2219 if (static_cast<int>(state) != static_cast<int>(m_networkState))
2220 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "new state = ", state, ", current state = ", m_networkState);
2221
2222 if (state == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::Empty) {
2223 // Just update the cached state and leave, we can't do anything.
2224 m_networkState = NETWORK_EMPTY;
2225 return;
2226 }
2227
2228 if (state == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError || state == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::NetworkError || state == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::DecodeError) {
2229 mediaLoadingFailed(state);
2230 return;
2231 }
2232
2233 if (state == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::Idle) {
2234 if (m_networkState > NETWORK_IDLE) {
2235 changeNetworkStateFromLoadingToIdle();
2236 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
2237 } else {
2238 m_networkState = NETWORK_IDLE;
2239 }
2240 }
2241
2242 if (state == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::Loading) {
2243 if (m_networkState < NETWORK_LOADING || m_networkState == NETWORK_NO_SOURCE)
2244 startProgressEventTimer();
2245 m_networkState = NETWORK_LOADING;
2246 }
2247
2248 if (state == MediaPlayer::NetworkState::Loaded) {
2249 if (m_networkState != NETWORK_IDLE)
2250 changeNetworkStateFromLoadingToIdle();
2251 m_completelyLoaded = true;
2252 }
2253}
2254
2255void HTMLMediaElement::changeNetworkStateFromLoadingToIdle()
2256{
2257 m_progressEventTimer.stop();
2258
2259 // Schedule one last progress event so we guarantee that at least one is fired
2260 // for files that load very quickly.
2261 scheduleEvent(eventNames().progressEvent);
2262 scheduleEvent(eventNames().suspendEvent);
2263 m_networkState = NETWORK_IDLE;
2264}
2265
2266void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerReadyStateChanged()
2267{
2268 if (isSuspended()) {
2269 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this] {
2270 mediaPlayerReadyStateChanged();
2271 });
2272 return;
2273 }
2274
2275 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
2276
2277 setReadyState(m_player->readyState());
2278
2279 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
2280}
2281
2282Expected<void, MediaPlaybackDenialReason> HTMLMediaElement::canTransitionFromAutoplayToPlay() const
2283{
2284 if (m_readyState != HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA) {
2285 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "m_readyState != HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA");
2286 return makeUnexpected(MediaPlaybackDenialReason::PageConsentRequired);
2287 }
2288 if (!isAutoplaying()) {
2289 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "!isAutoplaying");
2290 return makeUnexpected(MediaPlaybackDenialReason::PageConsentRequired);
2291 }
2292 if (!mediaSession().autoplayPermitted()) {
2293 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "!mediaSession().autoplayPermitted");
2294 return makeUnexpected(MediaPlaybackDenialReason::PageConsentRequired);
2295 }
2296 if (!paused()) {
2297 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "!paused");
2298 return makeUnexpected(MediaPlaybackDenialReason::PageConsentRequired);
2299 }
2300 if (!autoplay()) {
2301 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "!autoplay");
2302 return makeUnexpected(MediaPlaybackDenialReason::PageConsentRequired);
2303 }
2304 if (pausedForUserInteraction()) {
2305 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "pausedForUserInteraction");
2306 return makeUnexpected(MediaPlaybackDenialReason::PageConsentRequired);
2307 }
2308 if (document().isSandboxed(SandboxAutomaticFeatures)) {
2309 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "isSandboxed");
2310 return makeUnexpected(MediaPlaybackDenialReason::PageConsentRequired);
2311 }
2312
2313 auto permitted = mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing);
2314#if !RELEASE_LOG_DISABLED
2315 if (!permitted)
2316 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, permitted.error());
2317 else
2318 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "can transition!");
2319#endif
2320
2321 return permitted;
2322}
2323
2324void HTMLMediaElement::dispatchPlayPauseEventsIfNeedsQuirks()
2325{
2326 if (!document().quirks().needsAutoplayPlayPauseEvents())
2327 return;
2328
2329 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
2330 scheduleEvent(eventNames().playingEvent);
2331 scheduleEvent(eventNames().pauseEvent);
2332}
2333
2334void HTMLMediaElement::setReadyState(MediaPlayer::ReadyState state)
2335{
2336 // Set "wasPotentiallyPlaying" BEFORE updating m_readyState, potentiallyPlaying() uses it
2337 bool wasPotentiallyPlaying = potentiallyPlaying();
2338
2339 ReadyState oldState = m_readyState;
2340 ReadyState newState = static_cast<ReadyState>(state);
2341
2342 bool tracksAreReady = textTracksAreReady();
2343
2344 if (newState == oldState && m_tracksAreReady == tracksAreReady)
2345 return;
2346
2347 m_tracksAreReady = tracksAreReady;
2348
2349 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "new state = ", state, ", current state = ", m_readyState);
2350
2351 if (tracksAreReady)
2352 m_readyState = newState;
2353 else {
2354 // If a media file has text tracks the readyState may not progress beyond HAVE_FUTURE_DATA until
2355 // the text tracks are ready, regardless of the state of the media file.
2356 if (newState <= HAVE_METADATA)
2357 m_readyState = newState;
2358 else
2359 m_readyState = HAVE_CURRENT_DATA;
2360 }
2361
2362 if (oldState > m_readyStateMaximum)
2363 m_readyStateMaximum = oldState;
2364
2365 if (m_networkState == NETWORK_EMPTY)
2366 return;
2367
2368 if (m_seeking) {
2369 // 4.8.10.9, step 11
2370 if (wasPotentiallyPlaying && m_readyState < HAVE_FUTURE_DATA)
2371 scheduleEvent(eventNames().waitingEvent);
2372
2373 // 4.8.10.10 step 14 & 15.
2374 if (m_seekRequested && !m_player->seeking() && m_readyState >= HAVE_CURRENT_DATA)
2375 finishSeek();
2376 } else {
2377 if (wasPotentiallyPlaying && m_readyState < HAVE_FUTURE_DATA) {
2378 // 4.8.10.8
2379 invalidateCachedTime();
2380 scheduleTimeupdateEvent(false);
2381 scheduleEvent(eventNames().waitingEvent);
2382 }
2383 }
2384
2385 if (m_readyState >= HAVE_METADATA && oldState < HAVE_METADATA) {
2386 prepareMediaFragmentURI();
2387 scheduleEvent(eventNames().durationchangeEvent);
2388 scheduleResizeEvent();
2389 scheduleEvent(eventNames().loadedmetadataEvent);
2390#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
2391 if (hasEventListeners(eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent))
2392 enqueuePlaybackTargetAvailabilityChangedEvent();
2393#endif
2394 m_initiallyMuted = m_volume < 0.05 || muted();
2395
2396 updateRenderer();
2397
2398 if (is<MediaDocument>(document()))
2399 downcast<MediaDocument>(document()).mediaElementNaturalSizeChanged(expandedIntSize(m_player->naturalSize()));
2400
2401 logMediaLoadRequest(document().page(), m_player->engineDescription(), String(), true);
2402
2403#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
2404 scheduleUpdateMediaState();
2405#endif
2406
2407 mediaSession().clientCharacteristicsChanged();
2408 }
2409
2410 if (m_readyState >= HAVE_CURRENT_DATA && oldState < HAVE_CURRENT_DATA) {
2411 if (!m_haveFiredLoadedData) {
2412 m_haveFiredLoadedData = true;
2413 scheduleEvent(eventNames().loadeddataEvent);
2414 // FIXME: It's not clear that it's correct to skip these this operation just
2415 // because m_haveFiredLoadedData is already true. At one time we were skipping
2416 // the call to setShouldDelayLoadEvent, which was definitely incorrect.
2417 applyMediaFragmentURI();
2418 }
2419 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
2420 }
2421
2422 if (m_readyState == HAVE_FUTURE_DATA && oldState <= HAVE_CURRENT_DATA && tracksAreReady)
2423 scheduleEvent(eventNames().canplayEvent);
2424
2425 if (m_readyState == HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA && oldState < HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA && tracksAreReady) {
2426 if (oldState <= HAVE_CURRENT_DATA)
2427 scheduleEvent(eventNames().canplayEvent);
2428
2429 scheduleEvent(eventNames().canplaythroughEvent);
2430
2431 auto canTransition = canTransitionFromAutoplayToPlay();
2432 if (canTransition) {
2433 m_paused = false;
2434 setShowPosterFlag(false);
2435 invalidateCachedTime();
2436 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithoutUserGesture);
2437 m_playbackStartedTime = currentMediaTime().toDouble();
2438 scheduleEvent(eventNames().playEvent);
2439 } else if (canTransition.error() == MediaPlaybackDenialReason::UserGestureRequired) {
2440 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "Autoplay blocked, user gesture required");
2441 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
2442 }
2443 }
2444
2445 // If we transition to the Future Data state and we're about to begin playing, ensure playback is actually permitted first,
2446 // honoring any playback denial reasons such as the requirement of a user gesture.
2447 if (m_readyState == HAVE_FUTURE_DATA && oldState < HAVE_FUTURE_DATA && potentiallyPlaying() && !mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing)) {
2448 auto canTransition = canTransitionFromAutoplayToPlay();
2449 if (!canTransition && canTransition.error() == MediaPlaybackDenialReason::UserGestureRequired)
2450 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "Autoplay blocked, user gesture required");
2451
2452 pauseInternal();
2453 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
2454 }
2455
2456 updatePlayState();
2457 updateMediaController();
2458 updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime());
2459}
2460
2461#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
2462#if ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
2463void HTMLMediaElement::updateShouldContinueAfterNeedKey()

2466 return;
2467 bool shouldContinue = hasEventListeners("webkitneedkey") || (document().settings().encryptedMediaAPIEnabled() && !document().quirks().hasBrokenEncryptedMediaAPISupportQuirk());
2468 m_player->setShouldContinueAfterKeyNeeded(shouldContinue);
2469}
2470#endif

2476
2477void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerKeyNeeded(Uint8Array* initData)
2478{
2479 if (!document().settings().legacyEncryptedMediaAPIEnabled())
2480 return;
2481
2482 if (!hasEventListeners("webkitneedkey")
2483#if ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
2484 // Only fire an error if ENCRYPTED_MEDIA is not enabled, to give clients of the
2485 // "encrypted" event a chance to handle it without resulting in a synthetic error.
2486 && (!document().settings().encryptedMediaAPIEnabled() || document().quirks().hasBrokenEncryptedMediaAPISupportQuirk())
2487#endif
2488 ) {
2489 m_error = MediaError::create(MediaError::MEDIA_ERR_ENCRYPTED);
2490 scheduleEvent(eventNames().errorEvent);
2491 return;
2492 }
2493
2494 auto event = WebKitMediaKeyNeededEvent::create(eventNames().webkitneedkeyEvent, initData);
2495 scheduleEvent(WTFMove(event));
2496}

2498String HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerMediaKeysStorageDirectory() const

2500 auto* page = document().page();
2501 if (!page || page->usesEphemeralSession())
2502 return emptyString();

2507
2508 return FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(storageDirectory, document().securityOrigin().data().databaseIdentifier());

2539MediaKeys* HTMLMediaElement::mediaKeys() const

2542}
2543
2544void HTMLMediaElement::setMediaKeys(MediaKeys* mediaKeys, Ref<DeferredPromise>&& promise)
2545{
2546 // https://w3c.github.io/encrypted-media/#dom-htmlmediaelement-setmediakeys
2547 // W3C Editor's Draft 23 June 2017
2548
2549 // 1. If this object's attaching media keys value is true, return a promise rejected with an InvalidStateError.
2550 if (m_attachingMediaKeys) {
2551 promise->reject(InvalidStateError);
2552 return;
2553 }
2554
2555 // 2. If mediaKeys and the mediaKeys attribute are the same object, return a resolved promise.
2556 if (mediaKeys == m_mediaKeys) {
2557 promise->resolve();
2558 return;
2559 }
2560
2561 // 3. Let this object's attaching media keys value be true.
2562 m_attachingMediaKeys = true;
2563
2564 // 4. Let promise be a new promise.
2565 // 5. Run the following steps in parallel:
2566 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this, mediaKeys = RefPtr<MediaKeys>(mediaKeys), promise = WTFMove(promise)]() mutable {
2567 if (isContextStopped())
2568 return;
2569
2570 // 5.1. If all the following conditions hold:
2571 // - mediaKeys is not null,
2572 // - the CDM instance represented by mediaKeys is already in use by another media element
2573 // - the user agent is unable to use it with this element
2574 // then let this object's attaching media keys value be false and reject promise with a QuotaExceededError.
2575 // FIXME: ^
2576
2577 // 5.2. If the mediaKeys attribute is not null, run the following steps:
2578 if (m_mediaKeys) {
2579 // 5.2.1. If the user agent or CDM do not support removing the association, let this object's attaching media keys value be false and reject promise with a NotSupportedError.
2580 // 5.2.2. If the association cannot currently be removed, let this object's attaching media keys value be false and reject promise with an InvalidStateError.
2581 // 5.2.3. Stop using the CDM instance represented by the mediaKeys attribute to decrypt media data and remove the association with the media element.
2582 // 5.2.4. If the preceding step failed, let this object's attaching media keys value be false and reject promise with the appropriate error name.
2583 // FIXME: ^
2584
2585 m_mediaKeys->detachCDMClient(*this);
2586 if (m_player)
2587 m_player->cdmInstanceDetached(m_mediaKeys->cdmInstance());
2588 }
2589
2590 // 5.3. If mediaKeys is not null, run the following steps:
2591 if (mediaKeys) {
2592 // 5.3.1. Associate the CDM instance represented by mediaKeys with the media element for decrypting media data.
2593 mediaKeys->attachCDMClient(*this);
2594 if (m_player)
2595 m_player->cdmInstanceAttached(mediaKeys->cdmInstance());
2596
2597 // 5.3.2. If the preceding step failed, run the following steps:
2598 // 5.3.2.1. Set the mediaKeys attribute to null.
2599 // 5.3.2.2. Let this object's attaching media keys value be false.
2600 // 5.3.2.3. Reject promise with a new DOMException whose name is the appropriate error name.
2601 // FIXME: ^
2602
2603 // 5.3.3. Queue a task to run the Attempt to Resume Playback If Necessary algorithm on the media element.
2604 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this] {
2605 if (!isContextStopped())
2606 attemptToResumePlaybackIfNecessary();
2607 });
2608 }
2609
2610 // 5.4. Set the mediaKeys attribute to mediaKeys.
2611 // 5.5. Let this object's attaching media keys value be false.
2612 // 5.6. Resolve promise.
2613 m_mediaKeys = WTFMove(mediaKeys);
2614 m_attachingMediaKeys = false;
2615 promise->resolve();
2616 });
2617
2618 // 6. Return promise.
2619}
2620
2621void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerInitializationDataEncountered(const String& initDataType, RefPtr<ArrayBuffer>&& initData)
2622{
2623 if (!document().settings().encryptedMediaAPIEnabled() || document().quirks().hasBrokenEncryptedMediaAPISupportQuirk())
2624 return;
2625
2626 // https://w3c.github.io/encrypted-media/#initdata-encountered
2627 // W3C Editor's Draft 23 June 2017
2628
2629 // 1. Let the media element be the specified HTMLMediaElement object.
2630 // 2. Let initDataType be the empty string.
2631 // 3. Let initData be null.
2632 // 4. If the media data is CORS-same-origin and not mixed content, run the following steps:
2633 // 4.1. Let initDataType be the string representing the Initialization Data Type of the Initialization Data.
2634 // 4.2. Let initData be the Initialization Data.
2635 // FIXME: ^
2636
2637 // 5. Queue a task to create an event named encrypted that does not bubble and is not cancellable using the
2638 // MediaEncryptedEvent interface with its type attribute set to encrypted and its isTrusted attribute
2639 // initialized to true, and dispatch it at the media element.
2640 // The event interface MediaEncryptedEvent has:
2641 // initDataType = initDataType
2642 // initData = initData
2643 MediaEncryptedEventInit initializer { initDataType, WTFMove(initData) };
2644 scheduleEvent(MediaEncryptedEvent::create(eventNames().encryptedEvent, initializer, Event::IsTrusted::Yes));
2645}
2646
2647void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerWaitingForKeyChanged()
2648{
2649 if (!m_player)
2650 return;
2651
2652 if (!m_player->waitingForKey() && m_playbackBlockedWaitingForKey) {
2653 // https://w3c.github.io/encrypted-media/#resume-playback
2654 // W3C Editor's Draft 23 June 2017
2655
2656 // NOTE: continued from HTMLMediaElement::attemptToDecrypt().
2657 // 4. If the user agent can advance the current playback position in the direction of playback:
2658 // 4.1. Set the media element's decryption blocked waiting for key value to false.
2659 // FIXME: ^
2660 // 4.2. Set the media element's playback blocked waiting for key value to false.
2661 m_playbackBlockedWaitingForKey = false;
2662
2663 // 4.3. Set the media element's readyState value to HAVE_CURRENT_DATA, HAVE_FUTURE_DATA or HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA as appropriate.
2664 setReadyState(m_player->readyState());
2665
2666 return;
2667 }
2668
2669 // https://www.w3.org/TR/encrypted-media/#wait-for-key
2670 // W3C Recommendation 18 September 2017
2671
2672 // The Wait for Key algorithm queues a waitingforkey event and
2673 // updates readyState. It should only be called when the
2674 // HTMLMediaElement object is potentially playing and its
2675 // readyState is equal to HAVE_FUTURE_DATA or greater. Requests to
2676 // run this algorithm include a target HTMLMediaElement object.
2677
2678 // The following steps are run:
2679
2680 // 1. Let the media element be the specified HTMLMediaElement
2681 // object.
2682 // 2. If the media element's playback blocked waiting for key
2683 // value is true, abort these steps.
2684 if (m_playbackBlockedWaitingForKey)
2685 return;
2686
2687 // 3. Set the media element's playback blocked waiting for key
2688 // value to true.
2689 m_playbackBlockedWaitingForKey = true;
2690
2691 // NOTE
2692 // As a result of the above step, the media element will become a
2693 // blocked media element if it wasn't already. In that case, the
2694 // media element will stop playback.
2695
2696 // 4. Follow the steps for the first matching condition from the
2697 // following list:
2698
2699 // If data for the immediate current playback position is
2700 // available
2701 // Set the readyState of media element to HAVE_CURRENT_DATA.
2702 // Otherwise
2703 // Set the readyState of media element to HAVE_METADATA.
2704 ReadyState nextReadyState = buffered()->contain(currentTime()) ? HAVE_CURRENT_DATA : HAVE_METADATA;
2705 if (nextReadyState < m_readyState)
2706 setReadyState(static_cast<MediaPlayer::ReadyState>(nextReadyState));
2707
2708 // NOTE
2709 // In other words, if the video frame and audio data for the
2710 // current playback position have been decoded because they were
2711 // unencrypted and/or successfully decrypted, set readyState to
2712 // HAVE_CURRENT_DATA. Otherwise, including if this was previously
2713 // the case but the data is no longer available, set readyState to
2714 // HAVE_METADATA.
2715
2716 // 5. Queue a task to fire a simple event named waitingforkey at the
2717 // media element.
2718 scheduleEvent(eventNames().waitingforkeyEvent);
2719
2720 // 6. Suspend playback.
2721 // GStreamer handles this without suspending explicitly.
2722}
2723
2724void HTMLMediaElement::attemptToDecrypt()
2725{
2726 // https://w3c.github.io/encrypted-media/#attempt-to-decrypt
2727 // W3C Editor's Draft 23 June 2017
2728
2729 // 1. Let the media element be the specified HTMLMediaElement object.
2730 // 2. If the media element's encrypted block queue is empty, abort these steps.
2731 // FIXME: ^
2732
2733 // 3. If the media element's mediaKeys attribute is not null, run the following steps:
2734 if (m_mediaKeys) {
2735 // 3.1. Let media keys be the MediaKeys object referenced by that attribute.
2736 // 3.2. Let cdm be the CDM instance represented by media keys's cdm instance value.
2737 auto& cdmInstance = m_mediaKeys->cdmInstance();
2738
2739 // 3.3. If cdm is no longer usable for any reason, run the following steps:
2740 // 3.3.1. Run the media data is corrupted steps of the resource fetch algorithm.
2741 // 3.3.2. Run the CDM Unavailable algorithm on media keys.
2742 // 3.3.3. Abort these steps.
2743 // FIXME: ^
2744
2745 // 3.4. If there is at least one MediaKeySession created by the media keys that is not closed, run the following steps:
2746 if (m_mediaKeys->hasOpenSessions()) {
2747 // Continued in MediaPlayer::attemptToDecryptWithInstance().
2748 if (m_player)
2749 m_player->attemptToDecryptWithInstance(cdmInstance);
2750 }
2751 }
2752
2753 // 4. Set the media element's decryption blocked waiting for key value to true.
2754 // FIXME: ^
2755}
2756
2757void HTMLMediaElement::attemptToResumePlaybackIfNecessary()
2758{
2759 // https://w3c.github.io/encrypted-media/#resume-playback
2760 // W3C Editor's Draft 23 June 2017
2761
2762 // 1. Let the media element be the specified HTMLMediaElement object.
2763 // 2. If the media element's playback blocked waiting for key is false, abort these steps.
2764 if (!m_playbackBlockedWaitingForKey)
2765 return;
2766
2767 // 3. Run the Attempt to Decrypt algorithm on the media element.
2768 attemptToDecrypt();
2769
2770 // NOTE: continued in HTMLMediaElement::waitingForKeyChanged()
2771}

2785void HTMLMediaElement::progressEventTimerFired()
2786{
2787 ASSERT(m_player);
2788 if (m_networkState != NETWORK_LOADING)
2789 return;
2790
2791 m_player->didLoadingProgress([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(this)](bool progress) {
2792 if (!weakThis)
2793 return;
2794 MonotonicTime time = MonotonicTime::now();
2795 Seconds timedelta = time - m_previousProgressTime;
2796 if (progress) {
2797 scheduleEvent(eventNames().progressEvent);
2798 m_previousProgressTime = time;
2799 m_sentStalledEvent = false;
2800 updateRenderer();
2801 } else if (timedelta > 3_s && !m_sentStalledEvent) {
2802 scheduleEvent(eventNames().stalledEvent);
2803 m_sentStalledEvent = true;
2804 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
2805 }
2806 });
2807}

2848
2849void HTMLMediaElement::fastSeek(const MediaTime& time)
2850{
2851 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, time);
2852 // 4.7.10.9 Seeking
2853 // 9. If the approximate-for-speed flag is set, adjust the new playback position to a value that will
2854 // allow for playback to resume promptly. If new playback position before this step is before current
2855 // playback position, then the adjusted new playback position must also be before the current playback
2856 // position. Similarly, if the new playback position before this step is after current playback position,
2857 // then the adjusted new playback position must also be after the current playback position.
2858 refreshCachedTime();
2859
2860 MediaTime delta = time - currentMediaTime();
2861 MediaTime negativeTolerance = delta < MediaTime::zeroTime() ? MediaTime::positiveInfiniteTime() : delta;
2862 seekWithTolerance(time, negativeTolerance, MediaTime::zeroTime(), true);
2863}

2866void HTMLMediaElement::setAudioOutputDevice(String&& deviceId, DOMPromiseDeferred<void>&& promise)
2867{
2868 auto* window = document().domWindow();
2869 auto* mediaDevices = window ? NavigatorMediaDevices::mediaDevices(window->navigator()) : nullptr;
2870 if (!mediaDevices) {
2871 promise.reject(Exception { NotAllowedError });
2872 return;
2873 }
2874
2875 if (!document().processingUserGestureForMedia() && document().settings().speakerSelectionRequiresUserGesture()) {
2876 promise.reject(Exception { NotAllowedError, "A user gesture is required"_s });
2877 return;
2878 }
2879
2880 if (deviceId.isEmpty())
2881 deviceId = { };
2882
2883 if (deviceId == m_audioOutputHashedDeviceId) {
2884 promise.resolve();
2885 return;
2886 }
2887
2888 String persistentId;
2889 if (!deviceId.isNull()) {
2890 persistentId = mediaDevices->deviceIdToPersistentId(deviceId);
2891 if (persistentId.isNull()) {
2892 promise.reject(Exception { NotFoundError });
2893 return;
2894 }
2895 }
2896
2897 m_audioOutputPersistentDeviceId = WTFMove(persistentId);
2898 if (m_player)
2899 m_player->audioOutputDeviceChanged();
2900
2901 scriptExecutionContext()->eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::MediaElement, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), deviceId = WTFMove(deviceId), promise = WTFMove(promise)]() mutable {
2902 m_audioOutputHashedDeviceId = WTFMove(deviceId);
2903 promise.resolve();
2904 });
2905}
