2919
2920void HTMLMediaElement::seekWithTolerance(const MediaTime& inTime, const MediaTime& negativeTolerance, const MediaTime& positiveTolerance, bool fromDOM)
2921{
2922 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "time = ", inTime, ", negativeTolerance = ", negativeTolerance, ", positiveTolerance = ", positiveTolerance);
2923 // 4.8.10.9 Seeking
2924 MediaTime time = inTime;
2925
2926 // 1 - Set the media element's show poster flag to false.
2927 setShowPosterFlag(false);
2928
2929 // 2 - If the media element's readyState is HAVE_NOTHING, abort these steps.
2930 if (m_readyState == HAVE_NOTHING || !m_player)
2931 return;
2932
2933 // If the media engine has been told to postpone loading data, let it go ahead now.
2934 if (m_preload < MediaPlayer::Preload::Auto && m_readyState < HAVE_FUTURE_DATA)
2935 prepareToPlay();
2936
2937 // Get the current time before setting m_seeking, m_lastSeekTime is returned once it is set.
2938 refreshCachedTime();
2939 MediaTime now = currentMediaTime();
2940
2941 // 3 - If the element's seeking IDL attribute is true, then another instance of this algorithm is
2942 // already running. Abort that other instance of the algorithm without waiting for the step that
2943 // it is running to complete.
2944 if (m_seekTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask()) {
2945 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "cancelling pending seeks");
2946 m_seekTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
2947 if (m_pendingSeek) {
2948 now = m_pendingSeek->now;
2949 m_pendingSeek = nullptr;
2950 }
2951 m_pendingSeekType = NoSeek;
2952 }
2953
2954 // 4 - Set the seeking IDL attribute to true.
2955 // The flag will be cleared when the engine tells us the time has actually changed.
2956 m_seeking = true;
2957 if (m_playing) {
2958 if (m_lastSeekTime < now)
2959 addPlayedRange(m_lastSeekTime, now);
2960 }
2961 m_lastSeekTime = time;
2962
2963 // 5 - If the seek was in response to a DOM method call or setting of an IDL attribute, then continue
2964 // the script. The remainder of these steps must be run asynchronously.
2965 m_pendingSeek = makeUnique<PendingSeek>(now, time, negativeTolerance, positiveTolerance);
2966 if (fromDOM) {
2967 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "enqueuing seek from ", now, " to ", time);
2968 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_seekTaskCancellationGroup, std::bind(&HTMLMediaElement::seekTask, this));
2969 } else
2970 seekTask();
2971
2972 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
2973 mediaSession().removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
2974}
2975
2976void HTMLMediaElement::seekTask()
2977{
2978 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
2979
2980 if (!m_player) {
2981 clearSeeking();
2982 return;
2983 }
2984
2985 ASSERT(m_pendingSeek);
2986 MediaTime now = m_pendingSeek->now;
2987 MediaTime time = m_pendingSeek->targetTime;
2988 MediaTime negativeTolerance = m_pendingSeek->negativeTolerance;
2989 MediaTime positiveTolerance = m_pendingSeek->positiveTolerance;
2990 m_pendingSeek = nullptr;
2991
2992 ASSERT(negativeTolerance >= MediaTime::zeroTime());
2993
2994 // 6 - If the new playback position is later than the end of the media resource, then let it be the end
2995 // of the media resource instead.
2996 time = std::min(time, durationMediaTime());
2997
2998 // 7 - If the new playback position is less than the earliest possible position, let it be that position instead.
2999 MediaTime earliestTime = m_player->startTime();
3000 time = std::max(time, earliestTime);
3001
3002 // Ask the media engine for the time value in the movie's time scale before comparing with current time. This
3003 // is necessary because if the seek time is not equal to currentTime but the delta is less than the movie's
3004 // time scale, we will ask the media engine to "seek" to the current movie time, which may be a noop and
3005 // not generate a timechanged callback. This means m_seeking will never be cleared and we will never
3006 // fire a 'seeked' event.
3007 if (willLog(WTFLogLevel::Info)) {
3008 MediaTime mediaTime = m_player->mediaTimeForTimeValue(time);
3009 if (time != mediaTime)
3010 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, time, " media timeline equivalent is ", mediaTime);
3011 }
3012
3013 time = m_player->mediaTimeForTimeValue(time);
3014
3015 // 8 - If the (possibly now changed) new playback position is not in one of the ranges given in the
3016 // seekable attribute, then let it be the position in one of the ranges given in the seekable attribute
3017 // that is the nearest to the new playback position. ... If there are no ranges given in the seekable
3018 // attribute then set the seeking IDL attribute to false and abort these steps.
3019 RefPtr<TimeRanges> seekableRanges = seekable();
3020 bool noSeekRequired = !seekableRanges->length();
3021
3022 // Short circuit seeking to the current time by just firing the events if no seek is required.
3023 // Don't skip calling the media engine if 1) we are in poster mode (because a seek should always cancel
3024 // poster display), or 2) if there is a pending fast seek, or 3) if this seek is not an exact seek
3025 SeekType thisSeekType = (negativeTolerance == MediaTime::zeroTime() && positiveTolerance == MediaTime::zeroTime()) ? Precise : Fast;
3026 if (!noSeekRequired && time == now && thisSeekType == Precise && m_pendingSeekType != Fast && !showPosterFlag())
3027 noSeekRequired = true;
3028
3029#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
3030 // Always notify the media engine of a seek if the source is not closed. This ensures that the source is
3031 // always in a flushed state when the 'seeking' event fires.
3032 if (m_mediaSource && !m_mediaSource->isClosed())
3033 noSeekRequired = false;
3034#endif
3035
3036 if (noSeekRequired) {
3037 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "ignored seek to ", time);
3038 if (time == now) {
3039 scheduleEvent(eventNames().seekingEvent);
3040 scheduleTimeupdateEvent(false);
3041 scheduleEvent(eventNames().seekedEvent);
3042
3043 if (document().quirks().needsCanPlayAfterSeekedQuirk() && m_readyState > HAVE_CURRENT_DATA)
3044 scheduleEvent(eventNames().canplayEvent);
3045 }
3046 clearSeeking();
3047 return;
3048 }
3049 time = seekableRanges->ranges().nearest(time);
3050
3051 m_sentEndEvent = false;
3052 m_lastSeekTime = time;
3053 m_pendingSeekType = thisSeekType;
3054 m_seeking = true;
3055
3056 // 10 - Queue a task to fire a simple event named seeking at the element.
3057 scheduleEvent(eventNames().seekingEvent);
3058
3059 // 11 - Set the current playback position to the given new playback position
3060 m_seekRequested = true;
3061 m_player->seekWithTolerance(time, negativeTolerance, positiveTolerance);
3062
3063 // 12 - Wait until the user agent has established whether or not the media data for the new playback
3064 // position is available, and, if it is, until it has decoded enough data to play back that position.
3065 // 13 - Await a stable state. The synchronous section consists of all the remaining steps of this algorithm.
3066}
3067
3068void HTMLMediaElement::clearSeeking()
3069{
3070 m_seeking = false;
3071 m_seekRequested = false;
3072 m_pendingSeekType = NoSeek;
3073 invalidateCachedTime();
3074}
3075
3076void HTMLMediaElement::finishSeek()
3077{
3078 // 4.8.10.9 Seeking
3079 // 14 - Set the seeking IDL attribute to false.
3080 clearSeeking();
3081
3082 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "current time = ", currentMediaTime());
3083
3084 // 15 - Run the time maches on steps.
3085 // Handled by mediaPlayerTimeChanged().
3086
3087 // 16 - Queue a task to fire a simple event named timeupdate at the element.
3088 scheduleEvent(eventNames().timeupdateEvent);
3089
3090 // 17 - Queue a task to fire a simple event named seeked at the element.
3091 scheduleEvent(eventNames().seekedEvent);
3092
3093 if (document().quirks().needsCanPlayAfterSeekedQuirk() && m_readyState > HAVE_CURRENT_DATA)
3094 scheduleEvent(eventNames().canplayEvent);
3095
3096 if (m_mediaSession)
3097 m_mediaSession->clientCharacteristicsChanged();
3098
3099#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
3100 if (m_mediaSource)
3101 m_mediaSource->monitorSourceBuffers();
3102#endif
3103}

3130void HTMLMediaElement::refreshCachedTime() const
3131{
3132 if (!m_player)
3133 return;
3134
3135 m_cachedTime = m_player->currentTime();
3136 if (!m_cachedTime) {
3137 // Do not use m_cachedTime until the media engine returns a non-zero value because we can't
3138 // estimate current time until playback actually begins.
3139 invalidateCachedTime();
3140 return;
3141 }
3142
3143 m_clockTimeAtLastCachedTimeUpdate = MonotonicTime::now();
3144}
3145
3146void HTMLMediaElement::invalidateCachedTime() const
3147{
3148 m_cachedTime = MediaTime::invalidTime();
3149 if (!m_player || !m_player->maximumDurationToCacheMediaTime())
3150 return;
3151
3152 // Don't try to cache movie time when playback first starts as the time reported by the engine
3153 // sometimes fluctuates for a short amount of time, so the cached time will be off if we take it
3154 // too early.
3155 static const Seconds minimumTimePlayingBeforeCacheSnapshot = 500_ms;
3156
3157 m_minimumClockTimeToUpdateCachedTime = MonotonicTime::now() + minimumTimePlayingBeforeCacheSnapshot;
3158}
3159
3160// playback state
3161double HTMLMediaElement::currentTime() const
3162{
3163 return currentMediaTime().toDouble();
3164}
3165
3166MediaTime HTMLMediaElement::currentMediaTime() const
3167{
3168#if LOG_CACHED_TIME_WARNINGS
3169 static const MediaTime minCachedDeltaForWarning = MediaTime::create(1, 100);
3170#endif
3171
3172 if (!m_player)
3173 return MediaTime::zeroTime();
3174
3175 if (m_seeking) {
3176 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "seeking, returning", m_lastSeekTime);
3177 return m_lastSeekTime;
3178 }
3179
3180 if (m_cachedTime.isValid() && m_paused) {
3181#if LOG_CACHED_TIME_WARNINGS
3182 MediaTime delta = m_cachedTime - m_player->currentTime();
3183 if (delta > minCachedDeltaForWarning)
3184 WARNING_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "cached time is ", delta, " seconds off of media time when paused");
3185#endif
3186 return m_cachedTime;
3187 }
3188
3189 // Is it too soon to use a cached time?
3190 MonotonicTime now = MonotonicTime::now();
3191 double maximumDurationToCacheMediaTime = m_player->maximumDurationToCacheMediaTime();
3192
3193 if (maximumDurationToCacheMediaTime && m_cachedTime.isValid() && !m_paused && now > m_minimumClockTimeToUpdateCachedTime) {
3194 Seconds clockDelta = now - m_clockTimeAtLastCachedTimeUpdate;
3195
3196 // Not too soon, use the cached time only if it hasn't expired.
3197 if (clockDelta.seconds() < maximumDurationToCacheMediaTime) {
3198 MediaTime adjustedCacheTime = m_cachedTime + MediaTime::createWithDouble(effectivePlaybackRate() * clockDelta.seconds());
3199
3200#if LOG_CACHED_TIME_WARNINGS
3201 MediaTime delta = adjustedCacheTime - m_player->currentTime();
3202 if (delta > minCachedDeltaForWarning)
3203 WARNING_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "cached time is ", delta, " seconds off of media time when playing");
3204#endif
3205 return adjustedCacheTime;
3206 }
3207 }
3208
3209#if LOG_CACHED_TIME_WARNINGS
3210 if (maximumDurationToCacheMediaTime && now > m_minimumClockTimeToUpdateCachedTime && m_cachedTime != MediaPlayer::invalidTime()) {
3211 Seconds clockDelta = now - m_clockTimeAtLastCachedTimeUpdate;
3212 MediaTime delta = m_cachedTime + MediaTime::createWithDouble(effectivePlaybackRate() * clockDelta.seconds()) - m_player->currentTime();
3213 WARNING_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "cached time was ", delta, " seconds off of media time when it expired");
3214 }
3215#endif
3216
3217 refreshCachedTime();
3218
3219 if (m_cachedTime.isInvalid())
3220 return MediaTime::zeroTime();
3221
3222 return m_cachedTime;
3223}

3233}

3263
3264bool HTMLMediaElement::paused() const
3265{
3266 // As of this writing, JavaScript garbage collection calls this function directly. In the past
3267 // we had problems where this was called on an object after a bad cast. The assertion below
3268 // made our regression test detect the problem, so we should keep it because of that. But note
3269 // that the value of the assertion relies on the compiler not being smart enough to know that
3270 // isHTMLUnknownElement is guaranteed to return false for an HTMLMediaElement.
3271 ASSERT(!isHTMLUnknownElement());
3272
3273 return m_paused;
3274}
3275
3276double HTMLMediaElement::defaultPlaybackRate() const
3277{
3278#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
3279 // http://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#mediastreams-in-media-elements
3280 // "defaultPlaybackRate" - On setting: ignored. On getting: return 1.0
3281 // A MediaStream is not seekable. Therefore, this attribute must always have the
3282 // value 1.0 and any attempt to alter it must be ignored. Note that this also means
3283 // that the ratechange event will not fire.
3284 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject)
3285 return 1;
3286#endif
3287
3288 return m_defaultPlaybackRate;
3289}
3290
3291void HTMLMediaElement::setDefaultPlaybackRate(double rate)
3292{
3293#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
3294 // http://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#mediastreams-in-media-elements
3295 // "defaultPlaybackRate" - On setting: ignored. On getting: return 1.0
3296 // A MediaStream is not seekable. Therefore, this attribute must always have the
3297 // value 1.0 and any attempt to alter it must be ignored. Note that this also means
3298 // that the ratechange event will not fire.
3299 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject)
3300 return;
3301#endif
3302
3303 if (m_defaultPlaybackRate == rate)
3304 return;
3305
3306 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, rate);
3307 m_defaultPlaybackRate = rate;
3308 scheduleEvent(eventNames().ratechangeEvent);
3309}

3323#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
3324 // http://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#mediastreams-in-media-elements
3325 // "playbackRate" - A MediaStream is not seekable. Therefore, this attribute must always
3326 // have the value 1.0 and any attempt to alter it must be ignored. Note that this also
3327 // means that the ratechange event will not fire.
3328 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject)

3330#endif
3331

3333}
3334
3335void HTMLMediaElement::setPlaybackRate(double rate)
3336{
3337 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, rate);
3338
3339#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
3340 // http://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#mediastreams-in-media-elements
3341 // "playbackRate" - A MediaStream is not seekable. Therefore, this attribute must always
3342 // have the value 1.0 and any attempt to alter it must be ignored. Note that this also
3343 // means that the ratechange event will not fire.
3344 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject)
3345 return;
3346#endif
3347
3348 if (m_player && potentiallyPlaying() && !m_mediaController)
3349 m_player->setRate(rate);
3350
3351 if (m_requestedPlaybackRate != rate) {
3352 m_reportedPlaybackRate = m_requestedPlaybackRate = rate;
3353 invalidateCachedTime();
3354 scheduleEvent(eventNames().ratechangeEvent);
3355 }
3356}

3359{
3360 double requestedRate = requestedPlaybackRate();
3361 if (m_player && potentiallyPlaying() && m_player->rate() != requestedRate)
3362 m_player->setRate(requestedRate);
3363}

3381
3382bool HTMLMediaElement::ended() const
3383{
3384#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
3385 // http://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#mediastreams-in-media-elements
3386 // When the MediaStream state moves from the active to the inactive state, the User Agent
3387 // must raise an ended event on the HTMLMediaElement and set its ended attribute to true.
3388 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject && m_player && m_player->ended())
3389 return true;
3390#endif
3391
3392 // 4.8.10.8 Playing the media resource
3393 // The ended attribute must return true if the media element has ended
3394 // playback and the direction of playback is forwards, and false otherwise.
3395 return endedPlayback() && requestedPlaybackRate() > 0;
3396}

3402
3403String HTMLMediaElement::preload() const
3404{
3405#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
3406 // http://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#mediastreams-in-media-elements
3407 // "preload" - On getting: none. On setting: ignored.
3408 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject)
3409 return "none"_s;
3410#endif
3411
3412 switch (m_preload) {
3413 case MediaPlayer::Preload::None:
3414 return "none"_s;
3415 case MediaPlayer::Preload::MetaData:
3416 return "metadata"_s;
3417 case MediaPlayer::Preload::Auto:
3418 return "auto"_s;
3419 }
3420
3421 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3422 return String();
3423}

3430 // "preload" - On getting: none. On setting: ignored.
3431 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject)

3437
3438void HTMLMediaElement::play(DOMPromiseDeferred<void>&& promise)
3439{
3440 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
3441
3442 auto permitted = mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing);
3443 if (!permitted) {
3444 if (permitted.error() == MediaPlaybackDenialReason::UserGestureRequired)
3445 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
3446 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "rejecting promise: ", permitted.error());
3447 promise.reject(NotAllowedError);
3448 return;
3449 }
3450
3451 if (m_error && m_error->code() == MediaError::MEDIA_ERR_SRC_NOT_SUPPORTED) {
3452 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "rejecting promise because of error");
3453 promise.reject(NotSupportedError, "The operation is not supported.");
3454 return;
3455 }
3456
3457 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
3458 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture();
3459
3460 m_pendingPlayPromises.append(WTFMove(promise));
3461 playInternal();
3462}
3463
3464void HTMLMediaElement::play()
3465{
3466 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
3467
3468 auto permitted = mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing);
3469 if (!permitted) {
3470 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "playback not permitted: ", permitted.error());
3471 if (permitted.error() == MediaPlaybackDenialReason::UserGestureRequired)
3472 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
3473 return;
3474 }
3475 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
3476 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture();
3477
3478 playInternal();
3479}
3480
3481void HTMLMediaElement::playInternal()
3482{
3483 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
3484
3485 if (isSuspended()) {
3486 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning because context is suspended");
3487 return;
3488 }
3489
3490 if (!document().hasBrowsingContext()) {
3491 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning because there is no browsing context");
3492 return;
3493 }
3494
3495 mediaSession().setActive(true);
3496 if (!mediaSession().clientWillBeginPlayback()) {
3497 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning because of interruption");
3498 return;
3499 }
3500
3501 // 4.8.10.9. Playing the media resource
3502 if (!m_player || m_networkState == NETWORK_EMPTY)
3503 selectMediaResource();
3504
3505 if (endedPlayback())
3506 seekInternal(MediaTime::zeroTime());
3507
3508 if (m_mediaController)
3509 m_mediaController->bringElementUpToSpeed(*this);
3510
3511 if (m_paused) {
3512 m_paused = false;
3513 setShowPosterFlag(false);
3514 invalidateCachedTime();
3515
3516 // This avoids the first timeUpdated event after playback starts, when currentTime is still
3517 // the same as it was when the video was paused (and the time hasn't changed yet).
3518 m_lastTimeUpdateEventMovieTime = currentMediaTime();
3519 m_playbackStartedTime = m_lastTimeUpdateEventMovieTime.toDouble();
3520
3521 scheduleEvent(eventNames().playEvent);
3522
3523 if (m_readyState <= HAVE_CURRENT_DATA)
3524 scheduleEvent(eventNames().waitingEvent);
3525 } else if (m_readyState >= HAVE_FUTURE_DATA)
3526 scheduleResolvePendingPlayPromises();
3527
3528 if (processingUserGestureForMedia()) {
3529 if (m_autoplayEventPlaybackState == AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay) {
3530 handleAutoplayEvent(AutoplayEvent::DidPlayMediaWithUserGesture);
3531 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None);
3532 } else
3533 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithUserGesture);
3534 } else
3535 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithoutUserGesture);
3536
3537 m_autoplaying = false;
3538 updatePlayState();
3539}
3540
3541void HTMLMediaElement::pause()
3542{
3543 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
3544
3545 m_temporarilyAllowingInlinePlaybackAfterFullscreen = false;
3546
3547 if (m_waitingToEnterFullscreen)
3548 m_waitingToEnterFullscreen = false;
3549
3550 if (!mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Paused))
3551 return;
3552
3553 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
3554 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
3555
3556 pauseInternal();
3557}
3558
3559void HTMLMediaElement::pauseInternal()
3560{
3561 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
3562
3563 if (isSuspended()) {
3564 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning because context is suspended");
3565 return;
3566 }
3567
3568 if (!document().hasBrowsingContext()) {
3569 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning because there is no browsing context");
3570 return;
3571 }
3572
3573 if (!mediaSession().clientWillPausePlayback()) {
3574 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning because of interruption");
3575 return;
3576 }
3577
3578 // 4.8.10.9. Playing the media resource
3579 if (!m_player || m_networkState == NETWORK_EMPTY) {
3580 // Unless the restriction on media requiring user action has been lifted
3581 // don't trigger loading if a script calls pause().
3582 if (!mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing))
3583 return;
3584 selectMediaResource();
3585 }
3586
3587 m_autoplaying = false;
3588
3589 if (processingUserGestureForMedia())
3590 userDidInterfereWithAutoplay();
3591
3592 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None);
3593
3594 if (!m_paused && !m_pausedInternal) {
3595 m_paused = true;
3596 scheduleTimeupdateEvent(false);
3597 scheduleEvent(eventNames().pauseEvent);
3598 scheduleRejectPendingPlayPromises(DOMException::create(AbortError));
3599 if (MemoryPressureHandler::singleton().isUnderMemoryPressure())
3600 purgeBufferedDataIfPossible();
3601 }
3602
3603 updatePlayState();
3604}

3609{
3610 if (!m_mediaSource)
3611 return;
3612
3613 m_mediaSource->detachFromElement(*this);
3614 m_mediaSource = nullptr;
3615}
3616
3617#endif

3646
3647double HTMLMediaElement::volume() const
3648{
3649 return m_volume;
3650}
3651
3652ExceptionOr<void> HTMLMediaElement::setVolume(double volume)
3653{
3654 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, volume);
3655
3656 if (!(volume >= 0 && volume <= 1))
3657 return Exception { IndexSizeError };
3658
3659 if (m_volume == volume)
3660 return { };
3661
3662#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3663 if (volume && processingUserGestureForMedia())
3664 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture(MediaElementSession::AllRestrictions & ~MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
3665
3666 m_volume = volume;
3667 m_volumeInitialized = true;
3668 updateVolume();
3669 scheduleEvent(eventNames().volumechangeEvent);
3670
3671 if (isPlaying() && !mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing)) {
3672 scheduleRejectPendingPlayPromises(DOMException::create(NotAllowedError));
3673 pauseInternal();
3674 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
3675 }
3676#else
3677 auto oldVolume = m_volume;
3678 m_volume = volume;
3679
3680 if (m_volumeRevertTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
3681 return { };
3682
3683 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_volumeRevertTaskCancellationGroup, [this, oldVolume] {
3684 m_volume = oldVolume;
3685 });
3686
3687#endif
3688
3689 return { };
3690}
3691
3692bool HTMLMediaElement::muted() const
3693{
3694 return m_explicitlyMuted ? m_muted : hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(mutedAttr);
3695}
3696
3697void HTMLMediaElement::setMuted(bool muted)
3698{
3699 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, muted);
3700
3701 bool mutedStateChanged = m_muted != muted;
3702 if (mutedStateChanged || !m_explicitlyMuted) {
3703 if (processingUserGestureForMedia()) {
3704 removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture(MediaElementSession::AllRestrictions & ~MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
3705
3706 if (hasAudio() && muted)
3707 userDidInterfereWithAutoplay();
3708 }
3709
3710 m_muted = muted;
3711 m_explicitlyMuted = true;
3712
3713 // Avoid recursion when the player reports volume changes.
3714 if (!processingMediaPlayerCallback()) {
3715 if (m_player) {
3716 m_player->setMuted(effectiveMuted());
3717 }
3718 }
3719
3720 if (mutedStateChanged)
3721 scheduleEvent(eventNames().volumechangeEvent);
3722
3723 updateShouldPlay();
3724
3725 document().updateIsPlayingMedia();
3726
3727#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
3728 scheduleUpdateMediaState();
3729#endif
3730 mediaSession().canProduceAudioChanged();
3731 updateSleepDisabling();
3732 }
3733
3734 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
3735}

3737#if USE(AUDIO_SESSION) && PLATFORM(MAC)
3738void HTMLMediaElement::hardwareMutedStateDidChange(AudioSession* session)
3739{
3740 if (!session->isMuted())
3741 return;
3742
3743 if (!hasAudio())
3744 return;
3745
3746 if (effectiveMuted() || !volume())
3747 return;
3748
3749 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
3750 userDidInterfereWithAutoplay();
3751}
3752#endif
3753
3754void HTMLMediaElement::togglePlayState()
3755{
3756 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "canPlay() is ", canPlay());
3757
3758 // We can safely call the internal play/pause methods, which don't check restrictions, because
3759 // this method is only called from the built-in media controller
3760 if (canPlay()) {
3761 updatePlaybackRate();
3762 playInternal();
3763 } else
3764 pauseInternal();
3765}
3766
3767void HTMLMediaElement::beginScrubbing()
3768{
3769 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "paused() is ", paused());
3770
3771 if (!paused()) {
3772 if (ended()) {
3773 // Because a media element stays in non-paused state when it reaches end, playback resumes
3774 // when the slider is dragged from the end to another position unless we pause first. Do
3775 // a "hard pause" so an event is generated, since we want to stay paused after scrubbing finishes.
3776 pause();
3777 } else {
3778 // Not at the end but we still want to pause playback so the media engine doesn't try to
3779 // continue playing during scrubbing. Pause without generating an event as we will
3780 // unpause after scrubbing finishes.
3781 setPausedInternal(true);
3782 }
3783 }
3784
3785 mediaSession().removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
3786}
3787
3788void HTMLMediaElement::endScrubbing()
3789{
3790 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "m_pausedInternal is", m_pausedInternal);
3791
3792 if (m_pausedInternal)
3793 setPausedInternal(false);
3794}
3795
3796void HTMLMediaElement::beginScanning(ScanDirection direction)
3797{
3798 m_scanType = supportsScanning() ? Scan : Seek;
3799 m_scanDirection = direction;
3800
3801 if (m_scanType == Seek) {
3802 // Scanning by seeking requires the video to be paused during scanning.
3803 m_actionAfterScan = paused() ? Nothing : Play;
3804 pause();
3805 } else {
3806 // Scanning by scanning requires the video to be playing during scanninging.
3807 m_actionAfterScan = paused() ? Pause : Nothing;
3808 play();
3809 setPlaybackRate(nextScanRate());
3810 }
3811
3812 m_scanTimer.start(0_s, m_scanType == Seek ? SeekRepeatDelay : ScanRepeatDelay);
3813}
3814
3815void HTMLMediaElement::endScanning()
3816{
3817 if (m_scanType == Scan)
3818 setPlaybackRate(defaultPlaybackRate());
3819
3820 if (m_actionAfterScan == Play)
3821 play();
3822 else if (m_actionAfterScan == Pause)
3823 pause();
3824
3825 if (m_scanTimer.isActive())
3826 m_scanTimer.stop();
3827}
3828
3829double HTMLMediaElement::nextScanRate()
3830{
3831 double rate = std::min(ScanMaximumRate, fabs(playbackRate() * 2));
3832 if (m_scanDirection == Backward)
3833 rate *= -1;
3834#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3835 rate = std::min(std::max(rate, minFastReverseRate()), maxFastForwardRate());
3836#endif
3837 return rate;
3838}
3839
3840void HTMLMediaElement::scanTimerFired()
3841{
3842 if (m_scanType == Seek) {
3843 double seekTime = m_scanDirection == Forward ? SeekTime : -SeekTime;
3844 setCurrentTime(currentTime() + seekTime);
3845 } else
3846 setPlaybackRate(nextScanRate());
3847}
3848
3849// The spec says to fire periodic timeupdate events (those sent while playing) every
3850// "15 to 250ms", we choose the slowest frequency
3851static const Seconds maxTimeupdateEventFrequency { 250_ms };
3852
3853void HTMLMediaElement::startPlaybackProgressTimer()
3854{
3855 if (m_playbackProgressTimer.isActive())
3856 return;
3857
3858 m_previousProgressTime = MonotonicTime::now();
3859 m_playbackProgressTimer.startRepeating(maxTimeupdateEventFrequency);
3860}
3861
3862void HTMLMediaElement::playbackProgressTimerFired()
3863{
3864 ASSERT(m_player);
3865
3866 if (m_fragmentEndTime.isValid() && currentMediaTime() >= m_fragmentEndTime && requestedPlaybackRate() > 0) {
3867 m_fragmentEndTime = MediaTime::invalidTime();
3868 if (!m_mediaController && !m_paused) {
3869 // changes paused to true and fires a simple event named pause at the media element.
3870 pauseInternal();
3871 }
3872 }
3873
3874 scheduleTimeupdateEvent(true);
3875
3876 if (!requestedPlaybackRate())
3877 return;
3878
3879 updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime());
3880
3881#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
3882 if (m_mediaSource)
3883 m_mediaSource->monitorSourceBuffers();
3884#endif
3885
3886 bool playbackStarted = m_autoplayEventPlaybackState == AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithUserGesture || m_autoplayEventPlaybackState == AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithoutUserGesture;
3887 if (!seeking() && playbackStarted && currentTime() - playbackStartedTime() > AutoplayInterferenceTimeThreshold) {
3888 handleAutoplayEvent(m_autoplayEventPlaybackState == AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithoutUserGesture ? AutoplayEvent::DidAutoplayMediaPastThresholdWithoutUserInterference : AutoplayEvent::DidPlayMediaWithUserGesture);
3889 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None);
3890 }
3891}
3892
3893void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleTimeupdateEvent(bool periodicEvent)
3894{
3895 MonotonicTime now = MonotonicTime::now();
3896 Seconds timedelta = now - m_clockTimeAtLastUpdateEvent;
3897
3898 // throttle the periodic events
3899 if (periodicEvent && timedelta < maxTimeupdateEventFrequency)
3900 return;
3901
3902 // Some media engines make multiple "time changed" callbacks at the same time, but we only want one
3903 // event at a given time so filter here
3904 MediaTime movieTime = currentMediaTime();
3905 if (movieTime != m_lastTimeUpdateEventMovieTime) {
3906 scheduleEvent(eventNames().timeupdateEvent);
3907 m_clockTimeAtLastUpdateEvent = now;
3908 m_lastTimeUpdateEventMovieTime = movieTime;
3909 }
3910}
3911
3912bool HTMLMediaElement::canPlay() const
3913{
3914 return paused() || ended() || m_readyState < HAVE_METADATA;
3915}
3916
3917double HTMLMediaElement::percentLoaded() const
3918{
3919 if (!m_player)
3920 return 0;
3921 MediaTime duration = m_player->duration();
3922
3923 if (!duration || duration.isPositiveInfinite() || duration.isNegativeInfinite())
3924 return 0;
3925
3926 MediaTime buffered = MediaTime::zeroTime();
3927 bool ignored;
3928 std::unique_ptr<PlatformTimeRanges> timeRanges = m_player->buffered();
3929 for (unsigned i = 0; i < timeRanges->length(); ++i) {
3930 MediaTime start = timeRanges->start(i, ignored);
3931 MediaTime end = timeRanges->end(i, ignored);
3932 buffered += end - start;
3933 }
3934 return buffered.toDouble() / duration.toDouble();
3935}
3936
3937void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerDidAddAudioTrack(AudioTrackPrivate& track)
3938{
3939 if (isPlaying() && !mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing)) {
3940 scheduleRejectPendingPlayPromises(DOMException::create(NotAllowedError));
3941 pauseInternal();
3942 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
3943 }
3944
3945 addAudioTrack(AudioTrack::create(*this, track));
3946}
3947
3948void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerDidAddTextTrack(InbandTextTrackPrivate& track)
3949{
3950 // 4.8.10.12.2 Sourcing in-band text tracks
3951 // 1. Associate the relevant data with a new text track and its corresponding new TextTrack object.
3952 auto textTrack = InbandTextTrack::create(document(), *this, track);
3953 textTrack->setMediaElement(makeWeakPtr(this));
3954
3955 // 2. Set the new text track's kind, label, and language based on the semantics of the relevant data,
3956 // as defined by the relevant specification. If there is no label in that data, then the label must
3957 // be set to the empty string.
3958 // 3. Associate the text track list of cues with the rules for updating the text track rendering appropriate
3959 // for the format in question.
3960 // 4. If the new text track's kind is metadata, then set the text track in-band metadata track dispatch type
3961 // as follows, based on the type of the media resource:
3962 // 5. Populate the new text track's list of cues with the cues parsed so far, folllowing the guidelines for exposing
3963 // cues, and begin updating it dynamically as necessary.
3964 // - Thess are all done by the media engine.
3965
3966 // 6. Set the new text track's readiness state to loaded.
3967 textTrack->setReadinessState(TextTrack::Loaded);
3968
3969 // 7. Set the new text track's mode to the mode consistent with the user's preferences and the requirements of
3970 // the relevant specification for the data.
3971 // - This will happen in configureTextTracks()
3972 scheduleConfigureTextTracks();
3973
3974 // 8. Add the new text track to the media element's list of text tracks.
3975 // 9. Fire an event with the name addtrack, that does not bubble and is not cancelable, and that uses the TrackEvent
3976 // interface, with the track attribute initialized to the text track's TextTrack object, at the media element's
3977 // textTracks attribute's TextTrackList object.
3978 addTextTrack(WTFMove(textTrack));
3979}

4055
4056void HTMLMediaElement::forgetResourceSpecificTracks()
4057{
4058 while (m_audioTracks && m_audioTracks->length())
4059 removeAudioTrack(*m_audioTracks->lastItem());
4060
4061 if (m_textTracks) {
4062 TrackDisplayUpdateScope scope { *this };
4063 for (int i = m_textTracks->length() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
4064 auto track = makeRef(*m_textTracks->item(i));
4065 if (track->trackType() == TextTrack::InBand)
4066 removeTextTrack(WTFMove(track), false);
4067 }
4068 }
4069
4070 while (m_videoTracks && m_videoTracks->length())
4071 removeVideoTrack(*m_videoTracks->lastItem());
4072}
4073
4074ExceptionOr<TextTrack&> HTMLMediaElement::addTextTrack(const String& kind, const String& label, const String& language)
4075{
4076 // 4.8.10.12.4 Text track API
4077 // The addTextTrack(kind, label, language) method of media elements, when invoked, must run the following steps:
4078
4079 // 1. If kind is not one of the following strings, then throw a SyntaxError exception and abort these steps
4080 if (!TextTrack::isValidKindKeyword(kind))
4081 return Exception { TypeError };
4082
4083 // 2. If the label argument was omitted, let label be the empty string.
4084 // 3. If the language argument was omitted, let language be the empty string.
4085 // 4. Create a new TextTrack object.
4086
4087 // 5. Create a new text track corresponding to the new object, and set its text track kind to kind, its text
4088 // track label to label, its text track language to language...
4089 auto track = TextTrack::create(&document(), this, kind, emptyString(), label, language);
4090 auto& trackReference = track.get();
4091#if !RELEASE_LOG_DISABLED
4092 trackReference.setLogger(logger(), logIdentifier());
4093#endif
4094
4095 // Note, due to side effects when changing track parameters, we have to
4096 // first append the track to the text track list.
4097
4098 // 6. Add the new text track to the media element's list of text tracks.
4099 addTextTrack(WTFMove(track));
4100
4101 // ... its text track readiness state to the text track loaded state ...
4102 trackReference.setReadinessState(TextTrack::Loaded);
4103
4104 // ... its text track mode to the text track hidden mode, and its text track list of cues to an empty list ...
4105 trackReference.setMode(TextTrack::Mode::Hidden);
4106
4107 return trackReference;
4108}

4134void HTMLMediaElement::didAddTextTrack(HTMLTrackElement& trackElement)
4135{
4136 ASSERT(trackElement.hasTagName(trackTag));
4137
4138 // 4.8.10.12.3 Sourcing out-of-band text tracks
4139 // When a track element's parent element changes and the new parent is a media element,
4140 // then the user agent must add the track element's corresponding text track to the
4141 // media element's list of text tracks ... [continues in TextTrackList::append]
4142 addTextTrack(trackElement.track());
4143
4144 // Do not schedule the track loading until parsing finishes so we don't start before all tracks
4145 // in the markup have been added.
4146 if (!m_parsingInProgress)
4147 scheduleConfigureTextTracks();
4148}
4149
4150void HTMLMediaElement::didRemoveTextTrack(HTMLTrackElement& trackElement)
4151{
4152 ASSERT(trackElement.hasTagName(trackTag));
4153
4154 auto& textTrack = trackElement.track();
4155
4156 textTrack.setHasBeenConfigured(false);
4157
4158 if (!m_textTracks)
4159 return;
4160
4161 // 4.8.10.12.3 Sourcing out-of-band text tracks
4162 // When a track element's parent element changes and the old parent was a media element,
4163 // then the user agent must remove the track element's corresponding text track from the
4164 // media element's list of text tracks.
4165 removeTextTrack(textTrack);
4166
4167 m_textTracksWhenResourceSelectionBegan.removeFirst(&textTrack);
4168}
4169
4170void HTMLMediaElement::configureTextTrackGroup(const TrackGroup& group)
4171{
4172 ASSERT(group.tracks.size());
4173
4174 Page* page = document().page();
4175 CaptionUserPreferences* captionPreferences = page ? &page->group().captionPreferences() : 0;
4176 CaptionUserPreferences::CaptionDisplayMode displayMode = captionPreferences ? captionPreferences->captionDisplayMode() : CaptionUserPreferences::Automatic;
4177
4178 // First, find the track in the group that should be enabled (if any).
4179 Vector<RefPtr<TextTrack>> currentlyEnabledTracks;
4180 RefPtr<TextTrack> trackToEnable;
4181 RefPtr<TextTrack> defaultTrack;
4182 RefPtr<TextTrack> fallbackTrack;
4183 RefPtr<TextTrack> forcedSubitleTrack;
4184 int highestTrackScore = 0;
4185 int highestForcedScore = 0;
4186
4187 // If there is a visible track, it has already been configured so it won't be considered in the loop below. We don't want to choose another
4188 // track if it is less suitable, and we do want to disable it if another track is more suitable.
4189 int alreadyVisibleTrackScore = 0;
4190 if (group.visibleTrack && captionPreferences) {
4191 alreadyVisibleTrackScore = captionPreferences->textTrackSelectionScore(group.visibleTrack.get(), this);
4192 currentlyEnabledTracks.append(group.visibleTrack);
4193 }
4194
4195 for (size_t i = 0; i < group.tracks.size(); ++i) {
4196 RefPtr<TextTrack> textTrack = group.tracks[i];
4197
4198 if (m_processingPreferenceChange && textTrack->mode() == TextTrack::Mode::Showing)
4199 currentlyEnabledTracks.append(textTrack);
4200
4201 int trackScore = captionPreferences ? captionPreferences->textTrackSelectionScore(textTrack.get(), this) : 0;
4202 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'", textTrack->kindKeyword(), "' track with language '", textTrack->language(), "' and BCP 47 language '", textTrack->validBCP47Language(), "' has score ", trackScore);
4203
4204 if (trackScore) {
4205
4206 // * If the text track kind is { [subtitles or captions] [descriptions] } and the user has indicated an interest in having a
4207 // track with this text track kind, text track language, and text track label enabled, and there is no
4208 // other text track in the media element's list of text tracks with a text track kind of either subtitles
4209 // or captions whose text track mode is showing
4210 // ...
4211 // * If the text track kind is chapters and the text track language is one that the user agent has reason
4212 // to believe is appropriate for the user, and there is no other text track in the media element's list of
4213 // text tracks with a text track kind of chapters whose text track mode is showing
4214 // Let the text track mode be showing.
4215 if (trackScore > highestTrackScore && trackScore > alreadyVisibleTrackScore) {
4216 highestTrackScore = trackScore;
4217 trackToEnable = textTrack;
4218 }
4219
4220 if (!defaultTrack && textTrack->isDefault())
4221 defaultTrack = textTrack;
4222 if (!defaultTrack && !fallbackTrack)
4223 fallbackTrack = textTrack;
4224 if (textTrack->containsOnlyForcedSubtitles() && trackScore > highestForcedScore) {
4225 forcedSubitleTrack = textTrack;
4226 highestForcedScore = trackScore;
4227 }
4228 } else if (!group.visibleTrack && !defaultTrack && textTrack->isDefault()) {
4229 // * If the track element has a default attribute specified, and there is no other text track in the media
4230 // element's list of text tracks whose text track mode is showing or showing by default
4231 // Let the text track mode be showing by default.
4232 if (group.kind != TrackGroup::CaptionsAndSubtitles || displayMode != CaptionUserPreferences::ForcedOnly)
4233 defaultTrack = textTrack;
4234 }
4235 }
4236
4237 if (displayMode != CaptionUserPreferences::Manual) {
4238 if (!trackToEnable && defaultTrack)
4239 trackToEnable = defaultTrack;
4240
4241 // If no track matches the user's preferred language, none was marked as 'default', and there is a forced subtitle track
4242 // in the same language as the language of the primary audio track, enable it.
4243 if (!trackToEnable && forcedSubitleTrack)
4244 trackToEnable = forcedSubitleTrack;
4245
4246 // If no track matches, don't disable an already visible track unless preferences say they all should be off.
4247 if (group.kind != TrackGroup::CaptionsAndSubtitles || displayMode != CaptionUserPreferences::ForcedOnly) {
4248 if (!trackToEnable && !defaultTrack && group.visibleTrack)
4249 trackToEnable = group.visibleTrack;
4250 }
4251
4252 // If no track matches the user's preferred language and non was marked 'default', enable the first track
4253 // because the user has explicitly stated a preference for this kind of track.
4254 if (!trackToEnable && fallbackTrack)
4255 trackToEnable = fallbackTrack;
4256
4257 if (trackToEnable)
4258 m_subtitleTrackLanguage = trackToEnable->language();
4259 else
4260 m_subtitleTrackLanguage = emptyString();
4261 }
4262
4263 if (currentlyEnabledTracks.size()) {
4264 for (size_t i = 0; i < currentlyEnabledTracks.size(); ++i) {
4265 RefPtr<TextTrack> textTrack = currentlyEnabledTracks[i];
4266 if (textTrack != trackToEnable)
4267 textTrack->setMode(TextTrack::Mode::Disabled);
4268 }
4269 }
4270
4271 if (trackToEnable) {
4272 trackToEnable->setMode(TextTrack::Mode::Showing);
4273
4274 // If user preferences indicate we should always display captions, make sure we reflect the
4275 // proper status via the webkitClosedCaptionsVisible API call:
4276 if (!webkitClosedCaptionsVisible() && closedCaptionsVisible() && displayMode == CaptionUserPreferences::AlwaysOn)
4277 m_webkitLegacyClosedCaptionOverride = true;
4278 }
4279
4280 m_processingPreferenceChange = false;
4281}
4282
4283static JSC::JSValue controllerJSValue(JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, HTMLMediaElement& media)
4284{
4285 JSC::VM& vm = globalObject.vm();
4286 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
4287 auto mediaJSWrapper = toJS(&lexicalGlobalObject, &globalObject, media);
4288
4289 // Retrieve the controller through the JS object graph
4290 JSC::JSObject* mediaJSWrapperObject = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSObject*>(vm, mediaJSWrapper);
4291 if (!mediaJSWrapperObject)
4292 return JSC::jsNull();
4293
4294 JSC::Identifier controlsHost = JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "controlsHost");
4295 JSC::JSValue controlsHostJSWrapper = mediaJSWrapperObject->get(&lexicalGlobalObject, controlsHost);
4296 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsNull());
4297
4298 JSC::JSObject* controlsHostJSWrapperObject = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSObject*>(vm, controlsHostJSWrapper);
4299 if (!controlsHostJSWrapperObject)
4300 return JSC::jsNull();
4301
4302 JSC::Identifier controllerID = JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "controller");
4303 JSC::JSValue controllerJSWrapper = controlsHostJSWrapperObject->get(&lexicalGlobalObject, controllerID);
4304 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsNull());
4305
4306 return controllerJSWrapper;
4307}

4318
4319bool HTMLMediaElement::setupAndCallJS(const JSSetupFunction& task)
4320{
4321 Page* page = document().page();
4322 if (!page)
4323 return false;
4324
4325 auto pendingActivity = makePendingActivity(*this);
4326 auto& world = ensureIsolatedWorld();
4327 auto& scriptController = document().frame()->script();
4328 auto* globalObject = JSC::jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(scriptController.globalObject(world));
4329 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
4330 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
4331 auto* lexicalGlobalObject = globalObject;
4332 return task(*globalObject, *lexicalGlobalObject, scriptController, world);
4333}
4334
4335void HTMLMediaElement::updateCaptionContainer()
4336{
4337 if (m_haveSetUpCaptionContainer)
4338 return;
4339
4340 if (!ensureMediaControlsInjectedScript())
4341 return;
4342
4343 ensureMediaControlsShadowRoot();
4344
4345 if (!m_mediaControlsHost)
4346 m_mediaControlsHost = MediaControlsHost::create(*this);
4347
4348 setupAndCallJS([this](JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, ScriptController&, DOMWrapperWorld&) {
4349 auto& vm = globalObject.vm();
4350 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
4351
4352 auto reportExceptionAndReturnFalse = [&] () -> bool {
4353 auto* exception = scope.exception();
4354 scope.clearException();
4355 reportException(&globalObject, exception);
4356 return false;
4357 };
4358
4359 auto controllerValue = controllerJSValue(lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, *this);
4360 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
4361
4362 auto* controllerObject = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSObject*>(vm, controllerValue);
4363 if (!controllerObject)
4364 return false;
4365
4366 // The media controls script must provide a method on the Controller object with the following details.
4367 // Name: updateCaptionContainer
4368 // Parameters:
4369 // None
4370 // Return value:
4371 // None
4372 auto methodValue = controllerObject->get(&lexicalGlobalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "updateCaptionContainer"));
4373 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
4374
4375 auto* methodObject = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSObject*>(vm, methodValue);
4376 if (!methodObject)
4377 return false;
4378
4379 auto callData = JSC::getCallData(vm, methodObject);
4380 if (callData.type == JSC::CallData::Type::None)
4381 return false;
4382
4383 JSC::MarkedArgumentBuffer noArguments;
4384 ASSERT(!noArguments.hasOverflowed());
4385 JSC::call(&lexicalGlobalObject, methodObject, callData, controllerObject, noArguments);
4386 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
4387
4388 m_haveSetUpCaptionContainer = true;
4389
4390 return true;
4391 });
4392}

4394void HTMLMediaElement::layoutSizeChanged()
4395{
4396 if (auto frameView = makeRefPtr(document().view())) {
4397 auto task = [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this)] {
4398 if (auto root = userAgentShadowRoot())
4399 root->dispatchEvent(Event::create("resize", Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
4400 };
4401 frameView->queuePostLayoutCallback(WTFMove(task));
4402 }
4403
4404 if (!m_receivedLayoutSizeChanged) {
4405 m_receivedLayoutSizeChanged = true;
4406 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
4407 }
4408
4409 // If the video is a candidate for main content, we should register it for viewport visibility callbacks
4410 // if it hasn't already been registered.
4411 if (renderer() && m_mediaSession && !m_mediaSession->wantsToObserveViewportVisibilityForAutoplay() && m_mediaSession->wantsToObserveViewportVisibilityForMediaControls())
4412 renderer()->registerForVisibleInViewportCallback();
4413}

4419
4420void HTMLMediaElement::setSelectedTextTrack(TextTrack* trackToSelect)
4421{
4422 auto* trackList = textTracks();
4423 if (!trackList || !trackList->length())
4424 return;
4425
4426 if (trackToSelect == &TextTrack::captionMenuAutomaticItem()) {
4427 if (captionDisplayMode() != CaptionUserPreferences::Automatic)
4428 m_textTracks->scheduleChangeEvent();
4429 } else if (trackToSelect == &TextTrack::captionMenuOffItem()) {
4430 for (int i = 0, length = trackList->length(); i < length; ++i)
4431 trackList->item(i)->setMode(TextTrack::Mode::Disabled);
4432
4433 if (captionDisplayMode() != CaptionUserPreferences::ForcedOnly && !trackList->isChangeEventScheduled())
4434 m_textTracks->scheduleChangeEvent();
4435 } else {
4436 if (!trackToSelect || !trackList->contains(*trackToSelect))
4437 return;
4438
4439 for (int i = 0, length = trackList->length(); i < length; ++i) {
4440 auto& track = *trackList->item(i);
4441 if (&track != trackToSelect)
4442 track.setMode(TextTrack::Mode::Disabled);
4443 else
4444 track.setMode(TextTrack::Mode::Showing);
4445 }
4446 }
4447
4448 if (!document().page())
4449 return;
4450
4451 auto& captionPreferences = document().page()->group().captionPreferences();
4452 CaptionUserPreferences::CaptionDisplayMode displayMode;
4453 if (trackToSelect == &TextTrack::captionMenuOffItem())
4454 displayMode = CaptionUserPreferences::ForcedOnly;
4455 else if (trackToSelect == &TextTrack::captionMenuAutomaticItem())
4456 displayMode = CaptionUserPreferences::Automatic;
4457 else {
4458 displayMode = CaptionUserPreferences::AlwaysOn;
4459 if (trackToSelect->validBCP47Language().length())
4460 captionPreferences.setPreferredLanguage(trackToSelect->validBCP47Language());
4461 }
4462
4463 captionPreferences.setCaptionDisplayMode(displayMode);
4464}
4465
4466void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleConfigureTextTracks()
4467{
4468 if (m_configureTextTracksTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
4469 return;
4470
4471 auto logSiteIdentifier = LOGIDENTIFIER;
4472 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "task scheduled");
4473 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_configureTextTracksTaskCancellationGroup, [this, logSiteIdentifier] {
4474 UNUSED_PARAM(logSiteIdentifier);
4475 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "lambda(), task fired");
4476 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // configureTextTracks calls methods that can trigger arbitrary DOM mutations.
4477 configureTextTracks();
4478 });
4479}
4480
4481void HTMLMediaElement::configureTextTracks()
4482{
4483 TrackGroup captionAndSubtitleTracks(TrackGroup::CaptionsAndSubtitles);
4484 TrackGroup descriptionTracks(TrackGroup::Description);
4485 TrackGroup chapterTracks(TrackGroup::Chapter);
4486 TrackGroup metadataTracks(TrackGroup::Metadata);
4487 TrackGroup otherTracks(TrackGroup::Other);
4488
4489 if (!m_textTracks)
4490 return;
4491
4492 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_textTracks->length(); ++i) {
4493 RefPtr<TextTrack> textTrack = m_textTracks->item(i);
4494 if (!textTrack)
4495 continue;
4496
4497 auto kind = textTrack->kind();
4498 TrackGroup* currentGroup;
4499 if (kind == TextTrack::Kind::Subtitles || kind == TextTrack::Kind::Captions || kind == TextTrack::Kind::Forced)
4500 currentGroup = &captionAndSubtitleTracks;
4501 else if (kind == TextTrack::Kind::Descriptions)
4502 currentGroup = &descriptionTracks;
4503 else if (kind == TextTrack::Kind::Chapters)
4504 currentGroup = &chapterTracks;
4505 else if (kind == TextTrack::Kind::Metadata)
4506 currentGroup = &metadataTracks;
4507 else
4508 currentGroup = &otherTracks;
4509
4510 if (!currentGroup->visibleTrack && textTrack->mode() == TextTrack::Mode::Showing)
4511 currentGroup->visibleTrack = textTrack;
4512 if (!currentGroup->defaultTrack && textTrack->isDefault())
4513 currentGroup->defaultTrack = textTrack;
4514
4515 // Do not add this track to the group if it has already been automatically configured
4516 // as we only want to call configureTextTrack once per track so that adding another
4517 // track after the initial configuration doesn't reconfigure every track - only those
4518 // that should be changed by the new addition. For example all metadata tracks are
4519 // disabled by default, and we don't want a track that has been enabled by script
4520 // to be disabled automatically when a new metadata track is added later.
4521 if (textTrack->hasBeenConfigured())
4522 continue;
4523
4524 if (textTrack->language().length())
4525 currentGroup->hasSrcLang = true;
4526 currentGroup->tracks.append(textTrack);
4527 }
4528
4529 if (captionAndSubtitleTracks.tracks.size())
4530 configureTextTrackGroup(captionAndSubtitleTracks);
4531 if (descriptionTracks.tracks.size())
4532 configureTextTrackGroup(descriptionTracks);
4533 if (chapterTracks.tracks.size())
4534 configureTextTrackGroup(chapterTracks);
4535 if (metadataTracks.tracks.size())
4536 configureTextTrackGroup(metadataTracks);
4537 if (otherTracks.tracks.size())
4538 configureTextTrackGroup(otherTracks);
4539
4540 updateCaptionContainer();
4541 configureTextTrackDisplay();
4542}
4543
4544bool HTMLMediaElement::havePotentialSourceChild()
4545{
4546 // Stash the current <source> node and next nodes so we can restore them after checking
4547 // to see there is another potential.
4548 RefPtr<HTMLSourceElement> currentSourceNode = m_currentSourceNode;
4549 RefPtr<HTMLSourceElement> nextNode = m_nextChildNodeToConsider;
4550
4551 URL nextURL = selectNextSourceChild(0, 0, DoNothing);
4552
4553 m_currentSourceNode = currentSourceNode;
4554 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = nextNode;
4555
4556 return nextURL.isValid();
4557}
4558
4559URL HTMLMediaElement::selectNextSourceChild(ContentType* contentType, String* keySystem, InvalidURLAction actionIfInvalid)
4560{
4561 UNUSED_PARAM(keySystem);
4562
4563 // Don't log if this was just called to find out if there are any valid <source> elements.
4564 bool shouldLog = willLog(WTFLogLevel::Debug) && actionIfInvalid != DoNothing;
4565 if (shouldLog)
4566 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
4567
4568 if (!m_nextChildNodeToConsider) {
4569 if (shouldLog)
4570 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "end of list, stopping");
4571 return URL();
4572 }
4573
4574 // Because the DOM may be mutated in the course of the following algorithm,
4575 // keep strong references to each of the child source nodes, and verify that
4576 // each still is a child of this media element before using.
4577 Vector<Ref<HTMLSourceElement>> potentialSourceNodes;
4578 auto sources = childrenOfType<HTMLSourceElement>(*this);
4579 for (auto next = m_nextChildNodeToConsider ? sources.beginAt(*m_nextChildNodeToConsider) : sources.begin(); next; ++next)
4580 potentialSourceNodes.append(*next);
4581
4582 for (auto& source : potentialSourceNodes) {
4583 if (source->parentNode() != this)
4584 continue;
4585
4586 // If candidate does not have a src attribute, or if its src attribute's value is the empty string ... jump down to the failed step below
4587 auto mediaURL = source->getNonEmptyURLAttribute(srcAttr);
4588 String type;
4589 if (shouldLog)
4590 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'src' is ", mediaURL);
4591 if (mediaURL.isEmpty())
4592 goto CheckAgain;
4593
4594 if (auto* media = source->parsedMediaAttribute(document())) {
4595 if (shouldLog)
4596 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'media' is ", source->attributeWithoutSynchronization(mediaAttr));
4597 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
4598 LOG(MediaQueries, "HTMLMediaElement %p selectNextSourceChild evaluating media queries", this);
4599 if (!MediaQueryEvaluator { "screen", document(), renderer ? &renderer->style() : nullptr }.evaluate(*media))
4600 goto CheckAgain;
4601 }
4602
4603 type = source->attributeWithoutSynchronization(typeAttr);
4604 if (type.isEmpty() && mediaURL.protocolIsData())
4605 type = mimeTypeFromDataURL(mediaURL.string());
4606 if (!type.isEmpty()) {
4607 if (shouldLog)
4608 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'type' is ", type);
4609 MediaEngineSupportParameters parameters;
4610 parameters.type = ContentType(type);
4611 parameters.url = mediaURL;
4612#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
4613 parameters.isMediaSource = mediaURL.protocolIs(mediaSourceBlobProtocol);
4614#endif
4615#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
4616 parameters.isMediaStream = mediaURL.protocolIs(mediaStreamBlobProtocol);
4617#endif
4618 if (!document().settings().allowMediaContentTypesRequiringHardwareSupportAsFallback() || Traversal<HTMLSourceElement>::nextSkippingChildren(source))
4619 parameters.contentTypesRequiringHardwareSupport = mediaContentTypesRequiringHardwareSupport();
4620
4621 if (MediaPlayer::supportsType(parameters) == MediaPlayer::SupportsType::IsNotSupported)
4622 goto CheckAgain;
4623 }
4624
4625 // Is it safe to load this url?
4626 if (!isSafeToLoadURL(mediaURL, actionIfInvalid) || !dispatchBeforeLoadEvent(mediaURL.string()))
4627 goto CheckAgain;
4628
4629 // A 'beforeload' event handler can mutate the DOM, so check to see if the source element is still a child node.
4630 if (source->parentNode() != this) {
4631 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'beforeload' removed current element");
4632 continue;
4633 }
4634
4635 // Making it this far means the <source> looks reasonable.
4636 if (contentType)
4637 *contentType = ContentType(type);
4638 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = Traversal<HTMLSourceElement>::nextSkippingChildren(source);
4639 m_currentSourceNode = WTFMove(source);
4640
4641 if (shouldLog)
4642 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, " = ", mediaURL);
4643
4644 return mediaURL;
4645
4646CheckAgain:
4647 if (actionIfInvalid == Complain)
4648 source->scheduleErrorEvent();
4649 }
4650
4651 m_currentSourceNode = nullptr;
4652 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = nullptr;
4653
4654#if !LOG_DISABLED
4655 if (shouldLog)
4656 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "failed");
4657#endif
4658 return URL();
4659}
4660
4661void HTMLMediaElement::sourceWasAdded(HTMLSourceElement& source)
4662{
4663 if (willLog(WTFLogLevel::Info) && source.hasTagName(sourceTag)) {
4664 URL url = source.getNonEmptyURLAttribute(srcAttr);
4665 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'src' is ", url);
4666 }
4667
4668 if (!document().hasBrowsingContext()) {
4669 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "<source> inserted inside a document without a browsing context is not loaded");
4670 return;
4671 }
4672
4673 // We should only consider a <source> element when there is not src attribute at all.
4674 if (hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(srcAttr))
4675 return;
4676
4677 // 4.8.8 - If a source element is inserted as a child of a media element that has no src
4678 // attribute and whose networkState has the value NETWORK_EMPTY, the user agent must invoke
4679 // the media element's resource selection algorithm.
4680 if (m_networkState == NETWORK_EMPTY) {
4681 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = &source;
4682#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
4683 if (mediaSession().dataLoadingPermitted())
4684#endif
4685 selectMediaResource();
4686 return;
4687 }
4688
4689 if (m_currentSourceNode && &source == Traversal<HTMLSourceElement>::nextSibling(*m_currentSourceNode)) {
4690 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "<source> inserted immediately after current source");
4691 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = &source;
4692 return;
4693 }
4694
4695 if (m_nextChildNodeToConsider)
4696 return;
4697
4698 // 4.8.9.5, resource selection algorithm, source elements section:
4699 // 21. Wait until the node after pointer is a node other than the end of the list. (This step might wait forever.)
4700 // 22. Asynchronously await a stable state...
4701 // 23. Set the element's delaying-the-load-event flag back to true (this delays the load event again, in case
4702 // it hasn't been fired yet).
4703 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(true);
4704
4705 // 24. Set the networkState back to NETWORK_LOADING.
4706 m_networkState = NETWORK_LOADING;
4707
4708 // 25. Jump back to the find next candidate step above.
4709 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = &source;
4710 scheduleNextSourceChild();
4711}
4712
4713void HTMLMediaElement::sourceWasRemoved(HTMLSourceElement& source)
4714{
4715 if (willLog(WTFLogLevel::Info) && source.hasTagName(sourceTag)) {
4716 URL url = source.getNonEmptyURLAttribute(srcAttr);
4717 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'src' is ", url);
4718 }
4719
4720 if (&source != m_currentSourceNode && &source != m_nextChildNodeToConsider)
4721 return;
4722
4723 if (&source == m_nextChildNodeToConsider) {
4724 m_nextChildNodeToConsider = m_currentSourceNode ? Traversal<HTMLSourceElement>::nextSibling(*m_currentSourceNode) : nullptr;
4725 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
4726 } else if (&source == m_currentSourceNode) {
4727 // Clear the current source node pointer, but don't change the movie as the spec says:
4728 // 4.8.8 - Dynamically modifying a source element and its attribute when the element is already
4729 // inserted in a video or audio element will have no effect.
4730 m_currentSourceNode = nullptr;
4731 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "m_currentSourceNode cleared");
4732 }
4733}
4734
4735void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerTimeChanged()
4736{
4737 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
4738
4739 updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime());
4740
4741 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4742
4743 invalidateCachedTime();
4744 bool wasSeeking = seeking();
4745
4746 // 4.8.10.9 step 14 & 15. Needed if no ReadyState change is associated with the seek.
4747 if (m_seekRequested && m_readyState >= HAVE_CURRENT_DATA && !m_player->seeking())
4748 finishSeek();
4749
4750 // Always call scheduleTimeupdateEvent when the media engine reports a time discontinuity,
4751 // it will only queue a 'timeupdate' event if we haven't already posted one at the current
4752 // movie time.
4753 else
4754 scheduleTimeupdateEvent(false);
4755
4756 MediaTime now = currentMediaTime();
4757 MediaTime dur = durationMediaTime();
4758 double playbackRate = requestedPlaybackRate();
4759
4760 // When the current playback position reaches the end of the media resource then the user agent must follow these steps:
4761 if (dur && dur.isValid() && !dur.isPositiveInfinite() && !dur.isNegativeInfinite()) {
4762 // If the media element has a loop attribute specified and does not have a current media controller,
4763 if (loop() && !m_mediaController && playbackRate > 0) {
4764 m_sentEndEvent = false;
4765 // then seek to the earliest possible position of the media resource and abort these steps when the direction of
4766 // playback is forwards,
4767 if (now >= dur) {
4768 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "current time (", now, ") is greater then duration (", dur, "), looping");
4769 seekInternal(MediaTime::zeroTime());
4770 }
4771 } else if ((now <= MediaTime::zeroTime() && playbackRate < 0) || (now >= dur && playbackRate > 0)) {
4772
4773 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "current time (", now, ") is greater then duration (", dur, ") or <= 0, pausing");
4774
4775 // If the media element does not have a current media controller, and the media element
4776 // has still ended playback and paused is false,
4777 if (!m_mediaController && !m_paused) {
4778 // changes paused to true and fires a simple event named pause at the media element.
4779 m_paused = true;
4780 scheduleEvent(eventNames().pauseEvent);
4781 mediaSession().clientWillPausePlayback();
4782 }
4783 // Queue a task to fire a simple event named ended at the media element.
4784 if (!m_sentEndEvent) {
4785 m_sentEndEvent = true;
4786 scheduleEvent(eventNames().endedEvent);
4787 if (!wasSeeking)
4788 addBehaviorRestrictionsOnEndIfNecessary();
4789 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None);
4790 }
4791 setPlaying(false);
4792 // If the media element has a current media controller, then report the controller state
4793 // for the media element's current media controller.
4794 updateMediaController();
4795 } else
4796 m_sentEndEvent = false;
4797 } else {
4798#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
4799 if (m_mediaStreamSrcObject) {
4800 // http://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#event-mediastream-inactive
4801 // 6. MediaStreams in Media Elements
4802 // When the MediaStream state moves from the active to the inactive state, the User Agent
4803 // must raise an ended event on the HTMLMediaElement and set its ended attribute to true.
4804 // Note that once ended equals true the HTMLMediaElement will not play media even if new
4805 // MediaStreamTrack's are added to the MediaStream (causing it to return to the active
4806 // state) unless autoplay is true or the web application restarts the element, e.g.,
4807 // by calling play()
4808 if (!m_sentEndEvent && m_player && m_player->ended()) {
4809 m_sentEndEvent = true;
4810 scheduleEvent(eventNames().endedEvent);
4811 if (!wasSeeking)
4812 addBehaviorRestrictionsOnEndIfNecessary();
4813 m_paused = true;
4814 setPlaying(false);
4815 }
4816 } else
4817#endif
4818 m_sentEndEvent = false;
4819 }
4820
4821 scheduleUpdatePlayState();
4822 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4823}
4824
4825void HTMLMediaElement::addBehaviorRestrictionsOnEndIfNecessary()
4826{
4827 if (isFullscreen())
4828 return;
4829
4830 mediaSession().addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
4831 m_playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTimer.stop();
4832 m_playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTimer.startOneShot(hideMediaControlsAfterEndedDelay);
4833}
4834
4835void HTMLMediaElement::handleSeekToPlaybackPosition(double position)
4836{
4837#if PLATFORM(MAC)
4838 // FIXME: This should ideally use faskSeek, but this causes MediaRemote's playhead to flicker upon release.
4839 // Please see <rdar://problem/28457219> for more details.
4840 seek(MediaTime::createWithDouble(position));
4841 m_seekToPlaybackPositionEndedTimer.stop();
4842 m_seekToPlaybackPositionEndedTimer.startOneShot(500_ms);
4843
4844 if (!m_isScrubbingRemotely) {
4845 m_isScrubbingRemotely = true;
4846 if (!paused())
4847 pauseInternal();
4848 }
4849#else
4850 fastSeek(position);
4851#endif
4852}
4853
4854void HTMLMediaElement::seekToPlaybackPositionEndedTimerFired()
4855{
4856#if PLATFORM(MAC)
4857 if (!m_isScrubbingRemotely)
4858 return;
4859
4860 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().sessionDidEndRemoteScrubbing(mediaSession());
4861 m_isScrubbingRemotely = false;
4862 m_seekToPlaybackPositionEndedTimer.stop();
4863#endif
4864}

4892void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerDurationChanged()
4893{
4894 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4895
4896 scheduleEvent(eventNames().durationchangeEvent);
4897 mediaPlayerCharacteristicChanged();
4898
4899 MediaTime now = currentMediaTime();
4900 MediaTime dur = durationMediaTime();
4901 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "duration = ", dur, ", current time = ", now);
4902 if (now > dur)
4903 seekInternal(dur);
4904
4905 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4906}

4908void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerRateChanged()
4909{
4910 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4911
4912 // Stash the rate in case the one we tried to set isn't what the engine is
4913 // using (eg. it can't handle the rate we set)
4914 m_reportedPlaybackRate = m_player->rate();
4915
4916 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "rate: ", m_reportedPlaybackRate);
4917
4918 if (m_playing)
4919 invalidateCachedTime();
4920
4921 updateSleepDisabling();
4922
4923 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4924}

4926void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerPlaybackStateChanged()
4927{
4928 if (!m_player || m_pausedInternal)
4929 return;
4930
4931 auto playerPaused = m_player->paused();
4932 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, playerPaused);
4933
4934 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4935 if (playerPaused)
4936 pauseInternal();
4937 else
4938 playInternal();
4939
4940 updateSleepDisabling();
4941
4942 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
4943}

4976bool HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerRenderingCanBeAccelerated()
4977{
4978 // This function must return "true" when the video is playing in the
4979 // picture-in-picture window. Otherwise, the MediaPlayerPrivate* may
4980 // destroy the video layer.
4981 if (m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture)
4982 return true;
4983
4984 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
4985 return is<RenderVideo>(renderer)
4986 && downcast<RenderVideo>(*renderer).view().compositor().canAccelerateVideoRendering(downcast<RenderVideo>(*renderer));
4987}

5014void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleMediaEngineWasUpdated()
5015{
5016 if (m_mediaEngineUpdatedTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
5017 return;
5018
5019 auto logSiteIdentifier = LOGIDENTIFIER;
5020 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "task scheduled");
5021 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_mediaEngineUpdatedTaskCancellationGroup, [this, logSiteIdentifier] {
5022 UNUSED_PARAM(logSiteIdentifier);
5023 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "lambda(), task fired");
5024 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // mediaEngineWasUpdated calls methods that can trigger arbitrary DOM mutations.
5025 mediaEngineWasUpdated();
5026 });
5027}
5028
5029void HTMLMediaElement::mediaEngineWasUpdated()
5030{
5031 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
5032
5033 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
5034 m_cachedSupportsAcceleratedRendering = m_player && m_player->supportsAcceleratedRendering();
5035 updateRenderer();
5036 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
5037
5038 mediaSession().mediaEngineUpdated();
5039
5040#if ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
5041 if (m_player && m_mediaKeys)
5042 m_player->cdmInstanceAttached(m_mediaKeys->cdmInstance());
5043#endif
5044
5045#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
5046 if (m_player && m_webKitMediaKeys)
5047 m_player->setCDM(&m_webKitMediaKeys->cdm());
5048#endif
5049
5050#if ENABLE(VIDEO_PRESENTATION_MODE)
5051 if (m_player) {
5052 m_player->setVideoFullscreenFrame(m_videoFullscreenFrame);
5053 m_player->setVideoFullscreenGravity(m_videoFullscreenGravity);
5054 m_player->setVideoFullscreenLayer(m_videoFullscreenLayer.get());
5055 }
5056#endif
5057
5058#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
5059 scheduleUpdateMediaState();
5060#endif
5061
5062#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA) && ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
5063 updateShouldContinueAfterNeedKey();
5064#endif
5065
5066 if (auto* page = document().page())
5067 page->playbackControlsMediaEngineChanged();
5068}
5069
5070void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerEngineUpdated()
5071{
5072 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, m_player->engineDescription());
5073
5074#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
5075 m_droppedVideoFrames = 0;
5076#endif
5077
5078 m_havePreparedToPlay = false;
5079
5080 scheduleMediaEngineWasUpdated();
5081}

5083// Use WTF_IGNORES_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS since this function does conditional locking, which is not
5084// supported by analysis.
5085void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerWillInitializeMediaEngine() WTF_IGNORES_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS
5086{
5087 ASSERT(isMainThread());
5088#if ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO)
5089 // Make sure the MediaElementAudioSourceNode's process function does not try and access the media player while its engine is getting updated.
5090 if (m_audioSourceNode)
5091 m_audioSourceNode->processLock().lock();
5092#endif
5093}
5094
5095// Use WTF_IGNORES_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS since this function does conditional unlocking, which is not
5096// supported by analysis.
5097void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerDidInitializeMediaEngine() WTF_IGNORES_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS
5098{
5099 ASSERT(isMainThread());
5100#if ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO)
5101 if (m_audioSourceNode) {
5102 if (auto* provider = audioSourceProvider())
5103 provider->setClient(m_audioSourceNode);
5104
5105 m_audioSourceNode->processLock().unlock();
5106 }
5107#endif
5108}

5110void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerCharacteristicChanged()
5111{
5112 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
5113
5114 beginProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
5115
5116 if (captionDisplayMode() == CaptionUserPreferences::Automatic && m_subtitleTrackLanguage != m_player->languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack())
5117 markCaptionAndSubtitleTracksAsUnconfigured(AfterDelay);
5118
5119 if (potentiallyPlaying())
5120 mediaPlayerRenderingModeChanged();
5121
5122 updateRenderer();
5123
5124 if (!paused() && !mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing)) {
5125 scheduleRejectPendingPlayPromises(DOMException::create(NotAllowedError));
5126 pauseInternal();
5127 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
5128 }
5129
5130 document().updateIsPlayingMedia();
5131
5132 checkForAudioAndVideo();
5133 updateSleepDisabling();
5134
5135 endProcessingMediaPlayerCallback();
5136}

5138Ref<TimeRanges> HTMLMediaElement::buffered() const
5139{
5140 if (!m_player)
5141 return TimeRanges::create();
5142
5143#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
5144 if (m_mediaSource)
5145 return TimeRanges::create(*m_mediaSource->buffered());
5146#endif
5147
5148 return TimeRanges::create(*m_player->buffered());
5149}
5150
5151double HTMLMediaElement::maxBufferedTime() const
5152{
5153 auto bufferedRanges = buffered();
5154 unsigned numRanges = bufferedRanges->length();
5155 if (!numRanges)
5156 return 0;
5157 return bufferedRanges.get().ranges().end(numRanges - 1).toDouble();
5158}
5159
5160Ref<TimeRanges> HTMLMediaElement::played()
5161{
5162 if (m_playing) {
5163 MediaTime time = currentMediaTime();
5164 if (time > m_lastSeekTime)
5165 addPlayedRange(m_lastSeekTime, time);
5166 }
5167
5168 if (!m_playedTimeRanges)
5169 m_playedTimeRanges = TimeRanges::create();
5170
5171 return m_playedTimeRanges->copy();
5172}
5173
5174Ref<TimeRanges> HTMLMediaElement::seekable() const
5175{
5176#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
5177 if (m_mediaSource)
5178 return m_mediaSource->seekable();
5179#endif
5180
5181 if (m_player)
5182 return TimeRanges::create(*m_player->seekable());
5183
5184 return TimeRanges::create();
5185}
5186
5187double HTMLMediaElement::seekableTimeRangesLastModifiedTime() const
5188{
5189 return m_player ? m_player->seekableTimeRangesLastModifiedTime() : 0;
5190}
5191
5192double HTMLMediaElement::liveUpdateInterval() const
5193{
5194 return m_player ? m_player->liveUpdateInterval() : 0;
5195}
5196
5197bool HTMLMediaElement::potentiallyPlaying() const
5198{
5199 if (isBlockedOnMediaController())
5200 return false;
5201
5202 if (!couldPlayIfEnoughData())
5203 return false;
5204
5205 if (m_readyState >= HAVE_FUTURE_DATA)
5206 return true;
5207
5208 return m_readyStateMaximum >= HAVE_FUTURE_DATA && m_readyState < HAVE_FUTURE_DATA;
5209}
5210
5211bool HTMLMediaElement::couldPlayIfEnoughData() const
5212{
5213 if (paused())
5214 return false;
5215
5216 if (endedPlayback())
5217 return false;
5218
5219 if (stoppedDueToErrors())
5220 return false;
5221
5222 if (pausedForUserInteraction())
5223 return false;
5224
5225 return true;
5226}
5227
5228bool HTMLMediaElement::endedPlayback() const
5229{
5230 MediaTime dur = durationMediaTime();
5231 if (!m_player || !dur.isValid())
5232 return false;
5233
5234 // 4.8.10.8 Playing the media resource
5235
5236 // A media element is said to have ended playback when the element's
5237 // readyState attribute is HAVE_METADATA or greater,
5238 if (m_readyState < HAVE_METADATA)
5239 return false;
5240
5241 // and the current playback position is the end of the media resource and the direction
5242 // of playback is forwards, Either the media element does not have a loop attribute specified,
5243 // or the media element has a current media controller.
5244 MediaTime now = currentMediaTime();
5245 if (requestedPlaybackRate() > 0)
5246 return dur > MediaTime::zeroTime() && now >= dur && (!loop() || m_mediaController);
5247
5248 // or the current playback position is the earliest possible position and the direction
5249 // of playback is backwards
5250 if (requestedPlaybackRate() < 0)
5251 return now <= MediaTime::zeroTime();
5252
5253 return false;
5254}
5255
5256bool HTMLMediaElement::stoppedDueToErrors() const
5257{
5258 if (m_readyState >= HAVE_METADATA && m_error) {
5259 RefPtr<TimeRanges> seekableRanges = seekable();
5260 if (!seekableRanges->contain(currentTime()))
5261 return true;
5262 }
5263
5264 return false;
5265}
5266
5267bool HTMLMediaElement::pausedForUserInteraction() const
5268{
5269 if (mediaSession().state() == PlatformMediaSession::Interrupted)
5270 return true;
5271
5272 return false;
5273}
