5275MediaTime HTMLMediaElement::minTimeSeekable() const
5276{
5277 return m_player ? m_player->minTimeSeekable() : MediaTime::zeroTime();
5278}
5279
5280MediaTime HTMLMediaElement::maxTimeSeekable() const
5281{
5282 return m_player ? m_player->maxTimeSeekable() : MediaTime::zeroTime();
5283}
5284
5285void HTMLMediaElement::updateVolume()
5286{
5287 if (!m_player)
5288 return;
5289#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
5290 // Only the user can change audio volume so update the cached volume and post the changed event.
5291 float volume = m_player->volume();
5292 if (m_volume != volume) {
5293 m_volume = volume;
5294 scheduleEvent(eventNames().volumechangeEvent);
5295 }
5296#else
5297 // Avoid recursion when the player reports volume changes.
5298 if (!processingMediaPlayerCallback()) {
5299 m_player->setMuted(effectiveMuted());
5300 m_player->setVolume(effectiveVolume());
5301 }
5302
5303 document().updateIsPlayingMedia();
5304#endif // PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
5305}
5306
5307void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleUpdatePlayState()
5308{
5309 if (m_updatePlayStateTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
5310 return;
5311
5312 auto logSiteIdentifier = LOGIDENTIFIER;
5313 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "task scheduled");
5314 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_updatePlayStateTaskCancellationGroup, [this, logSiteIdentifier] {
5315 UNUSED_PARAM(logSiteIdentifier);
5316 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "lambda(), task fired");
5317 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // updatePlayState calls methods that can trigger arbitrary DOM mutations.
5318 updatePlayState();
5319 });
5320}
5321
5322void HTMLMediaElement::updatePlayState()
5323{
5324 if (!m_player)
5325 return;
5326
5327 if (m_pausedInternal) {
5328 if (!m_player->paused())
5329 m_player->pause();
5330 refreshCachedTime();
5331 m_playbackProgressTimer.stop();
5332 return;
5333 }
5334
5335 bool shouldBePlaying = potentiallyPlaying();
5336 bool playerPaused = m_player->paused();
5337
5338 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "shouldBePlaying = ", shouldBePlaying, ", playerPaused = ", playerPaused);
5339
5340 if (shouldBePlaying && playerPaused && mediaSession().requiresFullscreenForVideoPlayback() && (m_waitingToEnterFullscreen || !isFullscreen())) {
5341 if (!m_waitingToEnterFullscreen)
5342 enterFullscreen();
5343
5344#if PLATFORM(WATCHOS)
5345 // FIXME: Investigate doing this for all builds.
5346 return;
5347#endif
5348 }
5349
5350 if (shouldBePlaying) {
5351 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
5352
5353 invalidateCachedTime();
5354
5355 if (playerPaused) {
5356 mediaSession().clientWillBeginPlayback();
5357
5358 // Set rate, muted and volume before calling play in case they were set before the media engine was set up.
5359 // The media engine should just stash the rate, muted and volume values since it isn't already playing.
5360 m_player->setRate(requestedPlaybackRate());
5361 m_player->setMuted(effectiveMuted());
5362 m_player->setVolume(effectiveVolume());
5363
5364 if (m_firstTimePlaying) {
5365 // Log that a media element was played.
5366 if (auto* page = document().page())
5367 page->diagnosticLoggingClient().logDiagnosticMessage(isVideo() ? DiagnosticLoggingKeys::videoKey() : DiagnosticLoggingKeys::audioKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::playedKey(), ShouldSample::No);
5368 m_firstTimePlaying = false;
5369 }
5370
5371 m_player->play();
5372 }
5373
5374 startPlaybackProgressTimer();
5375 setPlaying(true);
5376 } else {
5377 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
5378
5379 if (!playerPaused)
5380 m_player->pause();
5381 refreshCachedTime();
5382
5383 m_playbackProgressTimer.stop();
5384 setPlaying(false);
5385 MediaTime time = currentMediaTime();
5386 if (time > m_lastSeekTime)
5387 addPlayedRange(m_lastSeekTime, time);
5388
5389 if (couldPlayIfEnoughData())
5390 prepareToPlay();
5391 }
5392
5393 updateMediaController();
5394 updateRenderer();
5395
5396 checkForAudioAndVideo();
5397}
5398
5399void HTMLMediaElement::checkForAudioAndVideo()
5400{
5401 m_hasEverHadAudio |= hasAudio();
5402 m_hasEverHadVideo |= hasVideo();
5403 mediaSession().canProduceAudioChanged();
5404}
5405
5406void HTMLMediaElement::setPlaying(bool playing)
5407{
5408 if (playing && m_mediaSession)
5409 m_mediaSession->removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequirePlaybackToControlControlsManager);
5410
5411 if (m_playing == playing)
5412 return;
5413
5414 m_playing = playing;
5415
5416 if (m_playing)
5417 scheduleNotifyAboutPlaying();
5418
5419 document().updateIsPlayingMedia();
5420
5421#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
5422 scheduleUpdateMediaState();
5423#endif
5424}

5427{
5428 m_pausedInternal = b;
5429 scheduleUpdatePlayState();
5430}

5435 updatePlayState();
5436}

5444void HTMLMediaElement::cancelPendingTasks()
5445{
5446 m_configureTextTracksTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5447 m_checkPlaybackTargetCompatibilityTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5448 m_updateMediaStateTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5449 m_mediaEngineUpdatedTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5450 m_updatePlayStateTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5451 m_resumeTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5452 m_seekTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5453 m_playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5454#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
5455 m_volumeRevertTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5456#endif
5457}
5458
5459void HTMLMediaElement::userCancelledLoad()
5460{
5461 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
5462
5463 // FIXME: We should look to reconcile the iOS and non-iOS code (below).
5464#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
5465 if (m_networkState == NETWORK_EMPTY || m_readyState >= HAVE_METADATA)
5466 return;
5467#else
5468 if (m_networkState == NETWORK_EMPTY || m_completelyLoaded)
5469 return;
5470#endif
5471
5472 // If the media data fetching process is aborted by the user:
5473
5474 // 1 - The user agent should cancel the fetching process.
5475 clearMediaPlayer();
5476
5477 // 2 - Set the error attribute to a new MediaError object whose code attribute is set to MEDIA_ERR_ABORTED.
5478 m_error = MediaError::create(MediaError::MEDIA_ERR_ABORTED);
5479
5480 // 3 - Queue a task to fire a simple event named error at the media element.
5481 scheduleEvent(eventNames().abortEvent);
5482
5483#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
5484 detachMediaSource();
5485#endif
5486
5487 // 4 - If the media element's readyState attribute has a value equal to HAVE_NOTHING, set the
5488 // element's networkState attribute to the NETWORK_EMPTY value, set the element's show poster
5489 // flag to true, and fire an event named emptied at the element.
5490 if (m_readyState == HAVE_NOTHING) {
5491 m_networkState = NETWORK_EMPTY;
5492 setShowPosterFlag(true);
5493 scheduleEvent(eventNames().emptiedEvent);
5494 }
5495 else
5496 m_networkState = NETWORK_IDLE;
5497
5498 // 5 - Set the element's delaying-the-load-event flag to false. This stops delaying the load event.
5499 setShouldDelayLoadEvent(false);
5500
5501 // 6 - Abort the overall resource selection algorithm.
5502 m_currentSourceNode = nullptr;
5503
5504 // Reset m_readyState since m_player is gone.
5505 m_readyState = HAVE_NOTHING;
5506 updateMediaController();
5507
5508 auto* context = scriptExecutionContext();
5509 if (!context || context->activeDOMObjectsAreStopped())
5510 return; // Document is about to be destructed. Avoid updating layout in updateActiveTextTrackCues.
5511
5512 updateActiveTextTrackCues(MediaTime::zeroTime());
5513}
5514
5515void HTMLMediaElement::clearMediaPlayer()
5516{
5517#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
5518 if (!m_settingMediaStreamSrcObject)
5519 m_mediaStreamSrcObject = nullptr;
5520#endif
5521
5522#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
5523 detachMediaSource();
5524#endif
5525
5526 m_blob = nullptr;
5527
5528 forgetResourceSpecificTracks();
5529
5530#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
5531 if (hasEventListeners(eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent) || m_remote->hasAvailabilityCallbacks()) {
5532 m_hasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners = false;
5533 if (m_mediaSession)
5534 m_mediaSession->setHasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners(false);
5535
5536 // Send an availability event in case scripts want to hide the picker when the element
5537 // doesn't support playback to a target.
5538 enqueuePlaybackTargetAvailabilityChangedEvent();
5539 }
5540
5541 if (m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget)
5542 setIsPlayingToWirelessTarget(false);
5543#endif
5544
5545 if (m_isWaitingUntilMediaCanStart) {
5546 m_isWaitingUntilMediaCanStart = false;
5547 document().removeMediaCanStartListener(*this);
5548 }
5549
5550 if (m_player) {
5551 m_player->invalidate();
5552 m_player = nullptr;
5553 m_cachedSupportsAcceleratedRendering = false;
5554 }
5555 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
5556
5557 stopPeriodicTimers();
5558 cancelPendingTasks();
5559
5560 m_loadState = WaitingForSource;
5561
5562 if (m_textTracks)
5563 configureTextTrackDisplay();
5564
5565 if (m_mediaSession) {
5566 m_mediaSession->clientCharacteristicsChanged();
5567 m_mediaSession->canProduceAudioChanged();
5568 }
5569
5570 m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5571
5572 updateSleepDisabling();
5573}
5574
5575const char* HTMLMediaElement::activeDOMObjectName() const
5576{
5577 return "HTMLMediaElement";
5578}
5579
5580void HTMLMediaElement::stopWithoutDestroyingMediaPlayer()
5581{
5582 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
5583
5584 if (m_videoFullscreenMode != VideoFullscreenModeNone)
5585 exitFullscreen();
5586
5587 setPreparedToReturnVideoLayerToInline(true);
5588
5589 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
5590 setInActiveDocument(false);
5591
5592 // Stop the playback without generating events
5593 setPlaying(false);
5594 pauseAndUpdatePlayStateImmediately();
5595 if (m_mediaSession)
5596 m_mediaSession->clientWillBeDOMSuspended();
5597
5598 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None);
5599
5600 userCancelledLoad();
5601
5602 updateRenderer();
5603
5604 stopPeriodicTimers();
5605
5606 updateSleepDisabling();
5607}
5608
5609void HTMLMediaElement::closeTaskQueues()
5610{
5611 cancelPendingTasks();
5612 m_resourceSelectionTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5613 m_asyncEventsCancellationGroup.cancel();
5614}
5615
5616void HTMLMediaElement::contextDestroyed()
5617{
5618 closeTaskQueues();
5619 m_pendingPlayPromises.clear();
5620
5621 ActiveDOMObject::contextDestroyed();
5622}
5623
5624void HTMLMediaElement::stop()
5625{
5626 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
5627
5628 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this);
5629 stopWithoutDestroyingMediaPlayer();
5630 closeTaskQueues();
5631
5632 // Once an active DOM object has been stopped it can not be restarted, so we can deallocate
5633 // the media player now. Note that userCancelledLoad will already called clearMediaPlayer
5634 // if the media was not fully loaded, but we need the same cleanup if the file was completely
5635 // loaded and calling it again won't cause any problems.
5636 clearMediaPlayer();
5637
5638 if (m_mediaSession)
5639 m_mediaSession->stopSession();
5640}
5641
5642void HTMLMediaElement::suspend(ReasonForSuspension reason)
5643{
5644 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
5645 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this);
5646
5647 m_resumeTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
5648
5649 switch (reason) {
5650 case ReasonForSuspension::BackForwardCache:
5651 stopWithoutDestroyingMediaPlayer();
5652 setBufferingPolicy(BufferingPolicy::MakeResourcesPurgeable);
5653 if (m_mediaSession)
5654 m_mediaSession->addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequirePageConsentToResumeMedia);
5655 break;
5656 case ReasonForSuspension::PageWillBeSuspended:
5657 case ReasonForSuspension::JavaScriptDebuggerPaused:
5658 case ReasonForSuspension::WillDeferLoading:
5659 // Do nothing, we don't pause media playback in these cases.
5660 break;
5661 }
5662}
5663
5664void HTMLMediaElement::resume()
5665{
5666 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
5667
5668 setInActiveDocument(true);
5669
5670 if (m_mediaSession && !m_mediaSession->pageAllowsPlaybackAfterResuming())
5671 document().addMediaCanStartListener(*this);
5672 else
5673 setPausedInternal(false);
5674
5675 if (m_mediaSession) {
5676 m_mediaSession->removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequirePageConsentToResumeMedia);
5677 m_mediaSession->updateBufferingPolicy();
5678 }
5679
5680 if (m_error && m_error->code() == MediaError::MEDIA_ERR_ABORTED && !m_resumeTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask()) {
5681 // Restart the load if it was aborted in the middle by moving the document to the back/forward cache.
5682 // m_error is only left at MEDIA_ERR_ABORTED when the document becomes inactive (it is set to
5683 // MEDIA_ERR_ABORTED while the abortEvent is being sent, but cleared immediately afterwards).
5684 // This behavior is not specified but it seems like a sensible thing to do.
5685 // As it is not safe to immedately start loading now, let's schedule a load.
5686 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_resumeTaskCancellationGroup, std::bind(&HTMLMediaElement::prepareForLoad, this));
5687 }
5688
5689 updateRenderer();
5690}
5691
5692bool HTMLMediaElement::hasLiveSource() const
5693{
5694 // FIXME: Handle the case of an ended media stream as srcObject.
5695 return m_player && m_player->hasMediaEngine() && (!ended() || seeking() || m_networkState >= NETWORK_IDLE);
5696}
5697
5698bool HTMLMediaElement::virtualHasPendingActivity() const
5699{
5700 return m_creatingControls
5701 || (hasAudio() && isPlaying())
5702 || (hasLiveSource() && hasEventListeners());
5703}

5714void HTMLMediaElement::visibilityStateChanged()
5715{
5716 bool elementIsHidden = document().hidden() && m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeNone;
5717 if (elementIsHidden == m_elementIsHidden)
5718 return;
5719
5720 m_elementIsHidden = elementIsHidden;
5721 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "visible = ", !m_elementIsHidden);
5722
5723 updateSleepDisabling();
5724 mediaSession().visibilityChanged();
5725 if (m_player)
5726 m_player->setVisible(!m_elementIsHidden);
5727
5728 bool isPlayingAudio = isPlaying() && hasAudio() && !muted() && volume();
5729 if (!isPlayingAudio) {
5730 if (m_elementIsHidden) {
5731 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "Suspending playback after going to the background");
5732 mediaSession().beginInterruption(PlatformMediaSession::EnteringBackground);
5733 } else {
5734 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "Resuming playback after entering foreground");
5735 mediaSession().endInterruption(PlatformMediaSession::MayResumePlaying);
5736 }
5737 }
5738}

5784void HTMLMediaElement::setIsPlayingToWirelessTarget(bool isPlayingToWirelessTarget)
5785{
5786 auto logSiteIdentifier = LOGIDENTIFIER;
5787 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this, isPlayingToWirelessTarget, logSiteIdentifier] {
5788 if (isContextStopped())
5789 return;
5790
5791 UNUSED_PARAM(logSiteIdentifier);
5792
5793 if (isPlayingToWirelessTarget == m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget)
5794 return;
5795
5796 m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget = m_player && m_player->isCurrentPlaybackTargetWireless();
5797 m_remote->isPlayingToRemoteTargetChanged(m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget);
5798 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget);
5799 configureMediaControls();
5800 mediaSession().isPlayingToWirelessPlaybackTargetChanged(m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget);
5801 mediaSession().canProduceAudioChanged();
5802 scheduleUpdateMediaState();
5803 updateSleepDisabling();
5804
5805 m_failedToPlayToWirelessTarget = false;
5806 m_currentPlaybackTargetIsWirelessEventFiredTime = MonotonicTime::now();
5807 scheduleCheckPlaybackTargetCompatability();
5808
5809 if (!isContextStopped())
5810 dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().webkitcurrentplaybacktargetiswirelesschangedEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::Yes));
5811 });
5812}

5819 scheduleEvent(WTFMove(event));

5858
5859void HTMLMediaElement::dispatchEvent(Event& event)
5860{
5861 DEBUG_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, event.type());
5862
5863 if (event.type() == eventNames().endedEvent) {
5864 if (m_removedBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture)
5865 document().userActivatedMediaFinishedPlaying();
5866
5867 updateSleepDisabling();
5868 }
5869
5870 HTMLElement::dispatchEvent(event);
5871
5872 // Some pages may change the position/size of an inline video element
5873 // when/after the video element enters fullscreen (rdar://problem/55814988).
5874 // We need to fire the end fullscreen event to notify the page
5875 // to change the position/size back *before* exiting fullscreen.
5876 // Otherwise, the exit fullscreen animation will be incorrect.
5877 if (!m_videoFullscreenStandby && m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeNone && event.type() == eventNames().webkitendfullscreenEvent)
5878 document().page()->chrome().client().exitVideoFullscreenForVideoElement(downcast<HTMLVideoElement>(*this));
5879}
5880
5881bool HTMLMediaElement::addEventListener(const AtomString& eventType, Ref<EventListener>&& listener, const AddEventListenerOptions& options)
5882{
5883#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA) && ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
5884 if (eventType == eventNames().webkitneedkeyEvent)
5885 updateShouldContinueAfterNeedKey();
5886#endif
5887
5888#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
5889 if (eventType != eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent)
5890 return Node::addEventListener(eventType, WTFMove(listener), options);
5891
5892 bool isFirstAvailabilityChangedListener = !hasEventListeners(eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent) && !m_remote->hasAvailabilityCallbacks();
5893
5894 if (!Node::addEventListener(eventType, WTFMove(listener), options))
5895 return false;
5896
5897 if (isFirstAvailabilityChangedListener) {
5898 m_hasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners = true;
5899 mediaSession().setActive(true);
5900 mediaSession().setHasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners(true);
5901 }
5902
5903 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "'webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychanged'");
5904
5905 enqueuePlaybackTargetAvailabilityChangedEvent(); // Ensure the event listener gets at least one event.
5906 return true;
5907#else
5908 return Node::addEventListener(eventType, WTFMove(listener), options);
5909#endif // ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
5910}
5911
5912bool HTMLMediaElement::removeEventListener(const AtomString& eventType, EventListener& listener, const EventListenerOptions& options)
5913{
5914#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA) && ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
5915 if (eventType == eventNames().webkitneedkeyEvent)
5916 updateShouldContinueAfterNeedKey();
5917#endif
5918
5919 bool listenerWasRemoved = Node::removeEventListener(eventType, listener, options);
5920#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
5921 if (eventType != eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent)
5922 return listenerWasRemoved;
5923
5924 if (!listenerWasRemoved)
5925 return false;
5926
5927 bool didRemoveLastAvailabilityChangedListener = !hasEventListeners(eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent) && !m_remote->hasAvailabilityCallbacks();
5928 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "removed last listener = ", didRemoveLastAvailabilityChangedListener);
5929 if (didRemoveLastAvailabilityChangedListener) {
5930 m_hasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners = false;
5931 mediaSession().setHasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners(false);
5932 scheduleUpdateMediaState();
5933 }
5934#endif // ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
5935
5936 return listenerWasRemoved;
5937}

5994
5995void HTMLMediaElement::enterFullscreen(VideoFullscreenMode mode)
5996{
5997 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, ", m_videoFullscreenMode = ", m_videoFullscreenMode, ", mode = ", mode);
5998 ASSERT(mode != VideoFullscreenModeNone);
5999
6000 if (m_videoFullscreenMode == mode)
6001 return;
6002
6003 if (m_waitingToEnterFullscreen)
6004 return;
6005
6006 m_changingVideoFullscreenMode = true;
6007
6008#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API) && ENABLE(VIDEO_USES_ELEMENT_FULLSCREEN)
6009 if (document().settings().fullScreenEnabled() && mode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard) {
6010 m_temporarilyAllowingInlinePlaybackAfterFullscreen = false;
6011 m_waitingToEnterFullscreen = true;
6012 document().fullscreenManager().requestFullscreenForElement(this, FullscreenManager::ExemptIFrameAllowFullscreenRequirement);
6013 return;
6014 }
6015#endif
6016
6017 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this, mode] {
6018 if (isContextStopped())
6019 return;
6020
6021 if (document().hidden()) {
6022 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, " returning because document is hidden");
6023 m_changingVideoFullscreenMode = false;
6024 return;
6025 }
6026
6027 if (is<HTMLVideoElement>(*this)) {
6028 HTMLVideoElement& asVideo = downcast<HTMLVideoElement>(*this);
6029 if (document().page()->chrome().client().supportsVideoFullscreen(mode)) {
6030 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "Entering fullscreen mode ", mode, ", m_videoFullscreenStandby = ", m_videoFullscreenStandby);
6031
6032 m_temporarilyAllowingInlinePlaybackAfterFullscreen = false;
6033 if (mode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard)
6034 m_waitingToEnterFullscreen = true;
6035
6036 auto oldMode = m_videoFullscreenMode;
6037 setFullscreenMode(mode);
6038 configureMediaControls();
6039
6040 document().page()->chrome().client().enterVideoFullscreenForVideoElement(asVideo, m_videoFullscreenMode, m_videoFullscreenStandby);
6041 if (m_videoFullscreenStandby)
6042 return;
6043
6044 if (mode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard)
6045 scheduleEvent(eventNames().webkitbeginfullscreenEvent);
6046 else if (oldMode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard && !document().quirks().shouldDisableEndFullscreenEventWhenEnteringPictureInPictureFromFullscreenQuirk())
6047 scheduleEvent(eventNames().webkitendfullscreenEvent);
6048
6049 return;
6050 }
6051 }
6052
6053 m_changingVideoFullscreenMode = false;
6054 });
6055}
6056
6057void HTMLMediaElement::enterFullscreen()
6058{
6059 enterFullscreen(VideoFullscreenModeStandard);
6060}
6061
6062void HTMLMediaElement::exitFullscreen()
6063{
6064 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
6065
6066 m_waitingToEnterFullscreen = false;
6067
6068#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
6069 if (document().settings().fullScreenEnabled() && document().fullscreenManager().currentFullscreenElement() == this) {
6070 if (document().fullscreenManager().isFullscreen()) {
6071 m_changingVideoFullscreenMode = true;
6072 document().fullscreenManager().cancelFullscreen();
6073 }
6074
6075 if (m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard)
6076 return;
6077 }
6078#endif
6079
6080 ASSERT(m_videoFullscreenMode != VideoFullscreenModeNone);
6081 VideoFullscreenMode oldVideoFullscreenMode = m_videoFullscreenMode;
6082 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // updateMediaControlsAfterPresentationModeChange calls methods that can trigger arbitrary DOM mutations.
6083 updateMediaControlsAfterPresentationModeChange();
6084
6085 if (!document().page() || !is<HTMLVideoElement>(*this))
6086 return;
6087
6088 if (!paused() && mediaSession().requiresFullscreenForVideoPlayback()) {
6089 if (!document().settings().allowsInlineMediaPlaybackAfterFullscreen() || isVideoTooSmallForInlinePlayback())
6090 pauseInternal();
6091 else {
6092 // Allow inline playback, but set a flag so pausing and starting again (e.g. when scrubbing or looping) won't go back to fullscreen.
6093 // Also set the controls attribute so the user will be able to control playback.
6094 m_temporarilyAllowingInlinePlaybackAfterFullscreen = true;
6095 setControls(true);
6096 }
6097 }
6098
6099 if (document().activeDOMObjectsAreSuspended() || document().activeDOMObjectsAreStopped()) {
6100 setFullscreenMode(VideoFullscreenModeNone);
6101 document().page()->chrome().client().exitVideoFullscreenToModeWithoutAnimation(downcast<HTMLVideoElement>(*this), VideoFullscreenModeNone);
6102 } else if (document().page()->chrome().client().supportsVideoFullscreen(oldVideoFullscreenMode)) {
6103 if (m_videoFullscreenStandby) {
6104 setFullscreenMode(VideoFullscreenModeNone);
6105 m_changingVideoFullscreenMode = true;
6106 document().page()->chrome().client().enterVideoFullscreenForVideoElement(downcast<HTMLVideoElement>(*this), m_videoFullscreenMode, m_videoFullscreenStandby);
6107 return;
6108 }
6109
6110 m_changingVideoFullscreenMode = true;
6111
6112 if (oldVideoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard) {
6113 setFullscreenMode(VideoFullscreenModeNone);
6114 // The exit fullscreen request will be sent in dispatchEvent().
6115 scheduleEvent(eventNames().webkitendfullscreenEvent);
6116 return;
6117 }
6118
6119 setFullscreenMode(VideoFullscreenModeNone);
6120 if (auto* page = document().page())
6121 page->chrome().client().exitVideoFullscreenForVideoElement(downcast<HTMLVideoElement>(*this));
6122 }
6123}
6124
6125void HTMLMediaElement::prepareForVideoFullscreenStandby()
6126{
6127#if ENABLE(VIDEO_PRESENTATION_MODE)
6128 if (!document().page())
6129 return;
6130
6131 document().page()->chrome().client().prepareForVideoFullscreen();
6132#endif
6133}
6134
6135WEBCORE_EXPORT void HTMLMediaElement::setVideoFullscreenStandby(bool value)
6136{
6137 ASSERT(is<HTMLVideoElement>(*this));
6138 if (m_videoFullscreenStandby == value)
6139 return;
6140
6141 if (!document().page())
6142 return;
6143
6144 if (!document().page()->chrome().client().supportsVideoFullscreenStandby())
6145 return;
6146
6147 m_videoFullscreenStandby = value;
6148
6149#if ENABLE(VIDEO_PRESENTATION_MODE)
6150 if (m_player)
6151 m_player->videoFullscreenStandbyChanged();
6152#endif
6153
6154 if (m_videoFullscreenMode != VideoFullscreenModeNone)
6155 return;
6156
6157 if (m_videoFullscreenStandby)
6158 document().page()->chrome().client().enterVideoFullscreenForVideoElement(downcast<HTMLVideoElement>(*this), VideoFullscreenModeNone, m_videoFullscreenStandby);
6159 else
6160 document().page()->chrome().client().exitVideoFullscreenForVideoElement(downcast<HTMLVideoElement>(*this), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this)](auto success) mutable {
6161 m_videoFullscreenStandby = !success;
6162 });
6163}

6284bool HTMLMediaElement::hasClosedCaptions() const
6285{
6286 if (m_player && m_player->hasClosedCaptions())
6287 return true;
6288
6289 if (!m_textTracks)
6290 return false;
6291
6292 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_textTracks->length(); ++i) {
6293 auto& track = *m_textTracks->item(i);
6294 if (track.readinessState() == TextTrack::FailedToLoad)
6295 continue;
6296 if (track.kind() == TextTrack::Kind::Captions || track.kind() == TextTrack::Kind::Subtitles)
6297 return true;
6298 }
6299
6300 return false;
6301}
6302
6303bool HTMLMediaElement::closedCaptionsVisible() const
6304{
6305 return m_closedCaptionsVisible;
6306}
6307
6308bool HTMLMediaElement::textTracksAreReady() const
6309{
6310 // 4.8.10.12.1 Text track model
6311 // ...
6312 // The text tracks of a media element are ready if all the text tracks whose mode was not
6313 // in the disabled state when the element's resource selection algorithm last started now
6314 // have a text track readiness state of loaded or failed to load.
6315 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_textTracksWhenResourceSelectionBegan.size(); ++i) {
6316 if (m_textTracksWhenResourceSelectionBegan[i]->readinessState() == TextTrack::Loading
6317 || m_textTracksWhenResourceSelectionBegan[i]->readinessState() == TextTrack::NotLoaded)
6318 return false;
6319 }
6320
6321 return true;
6322}
6323
6324void HTMLMediaElement::textTrackReadyStateChanged(TextTrack* track)
6325{
6326 if (track->readinessState() != TextTrack::Loading
6327 && track->mode() != TextTrack::Mode::Disabled) {
6328 // The display trees exist as long as the track is active, in this case,
6329 // and if the same track is loaded again (for example if the src attribute was changed),
6330 // cues can be accumulated with the old ones, that's why they needs to be flushed
6331 updateTextTrackDisplay();
6332 }
6333 if (m_player && m_textTracksWhenResourceSelectionBegan.contains(track)) {
6334 if (track->readinessState() != TextTrack::Loading)
6335 setReadyState(m_player->readyState());
6336 }
6337}
6338
6339void HTMLMediaElement::configureTextTrackDisplay(TextTrackVisibilityCheckType checkType)
6340{
6341 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, checkType);
6342 ASSERT(m_textTracks);
6343
6344 if (m_processingPreferenceChange)
6345 return;
6346
6347 if (document().activeDOMObjectsAreStopped())
6348 return;
6349
6350 bool haveVisibleTextTrack = false;
6351 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_textTracks->length(); ++i) {
6352 if (m_textTracks->item(i)->mode() == TextTrack::Mode::Showing) {
6353 haveVisibleTextTrack = true;
6354 break;
6355 }
6356 }
6357
6358 if (checkType == CheckTextTrackVisibility && m_haveVisibleTextTrack == haveVisibleTextTrack) {
6359 updateActiveTextTrackCues(currentMediaTime());
6360 return;
6361 }
6362
6363 m_haveVisibleTextTrack = haveVisibleTextTrack;
6364 m_closedCaptionsVisible = m_haveVisibleTextTrack;
6365
6366 if (!m_haveVisibleTextTrack)
6367 return;
6368
6369 ensureMediaControlsShadowRoot();
6370 updateTextTrackDisplay();
6371}
6372
6373void HTMLMediaElement::updateTextTrackDisplay()
6374{
6375 ensureMediaControlsShadowRoot();
6376 if (!m_mediaControlsHost)
6377 m_mediaControlsHost = MediaControlsHost::create(*this);
6378 m_mediaControlsHost->updateTextTrackContainer();
6379}
6380
6381void HTMLMediaElement::updateTextTrackRepresentationImageIfNeeded()
6382{
6383 ensureMediaControlsShadowRoot();
6384 if (!m_mediaControlsHost)
6385 m_mediaControlsHost = MediaControlsHost::create(*this);
6386 m_mediaControlsHost->updateTextTrackRepresentationImageIfNeeded();
6387}

6399 m_player->setClosedCaptionsVisible(closedCaptionVisible);
6400
6401 markCaptionAndSubtitleTracksAsUnconfigured(Immediately);
6402 updateTextTrackDisplay();
6403}

6520bool HTMLMediaElement::shouldForceControlsDisplay() const
6521{
6522 // Always create controls for autoplay video that requires user gesture due to being in low power mode.
6523 return isVideo() && autoplay() && mediaSession().hasBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoDueToLowPowerMode);
6524}
6525
6526void HTMLMediaElement::configureMediaControls()
6527{
6528 bool requireControls = controls();
6529
6530 // Always create controls for video when fullscreen playback is required.
6531 if (isVideo() && mediaSession().requiresFullscreenForVideoPlayback())
6532 requireControls = true;
6533
6534 if (shouldForceControlsDisplay())
6535 requireControls = true;
6536
6537 // Always create controls when in full screen mode.
6538 if (isFullscreen())
6539 requireControls = true;
6540
6541#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
6542 if (m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget)
6543 requireControls = true;
6544#endif
6545
6546 if (!requireControls || !isConnected() || !inActiveDocument())
6547 return;
6548
6549 ensureMediaControlsShadowRoot();
6550}
6551
6552void HTMLMediaElement::captionPreferencesChanged()
6553{
6554 if (!isVideo())
6555 return;
6556
6557 if (m_mediaControlsHost)
6558 m_mediaControlsHost->updateCaptionDisplaySizes(MediaControlsHost::ForceUpdate::Yes);
6559
6560 if (m_player)
6561 m_player->tracksChanged();
6562
6563 if (!document().page())
6564 return;
6565
6566 CaptionUserPreferences::CaptionDisplayMode displayMode = document().page()->group().captionPreferences().captionDisplayMode();
6567 if (captionDisplayMode() == displayMode)
6568 return;
6569
6570 m_captionDisplayMode = displayMode;
6571 setWebkitClosedCaptionsVisible(captionDisplayMode() == CaptionUserPreferences::AlwaysOn);
6572}
6573
6574CaptionUserPreferences::CaptionDisplayMode HTMLMediaElement::captionDisplayMode()
6575{
6576 if (!m_captionDisplayMode) {
6577 if (document().page())
6578 m_captionDisplayMode = document().page()->group().captionPreferences().captionDisplayMode();
6579 else
6580 m_captionDisplayMode = CaptionUserPreferences::Automatic;
6581 }
6582
6583 return m_captionDisplayMode.value();
6584}
6585
6586void HTMLMediaElement::markCaptionAndSubtitleTracksAsUnconfigured(ReconfigureMode mode)
6587{
6588 if (!m_textTracks)
6589 return;
6590
6591 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
6592
6593 // Mark all tracks as not "configured" so that configureTextTracks()
6594 // will reconsider which tracks to display in light of new user preferences
6595 // (e.g. default tracks should not be displayed if the user has turned off
6596 // captions and non-default tracks should be displayed based on language
6597 // preferences if the user has turned captions on).
6598 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_textTracks->length(); ++i) {
6599 auto& track = *m_textTracks->item(i);
6600 auto kind = track.kind();
6601 if (kind == TextTrack::Kind::Subtitles || kind == TextTrack::Kind::Captions)
6602 track.setHasBeenConfigured(false);
6603 }
6604
6605 m_processingPreferenceChange = true;
6606 m_configureTextTracksTaskCancellationGroup.cancel();
6607 if (mode == Immediately) {
6608 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // configureTextTracks calls methods that can trigger arbitrary DOM mutations.
6609 configureTextTracks();
6610 }
6611 else
6612 scheduleConfigureTextTracks();
6613}
6614
6615// Use WTF_IGNORES_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS because this function does conditional locking of m_audioSourceNode->processLock()
6616// which analysis doesn't support.
6617void HTMLMediaElement::createMediaPlayer() WTF_IGNORES_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS
6618{
6619 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
6620
6621 mediaSession().setActive(true);
6622
6623#if ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO)
6624 auto protectedAudioSourceNode = makeRefPtr(m_audioSourceNode);
6625 std::optional<Locker<Lock>> audioSourceNodeLocker;
6626 if (m_audioSourceNode)
6627 audioSourceNodeLocker.emplace(m_audioSourceNode->processLock());
6628#endif
6629
6630#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
6631 detachMediaSource();
6632#endif
6633
6634 forgetResourceSpecificTracks();
6635
6636#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
6637 if (m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget)
6638 setIsPlayingToWirelessTarget(false);
6639#endif
6640
6641 m_player = MediaPlayer::create(*this);
6642 m_player->setBufferingPolicy(m_bufferingPolicy);
6643 m_player->setPreferredDynamicRangeMode(m_overrideDynamicRangeMode.value_or(preferredDynamicRangeMode(document().view())));
6644 m_player->setMuted(effectiveMuted());
6645 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
6646
6647#if ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO)
6648 if (m_audioSourceNode) {
6649 // When creating the player, make sure its AudioSourceProvider knows about the MediaElementAudioSourceNode.
6650 if (audioSourceProvider())
6651 audioSourceProvider()->setClient(m_audioSourceNode);
6652 }
6653#endif
6654
6655#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
6656 if (hasEventListeners(eventNames().webkitplaybacktargetavailabilitychangedEvent) || m_remote->hasAvailabilityCallbacks()) {
6657 m_hasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners = true;
6658 mediaSession().setHasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners(true);
6659 enqueuePlaybackTargetAvailabilityChangedEvent(); // Ensure the event listener gets at least one event.
6660 }
6661#endif
6662
6663 updateSleepDisabling();
6664}

6671
6672 if (audioSourceProvider())
6673 audioSourceProvider()->setClient(m_audioSourceNode);
6674}

6681
6682 return nullptr;

6686
6687const String& HTMLMediaElement::mediaGroup() const
6688{
6689 return m_mediaGroup;
6690}
6691
6692void HTMLMediaElement::setMediaGroup(const String& group)
6693{
6694 if (m_mediaGroup == group)
6695 return;
6696 m_mediaGroup = group;
6697
6698 // When a media element is created with a mediagroup attribute, and when a media element's mediagroup
6699 // attribute is set, changed, or removed, the user agent must run the following steps:
6700 // 1. Let m [this] be the media element in question.
6701 // 2. Let m have no current media controller, if it currently has one.
6702 setController(nullptr);
6703
6704 // 3. If m's mediagroup attribute is being removed, then abort these steps.
6705 if (group.isEmpty())
6706 return;
6707
6708 // 4. If there is another media element whose Document is the same as m's Document (even if one or both
6709 // of these elements are not actually in the Document),
6710 // FIXME: It does not seem OK that this algorithm iterates the media elements in a random order.
6711 document().forEachMediaElement([&] (HTMLMediaElement& element) {
6712 // and which also has a mediagroup attribute, and whose mediagroup attribute has the same value as
6713 // the new value of m's mediagroup attribute,
6714 if (&element != this && !controller() && element.mediaGroup() == group) {
6715 // then let controller be that media element's current media controller.
6716 setController(element.controller());
6717 }
6718 });
6719
6720 // Otherwise, let controller be a newly created MediaController.
6721 if (!controller())
6722 setController(MediaController::create(document()));
6723}
6724
6725MediaController* HTMLMediaElement::controller() const
6726{
6727 return m_mediaController.get();
6728}
6729
6730void HTMLMediaElement::setController(RefPtr<MediaController>&& controller)
6731{
6732 if (m_mediaController)
6733 m_mediaController->removeMediaElement(*this);
6734
6735 m_mediaController = WTFMove(controller);
6736
6737 if (m_mediaController)
6738 m_mediaController->addMediaElement(*this);
6739}
6740
6741void HTMLMediaElement::setControllerForBindings(MediaController* controller)
6742{
6743 // 4.8.10.11.2 Media controllers: controller attribute.
6744 // On setting, it must first remove the element's mediagroup attribute, if any,
6745 setMediaGroup({ });
6746 // and then set the current media controller to the given value.
6747 setController(controller);
6748}
6749
6750void HTMLMediaElement::updateMediaController()
6751{
6752 if (m_mediaController)
6753 m_mediaController->reportControllerState();
6754}
6755
6756bool HTMLMediaElement::isBlocked() const
6757{
6758 // A media element is a blocked media element if its readyState attribute is in the
6759 // HAVE_NOTHING state, the HAVE_METADATA state, or the HAVE_CURRENT_DATA state,
6760 if (m_readyState <= HAVE_CURRENT_DATA)
6761 return true;
6762
6763 // or if the element has paused for user interaction.
6764 return pausedForUserInteraction();
6765}
6766
6767bool HTMLMediaElement::isBlockedOnMediaController() const
6768{
6769 if (!m_mediaController)
6770 return false;
6771
6772 // A media element is blocked on its media controller if the MediaController is a blocked
6773 // media controller,
6774 if (m_mediaController->isBlocked())
6775 return true;
6776
6777 // or if its media controller position is either before the media resource's earliest possible
6778 // position relative to the MediaController's timeline or after the end of the media resource
6779 // relative to the MediaController's timeline.
6780 double mediaControllerPosition = m_mediaController->currentTime();
6781 if (mediaControllerPosition < 0 || mediaControllerPosition > duration())
6782 return true;
6783
6784 return false;
6785}
6786
6787void HTMLMediaElement::prepareMediaFragmentURI()
6788{
6789 MediaFragmentURIParser fragmentParser(m_currentSrc);
6790 MediaTime dur = durationMediaTime();
6791
6792 MediaTime start = fragmentParser.startTime();
6793 if (start.isValid() && start > MediaTime::zeroTime()) {
6794 m_fragmentStartTime = start;
6795 if (m_fragmentStartTime > dur)
6796 m_fragmentStartTime = dur;
6797 } else
6798 m_fragmentStartTime = MediaTime::invalidTime();
6799
6800 MediaTime end = fragmentParser.endTime();
6801 if (end.isValid() && end > MediaTime::zeroTime() && (!m_fragmentStartTime.isValid() || end > m_fragmentStartTime)) {
6802 m_fragmentEndTime = end;
6803 if (m_fragmentEndTime > dur)
6804 m_fragmentEndTime = dur;
6805 } else
6806 m_fragmentEndTime = MediaTime::invalidTime();
6807
6808 if (m_fragmentStartTime.isValid() && m_readyState < HAVE_FUTURE_DATA)
6809 prepareToPlay();
6810}
6811
6812void HTMLMediaElement::applyMediaFragmentURI()
6813{
6814 if (m_fragmentStartTime.isValid()) {
6815 m_sentEndEvent = false;
6816 seek(m_fragmentStartTime);
6817 }
6818}
6819
6820void HTMLMediaElement::updateSleepDisabling()
6821{
6822 SleepType shouldDisableSleep = this->shouldDisableSleep();
6823 if (shouldDisableSleep == SleepType::None && m_sleepDisabler)
6824 m_sleepDisabler = nullptr;
6825 else if (shouldDisableSleep != SleepType::None) {
6826 auto type = shouldDisableSleep == SleepType::Display ? PAL::SleepDisabler::Type::Display : PAL::SleepDisabler::Type::System;
6827 if (!m_sleepDisabler || m_sleepDisabler->type() != type)
6828 m_sleepDisabler = makeUnique<SleepDisabler>("com.apple.WebCore: HTMLMediaElement playback", type);
6829 }
6830
6831 if (m_player)
6832 m_player->setShouldDisableSleep(shouldDisableSleep == SleepType::Display);
6833}
6834
6835#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
6836static inline bool isRemoteMediaStreamVideoTrack(RefPtr<MediaStreamTrack>& item)
6837{
6838 auto* track = item.get();
6839 return track->privateTrack().type() == RealtimeMediaSource::Type::Video && !track->isCaptureTrack() && !track->isCanvas();
6840}
6841#endif
6842
6843HTMLMediaElement::SleepType HTMLMediaElement::shouldDisableSleep() const
6844{
6845#if !PLATFORM(COCOA) && !PLATFORM(GTK) && !PLATFORM(WPE)
6846 return SleepType::None;
6847#endif
6848 if (m_sentEndEvent || !m_player || m_player->paused() || loop())
6849 return SleepType::None;
6850
6851#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
6852 // If the media is playing remotely, we can't know definitively whether it has audio or video tracks.
6853 if (m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget)
6854 return SleepType::System;
6855#endif
6856
6857 if (PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().processIsSuspended())
6858 return SleepType::None;
6859
6860 bool shouldBeAbleToSleep = mediaType() != PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::VideoAudio;
6861#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
6862 // Remote media stream video tracks may have their corresponding audio tracks being played outside of the media element. Let's ensure to not IDLE the screen in that case.
6863 // FIXME: We should check that audio is being/to be played. Ideally, we would come up with a media stream agnostic heuristisc.
6864 shouldBeAbleToSleep = shouldBeAbleToSleep && !(m_mediaStreamSrcObject && WTF::anyOf(m_mediaStreamSrcObject->getTracks(), isRemoteMediaStreamVideoTrack));
6865#endif
6866
6867 if (shouldBeAbleToSleep)
6868 return SleepType::None;
6869
6870 if (m_elementIsHidden)
6871 return SleepType::System;
6872
6873 return SleepType::Display;
6874}

6880 return String();
6881
6882 return SecurityPolicy::generateReferrerHeader(document().referrerPolicy(), m_currentSrc, frame->loader().outgoingReferrer());
6883}

6892}

6894#if ENABLE(AVF_CAPTIONS)
6895
6896static inline PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind toPlatform(TextTrack::Kind kind)
6897{
6898 switch (kind) {
6899 case TextTrack::Kind::Captions:
6900 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind::Caption;
6901 case TextTrack::Kind::Chapters:
6902 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind::Chapter;
6903 case TextTrack::Kind::Descriptions:
6904 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind::Description;
6905 case TextTrack::Kind::Forced:
6906 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind::Forced;
6907 case TextTrack::Kind::Metadata:
6908 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind::MetaData;
6909 case TextTrack::Kind::Subtitles:
6910 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind::Subtitle;
6911 }
6912 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
6913 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackKind::Caption;
6914}
6915
6916static inline PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode toPlatform(TextTrack::Mode mode)
6917{
6918 switch (mode) {
6919 case TextTrack::Mode::Disabled:
6920 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode::Disabled;
6921 case TextTrack::Mode::Hidden:
6922 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode::Hidden;
6923 case TextTrack::Mode::Showing:
6924 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode::Showing;
6925 }
6926 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
6927 return PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode::Disabled;
6928}
6929
6930Vector<RefPtr<PlatformTextTrack>> HTMLMediaElement::outOfBandTrackSources()
6931{
6932 Vector<RefPtr<PlatformTextTrack>> outOfBandTrackSources;
6933 for (auto& trackElement : childrenOfType<HTMLTrackElement>(*this)) {
6934 URL url = trackElement.getNonEmptyURLAttribute(srcAttr);
6935 if (url.isEmpty())
6936 continue;
6937
6938 if (!isAllowedToLoadMediaURL(*this, url, trackElement.isInUserAgentShadowTree()))
6939 continue;
6940
6941 auto& track = trackElement.track();
6942 auto kind = track.kind();
6943
6944 // FIXME: The switch statement below preserves existing behavior where we ignore chapters and metadata tracks.
6945 // If we confirm this behavior is valuable, we should remove this comment. Otherwise, remove both comment and switch.
6946 switch (kind) {
6947 case TextTrack::Kind::Captions:
6948 case TextTrack::Kind::Descriptions:
6949 case TextTrack::Kind::Forced:
6950 case TextTrack::Kind::Subtitles:
6951 break;
6952 case TextTrack::Kind::Chapters:
6953 case TextTrack::Kind::Metadata:
6954 continue;
6955 }
6956
6957 outOfBandTrackSources.append(PlatformTextTrack::createOutOfBand(trackElement.label(), trackElement.srclang(), url.string(), toPlatform(track.mode()), toPlatform(kind), track.uniqueId(), trackElement.isDefault()));
6958 }
6959
6960 return outOfBandTrackSources;
6961}

7119
7120void HTMLMediaElement::mediaPlayerBufferedTimeRangesChanged()
7121{
7122 if (!m_textTracks || m_bufferedTimeRangesChangedTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
7123 return;
7124
7125 auto logSiteIdentifier = LOGIDENTIFIER;
7126 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "task scheduled");
7127 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_bufferedTimeRangesChangedTaskCancellationGroup, [this, logSiteIdentifier] {
7128 UNUSED_PARAM(logSiteIdentifier);
7129 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "lambda(), task fired");
7130 if (!m_player || !m_textTracks)
7131 return;
7132
7133 std::unique_ptr<PlatformTimeRanges> buffered;
7134 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_textTracks->length(); ++i) {
7135 auto& track = *m_textTracks->item(i);
7136 if (!track.shouldPurgeCuesFromUnbufferedRanges())
7137 continue;
7138
7139 if (!buffered) {
7140#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
7141 if (m_mediaSource)
7142 buffered = m_mediaSource->buffered();
7143 else
7144#endif
7145 buffered = m_player->buffered();
7146
7147 track.removeCuesNotInTimeRanges(*buffered);
7148 }
7149 }
7150 });
7151}

7162
7163void HTMLMediaElement::removeBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture(MediaElementSession::BehaviorRestrictions mask)
7164{
7165 MediaElementSession::BehaviorRestrictions restrictionsToRemove = mask &
7166 (MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForLoad
7167#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
7168 | MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToShowPlaybackTargetPicker
7169 | MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToAutoplayToExternalDevice
7170#endif
7171 | MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoRateChange
7172 | MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForAudioRateChange
7173 | MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForFullscreen
7174 | MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoDueToLowPowerMode
7175 | MediaElementSession::InvisibleAutoplayNotPermitted
7176 | MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager);
7177
7178 m_removedBehaviorRestrictionsAfterFirstUserGesture = true;
7179
7180 mediaSession().removeBehaviorRestriction(restrictionsToRemove);
7181 document().topDocument().noteUserInteractionWithMediaElement();
7182}
7183
7184void HTMLMediaElement::updateRateChangeRestrictions()
7185{
7186 const auto& document = this->document();
7187 if (!document.ownerElement() && document.isMediaDocument())
7188 return;
7189
7190 const auto& topDocument = document.topDocument();
7191 if (topDocument.videoPlaybackRequiresUserGesture())
7192 mediaSession().addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoRateChange);
7193 else
7194 mediaSession().removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoRateChange);
7195
7196 if (topDocument.audioPlaybackRequiresUserGesture())
7197 mediaSession().addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForAudioRateChange);
7198 else
7199 mediaSession().removeBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForAudioRateChange);
7200}
7201
7202RefPtr<VideoPlaybackQuality> HTMLMediaElement::getVideoPlaybackQuality()
7203{
7204 RefPtr<DOMWindow> domWindow = document().domWindow();
7205 double timestamp = domWindow ? domWindow->nowTimestamp().milliseconds() : 0;
7206
7207 auto metrics = m_player ? m_player->videoPlaybackQualityMetrics() : std::nullopt;
7208 if (!metrics)
7209 return VideoPlaybackQuality::create(timestamp, { });
7210
7211#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
7212 metrics.value().totalVideoFrames += m_droppedVideoFrames;
7213 metrics.value().droppedVideoFrames += m_droppedVideoFrames;
7214#endif
7215
7216 return VideoPlaybackQuality::create(timestamp, metrics.value());
7217}

7219DOMWrapperWorld& HTMLMediaElement::ensureIsolatedWorld()

7221 if (!m_isolatedWorld)

7223 return *m_isolatedWorld;

7225
7226bool HTMLMediaElement::ensureMediaControlsInjectedScript()
7227{
7228 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
7229
7230 Page* page = document().page();
7231 if (!page)
7232 return false;
7233
7234 auto mediaControlsScripts = RenderTheme::singleton().mediaControlsScripts();
7235 if (mediaControlsScripts.isEmpty())
7236 return false;
7237
7238 return setupAndCallJS([mediaControlsScripts = WTFMove(mediaControlsScripts)](JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, ScriptController& scriptController, DOMWrapperWorld& world) {
7239 auto& vm = globalObject.vm();
7240 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
7241
7242 auto reportExceptionAndReturnFalse = [&] () -> bool {
7243 auto* exception = scope.exception();
7244 scope.clearException();
7245 reportException(&globalObject, exception);
7246 return false;
7247 };
7248
7249 auto functionValue = globalObject.get(&lexicalGlobalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "createControls"));
7250 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
7251 if (functionValue.isCallable(vm))
7252 return true;
7253
7254 for (auto& mediaControlsScript : mediaControlsScripts) {
7255 if (mediaControlsScript.isEmpty())
7256 continue;
7257 scriptController.evaluateInWorldIgnoringException(ScriptSourceCode(mediaControlsScript), world);
7258 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
7259 }
7260
7261 return true;
7262 });
7263}

7270
7271 setControllerJSProperty("pageScaleFactor", JSC::jsNumber(page->pageScaleFactor()));

7273
7274void HTMLMediaElement::updateUsesLTRUserInterfaceLayoutDirectionJSProperty()
7275{
7276 Page* page = document().page();
7277 if (!page)
7278 return;
7279
7280 bool usesLTRUserInterfaceLayoutDirectionProperty = page->userInterfaceLayoutDirection() == UserInterfaceLayoutDirection::LTR;
7281 setControllerJSProperty("usesLTRUserInterfaceLayoutDirection", JSC::jsBoolean(usesLTRUserInterfaceLayoutDirectionProperty));
7282}
7283
7284void HTMLMediaElement::setControllerJSProperty(const char* propertyName, JSC::JSValue propertyValue)
7285{
7286 setupAndCallJS([this, propertyName, propertyValue](JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, ScriptController&, DOMWrapperWorld&) {
7287 auto& vm = globalObject.vm();
7288 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
7289
7290 auto controllerValue = controllerJSValue(lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, *this);
7291 EXCEPTION_ASSERT_UNUSED(scope, !scope.exception() || controllerValue.isNull());
7292 if (controllerValue.isNull())
7293 return false;
7294
7295 JSC::PutPropertySlot propertySlot(controllerValue);
7296 auto* controllerObject = controllerValue.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7297 if (!controllerObject)
7298 return false;
7299
7300 scope.release();
7301 controllerObject->methodTable(vm)->put(controllerObject, &lexicalGlobalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, propertyName), propertyValue, propertySlot);
7302
7303 return true;
7304 });
7305}
7306
7307void HTMLMediaElement::didAddUserAgentShadowRoot(ShadowRoot& root)
7308{
7309 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
7310
7311 if (!ensureMediaControlsInjectedScript())
7312 return;
7313
7314 setupAndCallJS([this, &root](JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, ScriptController&, DOMWrapperWorld&) {
7315 auto& vm = globalObject.vm();
7316 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
7317
7318 // The media controls script must provide a method with the following details.
7319 // Name: createControls
7320 // Parameters:
7321 // 1. The ShadowRoot element that will hold the controls.
7322 // 2. This object (and HTMLMediaElement).
7323 // 3. The MediaControlsHost object.
7324 // Return value:
7325 // A reference to the created media controller instance.
7326
7327 auto functionValue = globalObject.get(&lexicalGlobalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "createControls"));
7328 if (functionValue.isUndefinedOrNull())
7329 return false;
7330
7331 if (!m_mediaControlsHost)
7332 m_mediaControlsHost = MediaControlsHost::create(*this);
7333
7334 auto mediaJSWrapper = toJS(&lexicalGlobalObject, &globalObject, *this);
7335 auto mediaControlsHostJSWrapper = toJS(&lexicalGlobalObject, &globalObject, *m_mediaControlsHost);
7336
7337 JSC::MarkedArgumentBuffer argList;
7338 argList.append(toJS(&lexicalGlobalObject, &globalObject, root));
7339 argList.append(mediaJSWrapper);
7340 argList.append(mediaControlsHostJSWrapper);
7341 ASSERT(!argList.hasOverflowed());
7342
7343 auto reportExceptionAndReturnFalse = [&] () -> bool {
7344 auto* exception = scope.exception();
7345 scope.clearException();
7346 reportException(&globalObject, exception);
7347 return false;
7348 };
7349
7350 auto* function = functionValue.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7351 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
7352 auto callData = JSC::getCallData(vm, function);
7353 if (callData.type == JSC::CallData::Type::None)
7354 return false;
7355
7356
7357 auto controllerValue = JSC::call(&lexicalGlobalObject, function, callData, &globalObject, argList);
7358 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
7359
7360 auto* controllerObject = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSObject*>(vm, controllerValue);
7361 if (!controllerObject)
7362 return false;
7363
7364 // Connect the Media, MediaControllerHost, and Controller so the GC knows about their relationship
7365 auto* mediaJSWrapperObject = mediaJSWrapper.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7366 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
7367 auto controlsHost = JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "controlsHost");
7368
7369 ASSERT(!mediaJSWrapperObject->hasProperty(&lexicalGlobalObject, controlsHost));
7370
7371 mediaJSWrapperObject->putDirect(vm, controlsHost, mediaControlsHostJSWrapper, JSC::PropertyAttribute::DontDelete | JSC::PropertyAttribute::DontEnum | JSC::PropertyAttribute::ReadOnly);
7372
7373 auto* mediaControlsHostJSWrapperObject = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSObject*>(vm, mediaControlsHostJSWrapper);
7374 if (!mediaControlsHostJSWrapperObject)
7375 return false;
7376
7377 auto controller = JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "controller");
7378
7379 ASSERT(!controllerObject->hasProperty(&lexicalGlobalObject, controller));
7380
7381 mediaControlsHostJSWrapperObject->putDirect(vm, controller, controllerValue, JSC::PropertyAttribute::DontDelete | JSC::PropertyAttribute::DontEnum | JSC::PropertyAttribute::ReadOnly);
7382
7383 updatePageScaleFactorJSProperty();
7384 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
7385
7386 updateUsesLTRUserInterfaceLayoutDirectionJSProperty();
7387 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, reportExceptionAndReturnFalse());
7388
7389 return true;
7390 });
7391}
7392
7393void HTMLMediaElement::setMediaControlsDependOnPageScaleFactor(bool dependsOnPageScale)
7394{
7395 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, dependsOnPageScale);
7396
7397 if (document().settings().mediaControlsScaleWithPageZoom()) {
7398 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "forced to false by Settings value");
7399 m_mediaControlsDependOnPageScaleFactor = false;
7400 return;
7401 }
7402
7403 m_mediaControlsDependOnPageScaleFactor = dependsOnPageScale;
7404}
7405
7406void HTMLMediaElement::updateMediaControlsAfterPresentationModeChange()
7407{
7408 // Don't execute script if the controls script hasn't been injected yet, or we have
7409 // stopped/suspended the object.
7410 if (!m_mediaControlsHost || document().activeDOMObjectsAreSuspended() || document().activeDOMObjectsAreStopped())
7411 return;
7412
7413#if !ENABLE(MODERN_MEDIA_CONTROLS)
7414 setupAndCallJS([this](JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, ScriptController&, DOMWrapperWorld&) {
7415 auto& vm = globalObject.vm();
7416 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
7417
7418 auto controllerValue = controllerJSValue(lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, *this);
7419 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, false);
7420 auto* controllerObject = controllerValue.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7421 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, false);
7422
7423 auto functionValue = controllerObject->get(&lexicalGlobalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "handlePresentationModeChange"));
7424 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()) || functionValue.isUndefinedOrNull())
7425 return false;
7426
7427 auto* function = functionValue.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7428 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, false);
7429 auto callData = JSC::getCallData(vm, function);
7430 if (callData.type == JSC::CallData::Type::None)
7431 return false;
7432
7433 JSC::MarkedArgumentBuffer argList;
7434 ASSERT(!argList.hasOverflowed());
7435 JSC::call(&lexicalGlobalObject, function, callData, controllerObject, argList);
7436
7437 return true;
7438 });
7439#endif // !ENABLE(MODERN_MEDIA_CONTROLS)
7440}

7453String HTMLMediaElement::getCurrentMediaControlsStatus()
7454{
7455 ensureMediaControlsShadowRoot();
7456
7457 String status;
7458 setupAndCallJS([this, &status](JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, ScriptController&, DOMWrapperWorld&) {
7459 auto& vm = globalObject.vm();
7460 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
7461
7462 auto controllerValue = controllerJSValue(lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, *this);
7463 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, false);
7464 auto* controllerObject = controllerValue.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7465 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, false);
7466
7467 auto functionValue = controllerObject->get(&lexicalGlobalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "getCurrentControlsStatus"));
7468 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()) || functionValue.isUndefinedOrNull())
7469 return false;
7470
7471 auto* function = functionValue.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7472 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, false);
7473 auto callData = JSC::getCallData(vm, function);
7474 JSC::MarkedArgumentBuffer argList;
7475 ASSERT(!argList.hasOverflowed());
7476 if (callData.type == JSC::CallData::Type::None)
7477 return false;
7478
7479 auto outputValue = JSC::call(&lexicalGlobalObject, function, callData, controllerObject, argList);
7480
7481 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, false);
7482
7483 status = outputValue.getString(&lexicalGlobalObject);
7484 return true;
7485 });
7486
7487 return status;

7507
7508PlatformMediaSession::MediaType HTMLMediaElement::mediaType() const
7509{
7510 if (m_player && m_readyState >= HAVE_METADATA) {
7511 auto hasVideo = this->hasVideo();
7512 if (hasVideo && hasAudio() && !muted())
7513 return PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::VideoAudio;
7514 return hasVideo ? PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::Video : PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::Audio;
7515 }
7516
7517 return presentationType();
7518}
7519
7520PlatformMediaSession::MediaType HTMLMediaElement::presentationType() const
7521{
7522 if (hasTagName(HTMLNames::videoTag))
7523 return muted() ? PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::Video : PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::VideoAudio;
7524
7525 return PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::Audio;
7526}
7527
7528PlatformMediaSession::DisplayType HTMLMediaElement::displayType() const
7529{
7530 if (m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard)
7531 return PlatformMediaSession::Fullscreen;
7532 if (m_videoFullscreenMode & VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture)
7533 return PlatformMediaSession::Optimized;
7534 if (m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeNone)
7535 return PlatformMediaSession::Normal;
7536
7537 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
7538 return PlatformMediaSession::Normal;
7539}
7540
7541bool HTMLMediaElement::canProduceAudio() const
7542{
7543#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
7544 // Because the remote target could unmute playback without notifying us, we must assume
7545 // that we may be playing audio.
7546 if (m_isPlayingToWirelessTarget)
7547 return true;
7548#endif
7549
7550 if (isSuspended())
7551 return false;
7552
7553 if (muted())
7554 return false;
7555
7556 if (m_player && m_readyState >= HAVE_METADATA)
7557 return hasAudio();
7558
7559 return hasEverHadAudio();
7560}

7596
7597String HTMLMediaElement::mediaSessionTitle() const
7598{
7599 if (!document().page() || document().page()->usesEphemeralSession())
7600 return emptyString();
7601
7602 auto title = String(attributeWithoutSynchronization(titleAttr)).stripWhiteSpace().simplifyWhiteSpace();
7603 if (!title.isEmpty())
7604 return title;
7605
7606 title = document().title().stripWhiteSpace().simplifyWhiteSpace();
7607 if (!title.isEmpty())
7608 return title;
7609
7610 title = m_currentSrc.host().toString();
7611#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
7612 if (!title.isEmpty())
7613 title = decodeHostName(title);
7614#endif
7615 if (!title.isEmpty()) {
7616 auto domain = RegistrableDomain { m_currentSrc };
7617 if (!domain.isEmpty())
7618 title = domain.string();
7619 }
7620
7621 return title;
7622}

7634
7635void HTMLMediaElement::didReceiveRemoteControlCommand(PlatformMediaSession::RemoteControlCommandType command, const PlatformMediaSession::RemoteCommandArgument& argument)
7636{
7637 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, command);
7638
7639 UserGestureIndicator remoteControlUserGesture(ProcessingUserGesture, &document());
7640 const double defaultSkipAmount = 15;
7641 switch (command) {
7642 case PlatformMediaSession::PlayCommand:
7643 play();
7644 break;
7645 case PlatformMediaSession::StopCommand:
7646 case PlatformMediaSession::PauseCommand:
7647 pause();
7648 break;
7649 case PlatformMediaSession::TogglePlayPauseCommand:
7650 canPlay() ? play() : pause();
7651 break;
7652 case PlatformMediaSession::BeginSeekingBackwardCommand:
7653 beginScanning(Backward);
7654 break;
7655 case PlatformMediaSession::BeginSeekingForwardCommand:
7656 beginScanning(Forward);
7657 break;
7658 case PlatformMediaSession::EndSeekingBackwardCommand:
7659 case PlatformMediaSession::EndSeekingForwardCommand:
7660 endScanning();
7661 break;
7662 case PlatformMediaSession::BeginScrubbingCommand:
7663 beginScrubbing();
7664 break;
7665 case PlatformMediaSession::EndScrubbingCommand:
7666 endScrubbing();
7667 break;
7668 case PlatformMediaSession::SkipForwardCommand: {
7669 auto delta = argument.time ? argument.time.value() : defaultSkipAmount;
7670 handleSeekToPlaybackPosition(std::min(currentTime() + delta, duration()));
7671 break;
7672 }
7673 case PlatformMediaSession::SkipBackwardCommand: {
7674 auto delta = argument.time ? argument.time.value() : defaultSkipAmount;
7675 handleSeekToPlaybackPosition(std::max(currentTime() - delta, 0.));
7676 break;
7677 }
7678 case PlatformMediaSession::SeekToPlaybackPositionCommand:
7679 ASSERT(argument.time);
7680 if (argument.time)
7681 handleSeekToPlaybackPosition(argument.time.value());
7682 break;
7683 default:
7684 { } // Do nothing
7685 }
7686}
7687
7688bool HTMLMediaElement::supportsSeeking() const
7689{
7690 return !document().quirks().needsSeekingSupportDisabled();
7691}
7692
7693bool HTMLMediaElement::shouldOverrideBackgroundPlaybackRestriction(PlatformMediaSession::InterruptionType type) const
7694{
7695 if (type == PlatformMediaSession::EnteringBackground) {
7696 if (isPlayingToExternalTarget()) {
7697 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning true because isPlayingToExternalTarget() is true");
7698 return true;
7699 }
7700 if (PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().isPlayingToAutomotiveHeadUnit()) {
7701 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning true because isPlayingToAutomotiveHeadUnit() is true");
7702 return true;
7703 }
7704 if (m_videoFullscreenMode & VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture)
7705 return true;
7706#if PLATFORM(COCOA) && ENABLE(VIDEO_PRESENTATION_MODE)
7707 if (((m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModeStandard) || m_videoFullscreenStandby) && supportsPictureInPicture() && isPlaying())
7708 return true;
7709#endif
7710#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
7711 if (hasMediaStreamSrcObject() && mediaState().containsAny(MediaProducer::MediaState::IsPlayingAudio) && document().mediaState().containsAny(MediaProducer::MediaState::HasActiveAudioCaptureDevice)) {
7712 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning true because playing an audio MediaStreamTrack");
7713 return true;
7714 }
7715#endif
7716 } else if (type == PlatformMediaSession::SuspendedUnderLock) {
7717 if (isPlayingToExternalTarget()) {
7718 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning true because isPlayingToExternalTarget() is true");
7719 return true;
7720 }
7721 if (PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().isPlayingToAutomotiveHeadUnit()) {
7722 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning true because isPlayingToAutomotiveHeadUnit() is true");
7723 return true;
7724 }
7725#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
7726 if (hasMediaStreamSrcObject() && mediaState().containsAny(MediaProducer::MediaState::IsPlayingAudio) && document().mediaState().containsAny(MediaProducer::MediaState::HasActiveAudioCaptureDevice)) {
7727 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning true because playing an audio MediaStreamTrack");
7728 return true;
7729 }
7730#endif
7731 }
7732 return false;
7733}

7736{
7737 return document().processingUserGestureForMedia();
7738}

7751#endif

7753
7754#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
7755
7756void HTMLMediaElement::scheduleUpdateMediaState()
7757{
7758 if (m_updateMediaStateTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
7759 return;
7760
7761 auto logSiteIdentifier = LOGIDENTIFIER;
7762 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "task scheduled");
7763 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_updateMediaStateTaskCancellationGroup, [this, logSiteIdentifier] {
7764 UNUSED_PARAM(logSiteIdentifier);
7765 ALWAYS_LOG(logSiteIdentifier, "lambda(), task fired");
7766 Ref<HTMLMediaElement> protectedThis(*this); // updateMediaState calls methods that can trigger arbitrary DOM mutations.
7767 updateMediaState();
7768 });
7769}
7770
7771void HTMLMediaElement::updateMediaState()
7772{
7773 MediaProducer::MediaStateFlags state = mediaState();
7774 if (m_mediaState == state)
7775 return;
7776
7777 m_mediaState = state;
7778 mediaSession().mediaStateDidChange(m_mediaState);
7779
7780 document().updateIsPlayingMedia();
7781}
7782#endif
7783
7784MediaProducer::MediaStateFlags HTMLMediaElement::mediaState() const
7785{
7786 MediaStateFlags state;
7787
7788 bool hasActiveVideo = isVideo() && hasVideo();
7789 bool hasAudio = this->hasAudio();
7790 if (isPlayingToExternalTarget())
7791 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::IsPlayingToExternalDevice);
7792
7793#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
7794 if (m_hasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListeners) {
7795 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::HasPlaybackTargetAvailabilityListener);
7796 if (!mediaSession().wirelessVideoPlaybackDisabled())
7797 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::RequiresPlaybackTargetMonitoring);
7798 }
7799
7800 bool requireUserGesture = m_mediaSession && mediaSession().hasBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToAutoplayToExternalDevice);
7801 if (m_readyState >= HAVE_METADATA && !requireUserGesture && !m_failedToPlayToWirelessTarget)
7802 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::ExternalDeviceAutoPlayCandidate);
7803
7804 if (hasActiveVideo || hasAudio)
7805 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::HasAudioOrVideo);
7806
7807 if (hasActiveVideo && endedPlayback())
7808 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::DidPlayToEnd);
7809#endif
7810
7811 if (!isPlaying())
7812 return state;
7813
7814 // For GStreamer ports the semantics of IsPlayingAudio slightly differ from Apple ports. The
7815 // webkit_web_view_is_playing_audio() API is expected to return true if a page is producing
7816 // audio even though it might be muted.
7817 bool isPlayingAudio = hasAudio && volume();
7818#if !USE(GSTREAMER)
7819 isPlayingAudio = isPlayingAudio && !muted();
7820#endif
7821 if (isPlayingAudio)
7822 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::IsPlayingAudio);
7823
7824 if (hasActiveVideo)
7825 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::IsPlayingVideo);
7826
7827 return state;
7828}
7829
7830void HTMLMediaElement::handleAutoplayEvent(AutoplayEvent event)
7831{
7832 if (Page* page = document().page()) {
7833 bool hasAudio = this->hasAudio() && !muted() && volume();
7834 bool wasPlaybackPrevented = m_autoplayEventPlaybackState == AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay;
7835 bool hasMainContent = m_mediaSession && m_mediaSession->isMainContentForPurposesOfAutoplayEvents();
7836 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "hasAudio = ", hasAudio, " wasPlaybackPrevented = ", wasPlaybackPrevented, " hasMainContent = ", hasMainContent);
7837
7838 OptionSet<AutoplayEventFlags> flags;
7839 if (hasAudio)
7840 flags.add(AutoplayEventFlags::HasAudio);
7841 if (wasPlaybackPrevented)
7842 flags.add(AutoplayEventFlags::PlaybackWasPrevented);
7843 if (hasMainContent)
7844 flags.add(AutoplayEventFlags::MediaIsMainContent);
7845
7846 page->chrome().client().handleAutoplayEvent(event, flags);
7847 }
7848}
7849
7850void HTMLMediaElement::userDidInterfereWithAutoplay()
7851{
7852 if (m_autoplayEventPlaybackState != AutoplayEventPlaybackState::StartedWithoutUserGesture)
7853 return;
7854
7855 // Only consider interference in the first 10 seconds of automatic playback.
7856 if (currentTime() - playbackStartedTime() > AutoplayInterferenceTimeThreshold)
7857 return;
7858
7859 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
7860 handleAutoplayEvent(AutoplayEvent::UserDidInterfereWithPlayback);
7861 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::None);
7862}
7863
7864void HTMLMediaElement::setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState reason)
7865{
7866 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, reason);
7867
7868 m_autoplayEventPlaybackState = reason;
7869
7870 if (reason == AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay) {
7871 dispatchPlayPauseEventsIfNeedsQuirks();
7872 handleAutoplayEvent(AutoplayEvent::DidPreventMediaFromPlaying);
7873 }
7874}
7875
7876void HTMLMediaElement::pageMutedStateDidChange()
7877{
7878 if (Page* page = document().page()) {
7879 // Propagate the new state to the platform player.
7880 if (m_player)
7881 m_player->setMuted(page->isAudioMuted());
7882 if (hasAudio() && !muted() && page->isAudioMuted())
7883 userDidInterfereWithAutoplay();
7884 }
7885}
7886
7887double HTMLMediaElement::effectiveVolume() const
7888{
7889 auto* page = document().page();
7890 double volumeMultiplier = page ? page->mediaVolume() : 1;
7891 if (m_mediaController)
7892 volumeMultiplier *= m_mediaController->volume();
7893 return m_volume * volumeMultiplier;
7894}
7895
7896bool HTMLMediaElement::effectiveMuted() const
7897{
7898 return muted() || (m_mediaController && m_mediaController->muted()) || (document().page() && document().page()->isAudioMuted());
7899}
7900
7901bool HTMLMediaElement::doesHaveAttribute(const AtomString& attribute, AtomString* value) const
7902{
7903 QualifiedName attributeName(nullAtom(), attribute, nullAtom());
7904
7905 auto& elementValue = attributeWithoutSynchronization(attributeName);
7906 if (elementValue.isNull())
7907 return false;
7908
7909 if (attributeName == HTMLNames::x_itunes_inherit_uri_query_componentAttr && !document().settings().enableInheritURIQueryComponent())
7910 return false;
7911
7912 if (value)
7913 *value = elementValue;
7914
7915 return true;
7916}

7918void HTMLMediaElement::setBufferingPolicy(BufferingPolicy policy)
7919{
7920 if (policy == m_bufferingPolicy)
7921 return;
7922
7923 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, policy);
7924
7925 m_bufferingPolicy = policy;
7926 if (m_player)
7927 m_player->setBufferingPolicy(policy);
7928}
7929
7930void HTMLMediaElement::purgeBufferedDataIfPossible()
7931{
7932 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
7933
7934 if (!MemoryPressureHandler::singleton().isUnderMemoryPressure() && mediaSession().preferredBufferingPolicy() == BufferingPolicy::Default)
7935 return;
7936
7937 if (isPlayingToExternalTarget()) {
7938 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "early return because playing to wireless target");
7939 return;
7940 }
7941
7942 setBufferingPolicy(BufferingPolicy::PurgeResources);
7943}
7944
7945bool HTMLMediaElement::canSaveMediaData() const
7946{
7947 if (m_player)
7948 return m_player->canSaveMediaData();
7949
7950 return false;
7951}

7953void HTMLMediaElement::allowsMediaDocumentInlinePlaybackChanged()
7954{
7955 if (potentiallyPlaying() && mediaSession().requiresFullscreenForVideoPlayback() && !isFullscreen())
7956 enterFullscreen();
7957}
7958
7959bool HTMLMediaElement::isVideoTooSmallForInlinePlayback()
7960{
7961 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
7962
7963 if (!renderer || !is<RenderVideo>(*renderer))
7964 return true;
7965
7966 IntRect videoBox = downcast<RenderVideo>(*renderer).videoBox();
7967 return (videoBox.width() <= 1 || videoBox.height() <= 1);
7968}
7969
7970void HTMLMediaElement::isVisibleInViewportChanged()
7971{
7972 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, [this] {
7973 if (isContextStopped())
7974 return;
7975 mediaSession().isVisibleInViewportChanged();
7976 updateShouldAutoplay();
7977 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
7978 });
7979}
7980
7981void HTMLMediaElement::updateShouldAutoplay()
7982{
7983 if (!autoplay())
7984 return;
7985
7986 if (!mediaSession().hasBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::InvisibleAutoplayNotPermitted))
7987 return;
7988
7989 bool canAutoplay = mediaSession().autoplayPermitted();
7990 if (canAutoplay
7991 && mediaSession().state() == PlatformMediaSession::Interrupted
7992 && mediaSession().interruptionType() == PlatformMediaSession::InvisibleAutoplay)
7993 mediaSession().endInterruption(PlatformMediaSession::MayResumePlaying);
7994 else if (!canAutoplay
7995 && mediaSession().state() != PlatformMediaSession::Interrupted)
7996 mediaSession().beginInterruption(PlatformMediaSession::InvisibleAutoplay);
7997}
7998
7999void HTMLMediaElement::updateShouldPlay()
8000{
8001 if (!paused() && !mediaSession().playbackStateChangePermitted(MediaPlaybackState::Playing)) {
8002 scheduleRejectPendingPlayPromises(DOMException::create(NotAllowedError));
8003 pauseInternal();
8004 setAutoplayEventPlaybackState(AutoplayEventPlaybackState::PreventedAutoplay);
8005 } else if (canTransitionFromAutoplayToPlay())
8006 play();
8007}
8008
8009void HTMLMediaElement::resetPlaybackSessionState()
8010{
8011 if (m_mediaSession)
8012 m_mediaSession->resetPlaybackSessionState();
8013}
8014
8015bool HTMLMediaElement::isVisibleInViewport() const
8016{
8017 auto renderer = this->renderer();
8018 return renderer && renderer->visibleInViewportState() == VisibleInViewportState::Yes;
8019}

8021void HTMLMediaElement::schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate()
8022{
8023 Page* page = document().page();
8024 if (!page)
8025 return;
8026 page->schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
8027}
8028
8029void HTMLMediaElement::playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTimerFired()
8030{
8031 if (m_playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTaskCancellationGroup.hasPendingTask())
8032 return;
8033
8034 if (!mediaSession().hasBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureToControlControlsManager))
8035 return;
8036
8037 queueCancellableTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::MediaElement, m_playbackControlsManagerBehaviorRestrictionsTaskCancellationGroup, [this] () {
8038 auto& mediaElementSession = mediaSession();
8039 if (isPlaying() || mediaElementSession.state() == PlatformMediaSession::Autoplaying || mediaElementSession.state() == PlatformMediaSession::Playing)
8040 return;
8041
8042 mediaElementSession.addBehaviorRestriction(MediaElementSession::RequirePlaybackToControlControlsManager);
8043 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
8044 });
8045}
8046
8047bool HTMLMediaElement::shouldOverrideBackgroundLoadingRestriction() const
8048{
8049 if (isPlayingToExternalTarget())
8050 return true;
8051
8052 return m_videoFullscreenMode == VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture;
8053}
8054
8055void HTMLMediaElement::setFullscreenMode(VideoFullscreenMode mode)
8056{
8057 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "changed from ", fullscreenMode(), ", to ", mode);
8058#if ENABLE(VIDEO_PRESENTATION_MODE)
8059 scheduleEvent(eventNames().webkitpresentationmodechangedEvent);
8060#endif
8061
8062 setPreparedToReturnVideoLayerToInline(mode != HTMLMediaElementEnums::VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture);
8063
8064#if ENABLE(VIDEO_PRESENTATION_MODE)
8065 if (player())
8066 player()->setVideoFullscreenMode(mode);
8067#endif
8068
8069 m_videoFullscreenMode = mode;
8070 visibilityStateChanged();
8071 schedulePlaybackControlsManagerUpdate();
8072}
